Marcus Antistius Labeo ( d. 10 or 11 AD ) was an Ancient Roman jurist of the gens Antistia .
Sir Daniel Ford Goddard PC ( 17 January 1850 -- 6 May 1922 ) was a British civil engineer , businessman and Liberal Party politician who served as a Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Ipswich from 1895 to 1918 .
Louis Gantois ( November 15 , 1929 -- 2011 ) was a French sprint canoer who competed in the early to mid-1950s .
James Begbie FRSE FRCPE FRCSE ( October 1798 , Edinburgh -- 26 August 1869 , Edinburgh ) was a Scottish medical doctor who served as president of the Medico - Chirurgical Society of Edinburgh ( 1850 - -2 ) and as president of the Royal College of Physicians of Edinburgh ( 1854 - -6 ) .
Botulf Botulfsson ( died April 1311 ) , from Gottröra , Uppland , was a Swedish man burned at the stake for heresy .
Walter S. Johnson ( 1884 - -1978 ) was a notable businessman and philanthropist in San Francisco , California .
Charles M. Bair ( 1857 -- 1943 ) was an early railroading businessman who also became one of the largest sheep ranchers in the United States .
Charles Howard Carter ( 1927 - 1990 ) was professor of History at Tulane University from 1963 to 1990 .
Alfred Lubbock ( 31 October 1845 -- 17 July 1916 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Kent and the Marylebone Cricket Club between 1863 and 1875 .
Herbert Henry Gowen ( 1864 - -1960 ) was an Anglican missionary and Orientalist .
Edmund Hickeringill ( 1631 - -1708 ) was an English churchman who lived during the period of the Commonwealth and the Restoration .
Giovanni Pontiero ( 10 February 1932 - 10 February 1996 ) was a British scholar and translator of Portuguese fiction , most notably the works of José Saramago .
Christian Haren ( February 1 , 1935 -- February 27 , 1996 ) was an American actor , model and community activist .
James Dixon Boyd ( 29 September 1907 -- 7 February 1968 ) was an Irish - American Professor of Anatomy , Cambridge University from 1951 until his death and a Fellow of Clare College , Cambridge .
He was consecrated as Mar Thoma V. On 24 March 1728 Mar Thoma IV died and was laid to rest at Kandanad Palli ( Kandanad Martha Mariam Syriac Orthodox Church ) .
Lieutenant - Colonel William Osborne Smith ( 1833 -- 11 May 1887 ) served as the first Acting Commissioner of the North - West Mounted Police , from 25 September to 17 October 1873 .
Akiva Govrin ( Hebrew : עקיבא גוברין‎ , born 12 August 1902 , died 26 June 1980 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a government minister between December 1963 and January 1966 , and was the country 's first Minister of Tourism .
Pietro Guarienti ( c. 1700 - -1765 ) was an Italian painter and art - biographer of the late - Baroque period , active mainly in Bologna .
Minamoto no Yoshitsuna ( 源 義綱 ) ( c. 1042 -- 1134 ) , also called Kamo Jirō ( 鴨 次郎 ) , was a samurai of the Minamoto clan , and brother of Minamoto no Yoshiie .
William Fraser , 12th Lord Saltoun ( 1654 - -1715 ) , was a Scottish peer and the 11th Laird of Philorth .
Kim Seong - il ( Hangul : 김성일 ; 1538 - -1593 ) was a Joseon Dynasty politician .
Anne Cobden - Sanderson or Julia Sarah Anne Cobden ( 26 March 1853 -- 2 November 1926 ) was a British socialist and suffragette .
Alphonse Chapanis ( 1917 - -2002 ) was a pioneer in the field of industrial design , and is widely considered one of the fathers of ergonomics or human factors - the science of ensuring that design takes account of human characteristics .
Erasmus Earle ( 15 September 1590 -- 10 September 1667 ) was an English lawyer and politician , who became sergeant - at - law to Oliver Cromwell .
Horatio Hathaway ( 1831 - 1898 ) was a New England industrialist , politician , and philanthropist and namesake of Berkshire Hathaway .
Robert Bertie , 3rd Earl of Lindsey PC FRS ( 8 November 1630 - 8 May 1701 ) , styled Lord Willoughby de Eresby from 1642 to 1666 , was an English nobleman .
Henryk Hechtkopf ( Hebrew : הנריק הכטקופף‎ ; April 4 , 1910 -- July 2004 ) was an artist , painter , and illustrator .
Jack Haw ( 27 December 1902 -- 29 April 1975 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Giovanni Battista Cirri ( 1 October 1724 -- 11 June 1808 ) was an Italian cellist and composer in the 18th century .
Edmund Freke ( also spelled Freake or Freak ; c. 1516 - -1591 ) was an English dean and bishop .
Mike the Headless Chicken ( April 1945 -- March 1947 ) , also known as Miracle Mike , was a Wyandotte chicken that lived for 18 months after his head had been cut off .
Khalid ibn Abi Habib al - Fihri ( ? -October , 740 ) was an Arab military commander in North Africa during the Berber Revolt , who led the Arab army that was defeated at the Battle of the Nobles in late 740 .
Vince Taylor ( 14 July 1939 -- 28 August 1991 ) , born Brian Maurice Holden , was a British rock and roll singer .
Ethel Anderson ( née Campbell ) ( 16 March 1883 -- 4 August 1958 ) was an early twentieth century Australian poet , essayist , novelist and painter .
Nini Haslund Gleditsch ( 22 June 1908 -- 25 July 1996 ) was a Norwegian political activist and advocate for peace .
Liuvigild , Leuvigild , Leovigild ( Gothic : Liubagilds ) , or Leovigildo ( Spanish and Portuguese ) , ( c. 519 -- 21 April 586 ) was a Visigothic King of Hispania and Septimania from 568 to April 21 , 586 .
Thomas Grey , Lord Grey of Groby ( c. 1623 - -1657 ) , was an elected Member of Parliament for Leicester during the English Long Parliament , an active member of the Parliamentary party and a regicide .
Spencer Compton , 1st Earl of Wilmington KG KB PC ( ca 1673 -- 2 July 1743 ) was a British Whig statesman who served continuously in government from 1715 until his death .
Joost Berman ( 9 January 1793 -- 18 March 1855 ) was a Dutch lawyer , judge , poet , nonfiction writer , and editor .
Lord Walter Bagenal ( 1670 - -1745 ) was a member of the prominent Bagenal family , who resided in Dunleckney Manor in County Carlow , Ireland .
Lars Johan Hierta ( 22 January 1801 -- 20 November 1872 ) was a Swedish newspaper publisher , social critic , businessman and politician .
Stanley Mullen ( June 20 , 1911 -- 1974 ) was an American artist , short story writer , novelist and publisher .
Hugh Fernando ( died 1993 ) was a Sri Lankan politician .
Sengrui ( 僧睿 ; 371 - -438 AD ) was a Buddhist monk and scholar .
Henry I , Count of Tecklenburg ( c. 1115 -- 22 November 1156 ) was a German nobleman .
Bohumil Honzátko ( 30 December 1875 -- 12 December 1950 ) was a Czech gymnast and long - distance runner .
James Tuchet , 5th Baron Audley , 2nd Baron Tuchet ( c. 1398 - -1459 ) was an English peer .
James Hadfield or Hatfield ( 1771/1772 -- 23 January 1841 ) attempted to assassinate George III of the United Kingdom in 1800 but was acquitted of attempted murder by reason of insanity .
Hugh Miller ( 10 October 1802 -- 23/24 December 1856 ) was a self - taught Scottish geologist and writer , folklorist and an evangelical Christian .
Nehemiah Grew ( 26 September 1641 -- 25 March 1712 ) was an English plant anatomist and physiologist , known as the `` Father of Plant Anatomy '' .
Lorne Earl Blanchard ( June 6 , 1883 -- 1967 ) was an American - born machinist and political figure in Saskatchewan .
John Cayo Evans ( 1 March 1879 -- 8 March 1958 ) was a Welsh mathematician and academic .
James Worsdale ( c. 1692 -- 10 June 1767 ) was an Irish and English portrait painter , actor , literary fraud , and libertine whose lively conversation , wittiness , and boldness allowed him to move among the highest circles of literary life .
Peng Jiamu ( simplified Chinese : 彭加木 ; pinyin : Péng Jiāmù , 1925 - -1980 ) was a Chinese biochemist and explorer .
Rabbi Avraham Shlomo Zalman Zoref ( 1786 - 1851 ) , born in Kėdainiai , was one of the first pioneers who rebuilt the Ashkenazi Jewish community in Jerusalem in the beginning of the 19th century and the first recorded victim of the Arab terror in Israel .
Stjepan Kovačević ( Hungarian : István Kovacsevics ; 1841 -- 25 April 1913 ) was a Croatian politician , who served as Minister without portfolio of Croatian Affairs between 1905 and 1906 .
Andrzej Jastrzębiec , also known as Andrzej Wasilko or Andrzej Polak , ( died 1398 ) was a Polish Catholic priest and diplomat , a first bishop of Seret and of Vilnius .
Wesley Newcomb ( 1818 - -1892 ) was an American physician and a malacologist who specialized in land snails .
Sanford H. Roth ( 1906 - -1962 ) was an internationally known photographer whose work has appeared in Time , Life , Look , Fortune , Paris Match , Elle , Der Stern , Harper 's Bazaar , Vogue , Oggi , People , and other publications .
Jean - Claude Verpilleux ( 2 May 1798 - 13 October 1875 ) was a French mine laborer who became a leading engineer , manufacturer and inventor .
Abdulkadir Dheel ( Somali : Cabdulqaadir Dheel , Arabic : عبد القادر ديل‎ ) ( d. 3 July 1972 ) was a prominent Somali military figure .
Meem Hay Latifi ( Urdu : محمد حسن لطیفی ) ( b. 11 December 1905 -- 23 May 1959 ) was a renowned poet and journalist of Urdu .
Traute Foresti ( 15 March 1915 in Payerbach -- 3 April 2015 in Vienna ) was an Austrian poet and actress .
Eduard Heinrich Graeffe or Gräffe ( 27 December 1833 , Zurich -- 23 April 1916 Ljubljana ) was a Swiss zoologist and naturalist .
William Hay , 17th Earl of Erroll ( 12 March 1772 -- 26 January 1819 ) , known as Lord Hay until 1778 , was a Scottish peer .
Wolfgang Heyda ( 14 November 1913 -- 21 August 1947 ) was a German U - boat commander during World War II .
Katharine Lambert Richards Rockwell ( 1891 - 1972 ) was an American theologian , writer , and professor .
Virupaksha Raya ( 1404 - -1405 CE ) was an emperor of the Vijayanagara Empire .
Margaret Irving Handy ( 1889 - 1977 ) was a pioneering doctor who was one of the first to specialize in pediatric medicine .
Prince Jan Lubomirski ( died 1736 ) was a Polish szlachcic .
Vladimir Yazdovsky ( 1913 - -1999 ) was a Soviet space program medical scientist .
Francis Cleyn ( or Francesco Cleyn or Clein ; also Frantz or Franz Klein ) ( c. 1582 -- 1658 ) was a German - born painter and tapestry designer who lived and worked in England .
Dr Honoria Somerville Keer , MBChB ( 26 December 1883 -- 20 March 1969 ) was a British surgeon during World War I , where she served as Assistant Medical Officer with the Girton and Newnham Unit of the Scottish Women 's Hospital for Foreign Service .
Sir Thomas Chaworth ( died 1459 ) was an English landowner and Member of Parliament .
Francesco Calcagno ( 1528 - 1550 ) was a young Franciscan friar famously executed for blasphemy and sodomy by the Venetian Inquisition .
Edmund Warwick ( 15 July 1907 -- 21 December 1989 ) was a British actor who appeared in various television programmes .
Edward Waddington ( 1670?--1731 ) was an English prelate , bishop of Chichester from 1724 to 1731 .
Ralph Swillington ( died 1525 ) was Recorder of Coventry and Attorney General to Henry VIII . Swillington was Attorney General for the short period of time between 1524 and his death in the following year .
Manès Sperber ( 12 December 1905 -- 5 February 1984 ) was an Austrian - French novelist , essayist and psychologist .
Naser Beadini ( 20 May 1962 -- 16 January 1992 ) was a football forward who played for clubs in the former Yugoslavia and Turkey .
Otto Casmann ( 1562 - 1 August 1607 ) ( also known by the Latinized name Casmannus ) was a German humanist who converted from Catholicism to Protestantism as a young man .
Renaat Bosschaert ( 1938 - -2007 ) was a Belgian artist working in painting , graphic arts , sculpture , ceramic arts , engraving and printmaking .
William Henry Hurlbert ( July 3 , 1827 - -September 4 , 1895 ) was an American journalist and author of `` The Diary of a Public Man , '' published in the North American Review in 1879 .
Helen Messinger Murdoch ( 1862 - -1956 ) was an American photographer who pioneered the use of Autochromes in travel photography .
George Sturt ( 1863 - 1927 ) , who also wrote under the pseudonym George Bourne , was an English writer on rural crafts and affairs .
Sir Francis Leke , 1st Baronet ( 1627 - October 1679 ) was an English soldier , administrator and Member of Parliament .
Jarava Lal Mehta ( 1912 -- 11 July 1988 ) was an Indian philosopher , an expert on the philosophy of Martin Heidegger .
Julio García Nakpil ( born Julio Nakpil y García ; 22 May 1867 -- 2 November 1960 ) was a Filipino musician , composer and a General during the Philippine Revolution against Spain .
Brigadier Harry Kenneth Dimoline CBE MBE DSO TD CPM ( 6 September ? 1903 - -15 November 1972 ) was an artillery officer in the British and British Indian Armies during World War II .
John Weldon ( 6 September 1890 -- 4 February 1963 ; alternatively `` A. E. Weldon '' ) , known by his pen- and stage - name Brinsley MacNamara , was an Irish writer , playwright , and the registrar of the National Gallery of Ireland .
Martin Finn ( 22 August 1917 -- 7 March 1988 ) was an Irish Fine Gael politician , farmer and auctioneer .
Lord Anne Hamilton ( 12 October 1709 -- 25 December 1748 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Walter Suffield ( died 19 May 1257 ) was a medieval Bishop of Norwich .
Natko Nodilo ( 31 August 1834 , Split -- 21 May 1912 , Zagreb ) was a Croatian politician , historian , publicist , university professor and rector of the University of Zagreb .
Sir Edward Astley , 4th Baronet ( 26 December 1729 -- 27 March 1802 ) was a British politician .
Nathaniel Wells ( 10 September 1779 -- 13 May 1852 ) , was the son of a Welsh merchant and a black slave .
Gwili Andre ( 4 February 1908 -- 5 February 1959 ) was a Danish model and actress who had a brief career in Hollywood films .
Vincenzo Manenti ( also known as Vincenzio Manenti ) ( c. 1600 - 1674 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period .
William Gurnall ( 1616 -- 12 October 1679 ) was an English author and clergyman born at King 's Lynn , Norfolk , where he was baptised on 17 November 1616 .
Fujiwara no Narichika ( 藤原 成親 ) ( 1138 - -1178 ) was a Japanese court noble who took part in a plot against the Taira clan 's dominance of the Imperial court .
Sir Anthony Shirley , 1st Baronet ( 1624 - June 1683 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1654 and 1659 .
Abdelmajid Benjelloun ( 1919 - -1981 ) was a novelist , journalist and ambassador from Morocco .
Carlo Troya ( also spelled Troja ; 7 June 1784 -- 28 July 1858 ) was a historian and politician who served as Prime Minister of the Two Sicilies from 3 April 1848 until 15 May 1848 .
Hans - Georg Bohle ( 3 March 1948 -- 20 September 2014 ) was a German geographer and international development researcher .
Saint Macrina the Elder ( before 270 -- c. 340 ) was the mother of Saint Basil the Elder , and the grandmother of Basil the Great , Saint Gregory of Nyssa , Saint Peter of Sebaste , and Saint Macrina the Younger .
Eliza Lucas Pinckney ( December 28 , 1722 - -1793 ) changed agriculture in colonial South Carolina , where she developed indigo as one of its most important cash crops .
Samuel Abraham Marx ( August 27 , 1885 - January 1964 ) was an American architect , designer and interior decorator .
Nils Abraham Langlet ( 9 July 1868 - 30 March 1936 ; known by his second given name ) was a Swedish chemist .
Linnaeus Tripe ( 14 April 1822 -- 2 March 1902 ) was a British photographer , best known for his photographs of India and Burma taken in the 1850s .
Marinus of Tyre ( Greek : Μαρῖνος ὁ Τύριος , Marînos o Týrios ; c. AD 70 - -130 ) was a Greek or Hellenized geographer , cartographer and mathematician , who founded mathematical geography and provided the underpinnings of Claudius Ptolemy 's influential Geography .
Margrethe Marie Thomasine Numsen , née Ingenhaef(f ) ( 8 March 1705 -8 October 1776 ) , was a politically active Danish courtier .
Randle Wilbraham Falconer ( 1816 -- 6 May 1881 ) was a British medical writer .
Antonio Gragnani ( 1740 - -1794 ) was an Italian violin maker .
Kathleen Hamilton , Duchess of Abercorn , DCVO ( 8 July 1905 -- 2 February 1990 ) was Mistress of the Robes to Queen Elizabeth The Queen Mother from 1964 to her death in 1990 .
Saints Cyrion and Candidus ( d. 320 AD ) are ethnic Armenian saints .
Ímar ua Ímair ( Old Norse : Ívarr , died 904 ) was a Norse or Norse - Gaelic King of Dublin .
Sir John Pryce , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1596 - -ca . 1657 ) , sometimes also spelt Price , was an Anglo - Welsh Baronet and Member of Parliament .
Jacob Osgood ( 16 March 1777 -- 29 November 1844 ) was the founder of a 19th - century Christian sect in New Hampshire known as the Osgoodites .
Alice Auma ( 1956 -- 17 January 2007 ) was an Acholi spirit - medium who , as the head of the Holy Spirit Movement , led a millennial rebellion against the Ugandan government forces of President Yoweri Museveni from August 1986 until November 1987 .
Edward Dalton Marchant ( 1806 - 1887 ) , also known as Edward D. Marchant and E. D. Marchant , was an American artist .
Charles Gargotta , also known as `` Mad Dog '' , ( 1900 - -1950 ) was a Kansas City , Missouri gangster who became a top enforcer for the Kansas City crime family .
Charlie Tyson ( 14 November 1897 - 23 September 1985 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League during the 1920s .
Nicholas Grimald ( or Grimoald ) ( 1519 - -1562 ) was an English poet and dramatist .
William Walls ( 2 August 1819 -- 27 September 1893 ) was a Scottish lawyer , industrialist and Dean of Guild of Glasgow .
Donald E. Worcester ( 1915 - 2003 ) was an American historian who specialized in Southwestern United States and Latin American history .
Roger Baynes ( 1546 - -1623 ) was secretary to Cardinal Allen and an author .
Christopher Anstey ( 31 October 1724 -- 3 August 1805 ) was an English poet who also wrote in Latin .
Robert Hugh Martin ( 1896 -- 14 March 1918 ) was a British soldier who is perhaps the only known soldier to receive heart surgery during World War I. On 14 November 1917 Trooper Martin was wounded in the Salonika Campaign when he was shot by a Bulgarian soldier .
John Bowyer Nichols ( 1779 - -1863 ) was an English printer and antiquary .
Bernard John McQuaid ( New York City , 15 December 1823 -- Rochester , New York , 18 January 1909 ) was an American Catholic priest , the first Bishop of Rochester , U.S.A. and the first president of Seton Hall University .
Gilbert de Greenlaw ( 1354 - -1421 ) was a medieval Bishop of Aberdeen and Bishop - elect of St. Andrews .
Sir William Lionel Fraser CMG ( 1895 -- 2 January 1965 ) was a British banker and self - made millionaire .
Ole Konrad Ribsskog ( 8 December 1886 -- 26 January 1941 ) was a Norwegian educator and politician for the Labour and the Social Democratic Labour parties .
Mildred Sanderson ( 1889 - 1914 ) was an American mathematician , best known for her mathematical theorem concerning modular invariants .
John Francillon ( 1744 - -1816 ) was a jeweler and lapidary , an English naturalist and an entomologist of Huguenot descent .
Ernst - Günther Schenck ( 3 October 1904 -- 21 December 1998 ) was a German Obersturmbannführer ( lieutenant - colonel ) and doctor who joined the SS in 1933 .
Richard Longe ( died 1650 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1642 .
Per Ivarson Undi ( 1803 -- 28 July 1860 ) , also known as Peter Iverson , was an early Norwegian - American homesteader in Wisconsin Territory .
Arsalan Pouria ( Persian : ارسلان پوریا‎ ) ( 1930 - 4 June 1994 ) was an Iranian poet and playwright who believed in archaism .
Adolph Lippe ( 11 May 1812 near Goerlitz , Prussia -- 23 January 1888 in Philadelphia ) was a homeopathic physician who worked in the United States .
Antonino Grano ( 1660 - -1718 ) was an Italian painter and engraver , principally active in Sicily .
Pietro Farnese , also called Piero de Farneto or Petruccio di Cola ( c. 1310 -- 20 June 1363 ) was an Italian condottiero .
Vittorio Arrigoni ( 4 February 1975 -- 15 April 2011 ) was an Italian reporter , writer , pacifist and activist .
Helmut Braunlich ( born 19 May 1929 in Brünn , Moravia ; d. 24 May 2013 ) was a German - American violinist , composer , and musicologist .
Bogdan Saltanov ( Russian : Богдан Салтанов ; 1630s -- 1703 ) , also known as Ivan Ievlevich Saltanov , was a Persian - born Armenian painter at the court of Alexis I of Russia and his successors .
Max Howell ( 26 December 1921 -- 3 October 2012 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Wing Commander Walter Gibb DSO , DFC ( 26 March 1919 at Port Talbot , Wales -- 4 October 2006 ) was a flying ace and a British test pilot who twice held the world altitude record .
Thomas Benbow Phillips ( 14 February 1828 - 30 January 1915 ) was a pioneer of the Welsh settlements in Brazil and , more successfully , Patagonia during the 19th century .
Kim Chung - seon ( 1571 - -1642 ) , born name Sayaka ( 沙也可 ) and often known by his pen name Mohadang , was a Japanese general who defected to Korea during the Japanese invasion .
Thomas Darbyshire ( 1518 - -1604 ) was an English churchman and Jesuit .
Alexandre Biyidi Awala ( 30 June 1932 -- 8 October 2001 ) , known as Mongo Beti or Eza Boto , was a Cameroonian writer .
Abdullah Abdul Latif Al Othman ( Arabic : عبدالله عبد اللطيف العثمان‎ ) ( 1895 -- 1965 ) was a Kuwaiti businessman who was amongst the first to live in Hawalli .
Ion Oblemenco ( 13 May 1945 -- 1 September 1996 ) was a Romanian football striker who spent the majority of his career playing for Universitatea Craiova .
Eugenia Berlin ( 1905 -- 2003 ) was a Russian - born Canadian sculptor , painter , designer and director .
Germund Dahlquist ( 16 January 1925 -- 8 February 2005 ) was a Swedish mathematician known primarily for his early contributions to the theory of numerical analysis as applied to differential equations .
Sir Robert Parker , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1655 -- 30 November 1691 ) of Ratton , Sussex was an English politician .
Captain Alexander V. Fraser , USRM , ( April 20 , 1804 -- 1868 ) was an American seaman , who served as the first Chief of the Revenue Marine Bureau , Department of the Treasury , one of the predecessor agencies of the United States Coast Guard .
Peter von Beeck ( died February 23 , 1624 in Aachen ) was a German religious figure and a canon of the church ..
Shangguan Yunxiang ( traditional Chinese : 上官雲相 ; simplified Chinese : 上官云相 ; pinyin : Shàngguān Yúnxiàng ; 1895 - -8 August 1969 ) was a Kuomintang general from Shanghe County , Shandong .
Diego López V de Haro , nicknamed el Intruso ( c. 1250 -- 1310 ) , was a Spanish noble of the House of Haro and held the title of the Lord of Biscay which he took from the pretender to the title , John of Castile .
Haworth Watson ( 26 September 1880 -- 24 November 1951 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played twenty nine matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1908 and 1914 .
Richard Gibbons ( born at Winchester , 1550 or 1549 ; died at Douai , 23 June 1632 ) was an English Jesuit scholar .
Hysni Curri ( ? --1925 ) was a Kosovar Albanian military figure and a prominent leader of the Kachak movement and the Committee for the National Defence of Kosovo .
Edmund Sharpe ( 31 October 1809 -- 8 May 1877 ) was an English architect , architectural historian , railway engineer , and sanitary reformer .
Percy Addleshaw ( b. 1866 Bowdon , Cheshire ; d. 1916 ) was an English barrister and writer .
Wallace Arnold Oakes GC ( 23 April 1932 -- 12 June 1965 ) , known as Wally Oakes , was a train driver with British Railways who was born in Barbridge , Cheshire and lived at Wheelock Heath , Sandbach , Cheshire .
Ibrahim ibn Tashfin ( died 1147 ) was the seventh Almoravid king , who reigned shortly in 1146 - -1147 .
Franz Dischinger ( 8 October 1887 - 9 January 1953 ) was a pioneering German civil and structural engineer , responsible for the development of the modern cable - stayed bridge .
Barsauma died in 491 , according to Bar Hebraeus he was killed by monks from Tur Abdin with the keys of their cells , however he also mentions how his tomb may be found in the Church of Mar Jacob in Nisibis .
Aharon Rokeach ( 19 December 1880 -- 18 August 1957 ) was the fourth Rebbe of the Belz Hasidic dynasty .
Humphrey Berisford ( probably died ca . 1588 ) was an English recusant who was imprisoned for his adherence to Roman Catholicism , dying in prison .
Melania the Elder ( 325 - 410 ) , one of the wealthiest citizens of the empire , was born in Spain , and was related to Paulinus of Nola .
Willy Oskar Dressler ( 25 April 1876 -- 7 November 1954 ) , was a German writer on art and interior decoration .
Norm Harris ( 11 September 1906 -- 4 October 1985 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Fitnat Hanım ( died in 1780 ) was the pen name of Ottoman Turkish woman poet Zübeyde , who lived in the 18th century .
Jean - Jacques Dussumier ( 1792 - -1883 ) was a French voyager and merchant from Bordeaux .
Salomo Liscow ( 1640 , Niemitsch -- 1689 ) was a German clergyman and hymn writer .
Marko Vovchok ( Ukrainian : Марко́ Вовчо́к , real name Mariya Vilinska , Ukrainian : Марія Олександрівна Вілінська ; 22 December 1833 -- 10 August 1907 ) was a famous Ukrainian writer .
Bjørn Bue ( 30 January 1934 -- 13 April 1997 ) was a Norwegian Lutheran missionary and bishop .
Henry Perrine ( 5 April 1797 -- 7 August 1840 ) was a physician , horticulturist , United States Consul in Campeche , Campeche , Mexico , and an enthusiast for introducing tropical plants into cultivation in the United States .
David Sutherland Hibbard ( 1868 - -1966 ) was an American missionary and educator who established and served as first president of Silliman Institute , now Silliman University in Dumaguete City , Philippines .
Henry Harold Welch Pearson ( 28 January 1870 , Long Sutton , Lincolnshire - 3 November 1916 , Wynberg , Cape Town ) , was a British - born South African botanist , chiefly remembered for founding Kirstenbosch National Botanical Garden in 1913 .
Robert Straube was an American artist born in 1938 St Louis , Missouri and died in 2006 in Shoreview , Minnesota .
Nikolaos Paparrodou ( Greek : Νικόλαος Παπαρρόδου , 1902 -- 1980 ) was a Greek fencer .
Paddy Moclair ( 1908 -- 9 May 1983 ) was an Irish Gaelic footballer who played as a full - forward and as a full - back for the Mayo senior team .
Henry Clive ( 1882 - -1960 ) was an Australian - born American graphic artist and illustrator .
Dr. Jacob Seidenberg ( 1914 - -1996 ) was a government official who specialized in labor arbitration and non - discrimination contracts , and wrote extensively on labor law and negotiations .
Mihály Fincicky ( Csepely , 22 September 1842 -- Ungvár 1916 ) was a Hungarian lawyer , translator , collector of folk - songs and folk - poets , mayor of Ungcár .
Rear - Admiral Alexander Innes ( died 1786 ) was a Royal Navy officer who became Commander - in - Chief of the Jamaica Station .
Charles Bousfield Huleatt ( 1863 -- 1908 ) also known under the pseudonym of Caulifield , was an Anglican priest born in Folkestone , England .
Edwin Thorne , II ( 20 December 1914 , New York City -- 15 October 2002 , Grand Junction , Colorado ) was a member of a prominent American family .
Trevor Storton ( 26 November 1949 -- 23 March 2011 ) was an English footballer who played as a central defender .
Pandit Raghunath Prasanna ( c.1920 -- June 1999 ) was an Indian classical shehnai and flute player .
Albert Kinross ( 4 July 1870 -- 19 March 1929 ) was an English journalist , magazine editor and writer of novels , stories and articles .
Helen Gloag ( 1750 - -1790 ) , of Muthill , Perthshire , Scotland , became the Empress of Morocco .
Ove Ødegaard ( 11 April 1931 -- 15 November 1964 ) was a Norwegian footballer .
Harutiun Shahrigian ( Armenian : Հարություն Մկրտիչի Շահրիկյան ; 1860 -- 1915 ) was an Armenian politician , soldier , lawyer , and author .
Teige Ó Flaithbheartaigh ( died 1589 ) was an Irish rebel and warlord .
Anna Masterton Buchan ( 1877 - -1948 ) was a Scottish novelist who wrote under the pen name O. Douglas .
Josie McDermott ( 1925 - -1992 ) was a traditional Irish musician : a flute and tin whistle player , composer and singer .
Edward Webb ( 1779 - 1839 ) , of Adwell , near Tetsworth , Gloucestershire and 181 Piccadilly , Middlesex , was a politician .
Yang Changji ( simplified Chinese : 杨昌济 ; traditional Chinese : 楊昌濟 ; pinyin : Yáng Chāngjì ; 21 April 1871 -- 17 January 1920 ) was a Chinese educator , philosopher , and writer .
Robert Louis - Dreyfus ( 14 June 1946 -- 4 July 2009 ) was a French businessman who had major success as Chief Executive Officer ( CEO ) of Adidas - Salomon and Saatchi & Saatchi .
Minnie Blanche Bishop ( 27 December 1864 -- 16 October 1917 ) was a teacher and author in Canada .
Chen Liting ( Chinese : 陈鲤庭 ; pinyin : Chén Lǐtíng ; 20 October 1910 -- 27 August 2013 ) was a Chinese playwright , drama and film director , screenwriter , and film theorist .
Raya Rahutta Raya Vajridu Raya Mannida Raya Avadai Raghunatha Tondaiman ( died 1661 ) was a Kallar chieftain of Karambakudi and a feudatory of the Vijayanagar Empire .
Hélion de Villeneuve ( c. 1270 -- 1346 ) was a French - born Grand Master of the Knights of St. John .
General Sir Francis Reginald Wingate , 1st Baronet GCB , GCVO , GBE , KCMG , DSO , TD ( 25 June 1861 -- 29 January 1953 ) was a British general and administrator in Egypt and the Sudan .
Bruno Franz Kaulbach ( 1880 - 1963 ) was an Austrian lawyer and a member of the Kohn family from Bennisch whose descendants include the U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry .
Reginald Somerville ( 1867 -- 8 July 1948 ) was an English composer and actor .
Giorgi Avalishvili ( Georgian : გიორგი ავალიშვილი ) ( 1769 -- 1850 ) was a Georgian diplomat , writer and one of the founding fathers of the Georgian theatre .
Ezzelino I da Romano , also known as Ezzelino il Balbo ( died 1189 ) was an Italian nobleman of the Ezzelini family , who was lord of Onara , Romano , Bassano and Godego .
Johannes Anton Ullrich ( 1826 - -1895 ) was a German industrialist , inventor , and co - founder of the `` Gebrüder Ullrich '' in the Rhineland - Palatinate .
Emma Jane Catherine Cobden ( 28 April 1851 -- 7 July 1947 ) , known as Jane Cobden , was a British Liberal politician who was active in many radical causes in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries .
John Rushout , 1st Baron Northwick ( 23 July 1738 -- 20 October 1800 ) was a British politician and Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Evesham .
Saul Gorn ( 10 November 1912 -- 22 February 1992 ) was an American pioneer in computer and information science who was a member of the School of Engineering and Applied Science at the University of Pennsylvania for more than 30 years .
Virginia Satir ( 26 June 1916 -- 10 September 1988 ) was an American author and social worker , known especially for her approach to family therapy and her work with family reconstruction .
Peter Craine ( 19 ? ? -- 2003 ) was a politician from the Isle of Man and an MHK for Douglas South .
He Tianjian ( Chinese : 贺天健 ; 1891 -- 2 April 1977 ) , formerly romanized as Ho T'ien - chien , was a Chinese guohua painter and a leading member of the Shanghai School of art .
John Clement Gordon ( 1644 - -1726 ) , originally just John Gordon , bishop of Galloway , was born in Scotland on 1644 , and was a member of the Gordon family of Coldwells , near Ellon in Buchan , Aberdeenshire .
Carl Keller ( 9 July 1893 -- 17 June 1981 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rev. Benjamin Rush Rhees ( 1860 - -1939 ) was the third president of the University of Rochester , serving from 1900 - 1935 .
Josiah Charles Trent ( 7 August 1914 - -10 December 1948 ) was an American surgeon and a historian of medicine .
Francis Hely - Hutchinson ( 26 October 1769 -- 16 December 1827 ) , styled The Honourable from 1783 , was an Irish politician .
Ieuan ap Hywel Swrdwal ( ? 1430 - ? 1480 ) was a Welsh poet , from Norman stock .
Guillaume le Vinier ( c. 1190 - -1245 ) was a cleric and trouvère , one of the most prolific composers in the genre .
Ronald Haworth ( born 10 March 1901 -- October 1973 ) was an English footballer .
Thomas Griffitts ( died 1746 ) was Mayor of Philadelphia on three occasions .
Andriantsimitoviaminiandriana Andriandrazaka ( also Andriantsimitoviaminandriandrazaka ) was King of Avaradrano in the central highlands of Madagascar from 1710 to 1730 , and king of neighboring Ambohidrabiby after defeating his brother , Andrianavalonimerina .
Ali Jalla Abdul Jalil Shah II ( died 1597 ) was the Sultan of Johor from 1571 to 1597 .
Dnyaneshwar or Dnyandev ( IAST : Jñāneśvar ) ( 1275 - -1296 ) was a 13th - century Marathi saint , poet , philosopher and yogi of the Nath tradition whose Dnyaneshvari ( a commentary on the Bhagavad Gita ) and Amrutanubhav are considered to be milestones in Marathi literature
Saint Joseph Zhang Dapeng ( Chinese:張大鵬 , 1754 -- 12 March 1815 ) , was a Chinese martyr .
Brian Burland ( 23 April 1931 -- 11 February 2010 ) was a Bermudian writer , who was the author of nine acclaimed novels that typically dealt with colonialism , family strife and race .
Foolabai ( 1664 - -1682 ) was a saintly Jat woman popularly known as Bhakt Shiromani Foolabai .
William Whittingham Lyman ( July 28 , 1850 in Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania -- 1921 ) was the son of Theodore Benedict Lyman .
Sir Charles Rivers Wilson ( 1831 - 1916 ) was a British civil servant and financier .
Carl Aschan ( 6 May 1906 -- 27 July 2008 ) was a Swedish - born British intelligence officer and spy during World War II . Aschan later helped to track down some of Adolf Hitler 's associates following the defeat of Nazi Germany .
Lucy Faithfull , Baroness Faithfull , OBE ( 26 October 1910 -- 13 March 1996 ) was a British social worker and children 's campaigner .
Robert Burn ( 22 October 1829 -- 30 April 1904 ) was an English classical scholar and archaeologist and Fellow of Trinity College , Cambridge .
Henry DiSpirito ( 1898 - -1995 ) was an Italian - American artist and sculptor .
Seán Cunningham , Irish cooperative activist and Republican , 1918 - -1997 .
Marisa Mell ( 24 February 1939 -- 16 May 1992 ) was an Austrian actress who became a cult figure of 1960s Italian B - movies .
Sir Percival Willoughby ( died 23 August 1643 ) was a prominent land owner , businessman involved during his lifetime variously in mining , iron smelting , glass making and as an investor in the Newfoundland Company .
Richard Assmann ( Anglicized spelling of the German name Richard Aßmann ) ; ( 13 April 1845 -- 28 May 1918 ) was a German meteorologist and physician who was a native of Magdeburg .
Thomas Thornycroft ( 19 May 1815 -- 30 August 1885 ) was an English sculptor and engineer .
Nicolas Fuss ( 29 January 1755 -- 4 January 1826 ) , also known as Nikolai Fuss , was a Swiss mathematician , living most of his life in Russia .
Rev. Richard Jukes ( 1804 - -1867 ) was a popular Primitive Methodist minister and hymn writer .
Coley Wallace ( April 5 , 1927 -- January 30 , 2005 ) was an American actor and heavyweight boxer who outpointed Rocky Marciano in a three - round amateur fight .
Edgar Craven Bredin ( 16 April 1886 -- 5 August 1950 ) was an Irish mechanical and locomotive engineer and later a railway manager .
Lawrence Bruner ( born Catasauqua , Pennsylvania , 2 March 1856 ; died Berkeley , California , 30 January 1937 ) was a United States entomologist .
George Stapleton ( born Dublin , Ireland , in 1777 , died 1841 , in Dublin ) was a prominent Irish stuccodore , son of Michael Stapleton .
Douglas Z. Doty ( October 15 , 1874 -- 20 February 1935 ) was an American screenwriter and editor .
Galindo Aznárez II ( died 922 ) was Count of Aragón ( 893 - -922 ) , the son and successor of Aznar Galíndez II . Galindo was one of a coalition that sponsored the 905 coup d'état in Pamplona in favor of his brother - in - law , Sancho I of Pamplona .
Hernando de Luque ( Unknown -- 1532 ) was a Spanish priest who travelled to the New World in the 16th century .
Hertha Sponer ( 1 September 1895 -- 27 February 1968 ) was a German physicist and chemist who contributed to modern quantum mechanics and molecular physics and was the first woman on the physics faculty of Duke University .
Luciano Vincenzoni ( Italian pronunciation : ( luˈtʃano vintʃenˈtsoni ) ; 7 March 1926 -- 22 September 2013 ) was an Italian screenwriter , known as the `` script doctor '' .
Isaac Snowman ( 1873 -- 11 February 1947 ) was an Anglo - Jewish artist who made Jewish cultural themes his subject .
Lord Charles Cavendish FRS ( 17 March 1704 -- 28 April 1783 ) was a British nobleman , Whig politician and scientist .
Alfred Thomas Story ( 1842 - -1934 ) was an English journalist , poet and author of numerous books .
Sir Alexander Ogilvy , 1st Baronet ( died 1727 ) was a Scottish politician and judge , lord of session under the title Lord Forglen ,
Sir Andrew Rae Duncan , GBE ( 1884 -- 1952 ) was a British businessman who was brought into government during the Second World War , serving twice as both President of the Board of Trade and Minister of Supply .
John Hartley Williams ( 7 February 1942 -- 3 May 2014 ) was a British poet who was born in Cheshire and grew up in London .
Charles Loomis Dana ( 1852 - 1935 ) was an American physician , professor of nervous and mental disease at Cornell Medical College .
William Frederick Koch ( 1885 - -1967 ) was a U. S. medical doctor and pharmaceutical entrepreneur .
Justin the Confessor ( died 269 in Rome ) was a Christian martyr in the Roman Empire .
Brigadier Oliver David Jackson DSO , OBE ( 24 November 1919 -- 7 May 2004 ) was a senior officer in the Australian Army , seeing service during the Second World War and the Vietnam War .
Arthur Pember ( 1835 -- 3 April 1886 ) was a British sportsman , journalist and author , notable for being the first president of The Football Association , from 1863 to 1867 , as a member of N.N. Club or N.N. Kilburn , one of the founder clubs of the FA .
Adam of Melrose ( died 1222 ) was Abbot of Melrose and Bishop of Caithness , famously burned to death by the husbandmen of Caithness .
Samuel Lyde ( 1825 - -1860 ) was an English writer and Church of England missionary who worked in Syria in the 1850s and wrote a pioneering book on the Alawite sect .
Ronald Radd ( born 22 January 1929 -- 23 April 1976 ) was a British television actor .
Petros Orologas ( Greek : Πέτρος Ωρολογάς , 1892 - -1958 ) was a Greek journalist and newspaper publisher .
Robert Landale ( 1833 -- 5 November 1903 ) was an Australian politician , elected as a member of the New South Wales Legislative Assembly .
Princess Maria Margaretha of Saxony(Maria Margaretha Franziska Xaveria ; 13 September 1727 -- 1 February 1734 ) was a Princess of Poland , Lithuania and Saxony of the House of Wettin .
James Stevenson , 1st Baron Stevenson , GCMG , ( 2 April 1873 -- 10 June 1926 ) , known as Sir James Stevenson , Bt , between 1917 and 1924 , was a British businessman and civil servant .
Dr. Franz Polgar ( April 18 , 1900 - June 1979 ) was a renowned psychologist , hypnotist , lecturer and entertainer .
Louis Charles Salvana ( 20 January 1897 -- 8 December 1974 ) was an Australian sportsman who played first - class cricket for Victoria and Australian rules football with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Fra ' Didier de Saint - Jaille ( died 1536 ) was the 46th Grand Master of the Order of Saint John between 1535 and 1536 .
Patrick Roger Cleary ( 1858 - 1948 ) ( known locally as P.R. Cleary ) was the founder and namesake of Cleary University in Howell , Michigan .
John Row ( 1568 - -1646 ) was a Scottish ecclesiastical historian and one of the Scottish Reformers .
Paul Troger ( 30 October 1698 -- 20 July 1762 ) was an Austrian painter , draughtsman and printmaker of the late Baroque period .
Edson Décimo Alves Araújo or simply Piauí ( 2 December 1986 -- 1 November 2014 ) was a Brazilian footballer , who played as left back .
George Henry Law ( 12 September 1761 -- 22 September 1845 ) was the Bishop of Chester ( 1812 ) and then , from 1824 , Bishop of Bath and Wells .
Knut Rød ( 30 June 1900 -- 19 May 1986 ) was a Norwegian police officer responsible for the arrest , detention and transfer of Jewish men , women and children to SS troops at Oslo harbor .
Samuel Lewis Shane ( 14 April 1900 -- 14 October 1993 ) was a modern American painter whose works span a period from the early 1920s to shortly before his death in 1993 .
Miles Coope , born at Gildersome , Yorkshire , on 18 November 1916 and died also at Gildersome on 5 July 1974 , played first - class cricket for three seasons after the second World War for Somerset .
Adam Hyler ( 1735 - -1782 ) , born in Wurttemberg , Germany , was a privateer and whaleboat captain during the American War for Independence .
Finally , Eusebio Lillo died in Santiago on 8 July 1910 .
Tomás Monfil ( died 2009 ) was a Chilean forester , and one of the principal persons behind the reforestation program of CONAF in Aysén del General Carlos Ibáñez del Campo Region in the 1960s .
William Hubert Burr C.E. ( 1851 - -1934 ) was an American civil engineer , born at Watertown , Connecticut .
Joseph Albert Lintner ( 8 February 1822 in Schoharie , New York -- 5 May 1898 in Rome ) was an American entomologist .
Lindley Evans CMG ( 18 November 1895 -- 2 December 1982 ) was a South African - born Australian composer , pianist and teacher .
Zora Petrović ( born in Dobrica , Banat on May 17 , 1894 - - died in Belgrade on May 25 , 1962 ) was a famous Serbian painter .
Ji Chuna ( Chinese : 紀處訥 ; died July 24 , 710 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reign of Emperor Zhongzong and Emperor Zhongzong 's son Emperor Shang .
Asbjørn Kjønstad ( 6 February 1943 -- 14 February 2015 ) was a Norwegian professor of law .
King Xie of Zhou ( died 750 BCE ) claimed sovereignty during the final stages of the Chinese Western Zhou Dynasty ( 1046 - -771 BCE ) .
Atma Jayaram ( 31 August 1915 - 19 March 1990 ) was the Director of the Indian Intelligence Bureau between November 1971 to August 1975 .
Sir John Dauntsey ( died 1391 ) , of Dauntsey , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Edward William Price ( 1832 -- 14 November 1893 ) was an Irish - born Australian civil servant , who served as Government Resident of the Northern Territory between 1876 and 1883 .
Yulia Aroustamova ( 23 November 1982 -- 5 July 2007 ) was a Russian track racing cyclist .
Karma Tenkyong ( 1606 -- Neu , Central Tibet , 1642 ) , in full Karma Tenkyong Wangpo ( Wylie : Kar ma bstan skyong dbang po ) , was a king of Tibet who ruled from 1620 to 1642 .
Johann Dzierzon , or Jan Dzierżon ( ˈjan ˈd͡ʑɛrʐɔn ) or Dzierżoń ( ˈd͡ʑɛrʐɔɲ ) , also John Dzierzon ( 16 January 1811 -- 26 October 1906 ) , was a pioneering apiarist who discovered the phenomenon of parthenogenesis in bees and designed the first successful movable - frame beehive .
Wei Guoqing ( simplified Chinese : 韦国清 ; traditional Chinese : 韋國清 ; pinyin : Wéi Guóqīng ; Zhuang : Veiz Gozcing ) ( 2 September 1913 -- 14 June 1989 ) was a Chinese government official , military officer and political commissar .
Christen Mølbach ( 8 November 1766 -- 7 July 1834 ) was a Norwegian merchant who represented Stavanger amt at the Norwegian Constituent Assembly at Eidsvoll in 1814 .
Farrukh Beg ( ca . 1545 -- ca . 1615 ) was a Persian born Mughal painter who served in the court of Mirza Muhammad Hakim before working directly for Mughal Emperor Akbar .
Ignatius Bonomi ( 1787 - -1870 ) was an English architect and surveyor , with Italian origins by his father , strongly associated with Durham in north - east England .
Isabella Coymans ( 1626 -- 1689 ) , was the Dutch wife of Stephanus Geraerdts best known for her portrait painted by Frans Hals .
John Kewish , Jr. ( died 1 August 1872 ) was the last person executed by the Isle of Man .
William Goldwin ( born c.1682 ; died at Bristol 1747 ) was an English schoolteacher and vicar who left his mark on cricket by creating the sport 's earliest known work of literature .
Arthur Thistlewood ( 1774 - -1 May 1820 ) was a British radical activist and conspirator in the Cato Street Conspiracy .
James B. Simpson ( 1927 - 2002 ) was a journalist , author and Episcopal priest , best known for writing several volumes of Simpson 's Contemporary Quotations , a set of books of quotations .
Royal Cortissoz ( 10 February 1869 -- 17 October 1948 , last name pronounced `` Kor - tee - zus '' ) was an American art historian and long - time art critic for the New York Herald Tribune from 1891 until his death .
Margery Clinton ( 1931 -- 2005 ) was a specialist in reduction lustre glazes .
Ion Petre Stoican ( born 1930 , Olteniţa , Călăraşi - d. 1994 , Constanţa ) was a Romani - Romanian violinist , a lăutar ( performer of traditional music , especially for weddings ) .
Nguyển Cát Ngạc , pen name Nam Xương ( 1905 - 1958 ) was a popular Vietnamese playwright in the 1930s .
Anthony J. DePace ( 1892 - -1977 ) was an American architect who designed numerous Roman Catholic churches throughout the Northeastern United States area during the mid to late 20th century .
Jørgen Lykke ( 1515 at Havnø -- 26 December 1583 ) was a Danish nobleman , diplomat and politician .
Margaret Coke , Countess of Leicester ( 16 June 1700 -- 28 February 1775 ) was a British peer .
Fredrik Thoresen ( 7 May 1926 -- 23 December 2012 ) is a Norwegian businessperson .
Beryl Measor , ( 22 April 1908 -- 8 February 1965 ) was an English actress .
Francisco de Silva , 10th Duke of Huéscar ( in full , Spanish : Don Francisco de Paula de Silva Mendoza y Álvarez de Toledo , décimo duque de Huéscar ) , ( 1733 - -1770 ) , was a Spanish nobleman .
Spokane Garry ( sometimes spelled Spokan Garry ) ( c. 1811 -- 1892 ) was a Native American leader of the Middle Spokane tribe .
George Markstein ( 29 August 1926 -- 15 January 1987 ) was a British journalist and subsequent writer of thrillers and teleplays .
François - Joseph - Philippe de Riquet ( 21 September 1771 - 2 March 1843 ) , comte de Caraman was the 16th Prince de Chimay from 24 July 1804 to 1843 .
Barbara Kolanka or Barbara Kołówna h. Junosza ( end of the 15th century--1550 ) was a Polish noble lady .
Willem van Ruytenburch ( baptized 13 August 1600 - 1657 ) of Amsterdam was a lieutenant to Captain Frans Banning Cocq in the mid-17th century .
Jack Bloomfield ( 20 November 1899 -- 1961 ) was an English light heavyweight professional boxer , whose birth name was Sol Blumenfeld , and who was also known as `` Basking '' Jack Bloomfield during his career .
Roland Ansieau ( 1901 - -1987 ) was an early 20th - century French art deco graphic artist , best known for his 1935 `` Berger 45 '' wine advertisement which is widely reproduced as poster prints .
Germanos Mouakkad ( born April 1853 in Damascus , Syria - died on 11 February 1912 in Beirut ) was a Melkite priest and bishop of the Melkite Greek Catholic Archeparchy of Baalbek .
Nina Genke or Nina Genke - Meller , or Nina Henke - Meller , ( Russian : Нина Генке-Меллер , Нина Генке , 1893 - -1954 ) was a Ukrainian - Russian avant - garde artist , ( Suprematist , Futurist ) , designer , graphic artist and scenographer .
David Jagger , RP , ROI ( 1891 , Kilnhurst , near Rotherham , Yorkshire -- 1958 ) was an English portrait painter .
Miroslav Filipović ( 5 June 1915 -- 1946 ) , also known as Tomislav Filipović and Tomislav Filipović - Majstorović , was a Croatian Nazi collaborator , Franciscan friar and military chaplain , and convicted war criminal .
Dougald Currie ( August 22 , ca . 1844 -- November 5 , 1918 ) was a farmer and political figure on Prince Edward Island , and was educated there .
Akin Ogungbe ( 1934 - -November 2012 ) was a Nigerian film actor , filmmaker , producer and director .
George Stanhope ( 5 March 1660 -- 18 March 1728 ) was a clergyman of the Church of England , rising to be Dean of Canterbury and a Royal Chaplain .
Hon . Charles Leslie Courtenay ( d. 29 October 1894 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1859 - 1894 .
Brigadier General Stanley Price Weir , DSO , VD , JP ( 23 April 1866 -- 14 November 1944 ) was a public servant and Australian Army officer .
Helene Kottanner ( née Wolfram ; Hungarian : Kottaner Ilona ; c. 1400 -- after 1470 ) was a late - medieval woman born in Sopron , Hungary .
Jacques Gerschwiler ( 10 September 1898 -- 4 May 2000 ) was a noted Swiss figure skater and coach .
Samuel Scott Johnston Huey , usually known as Scott Huey ( 21 December 1923 -- 8 March 2012 ) was an Irish cricketer .
Jean - François Buisson de Saint - Cosme ( 1667 - -1706 ) was a Canadian missionary , born in Quebec , ordained in 1690 , and murdered while on a missionary trip .
Thomas John Burdett ( 29 October 1915 -- 2001 ) , known as Tom or Tommy Burdett , was an English footballer who scored 12 goals from 30 appearances in the Football League playing for Hull City and Lincoln City .
William Feilding , 1st Earl of Denbigh ( c. 1587 -- 8 April 1643 , Cannock ) was an English naval officer and courtier .
Regina Fryxell , born Regina Holmén ( November 24 , 1899 -- September 19 , 1993 ) was an American educator and musician .
María Julieta Kirkwood Bañados ( 5 April 1936 -- 8 April 1985 ) was a Chilean sociologist , political scientist , university professor and feminist activist .

Yvette Espinosa ( 1911 - 1992 ) Born in England - daughter of Eve Louise Kelland and Edouard Espinosa , founder of the British Ballet Organization .
Augustin Maior ( 22 August 1882 - 3 October 1963 ) was a Romanian physicist , educator and inventor .
J. William Schickel , FAIA , ( 1850 - -1907 ) known professionally as William Schickel , was a German - American architect and founder of the New York architectural firm of Schickel & Ditmars .
Andrew Duncan , the younger ( 1773 - -1832 ) was a Scottish physician and professor at Edinburgh University .
John Raphael Rodrigues Brandon ( 5 April 1817 in London -- 8 October 1877 at his chambers at 17 Clement 's Inn , Strand , London ) was a British architect and architectural writer .
Karl Chircop ( 7 August 1965 -- 12 October 2008 ) was a doctor and practiced as a family doctor and a Maltese politician .
Les Kaine ( 8 August 1936 -- 18 August 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Charles Lilburn Lewis ( 1747 -- 1831 or 1837 ) , sometimes referred to as Charles Lilburn Lewis of Monteagle , was one of the founders of Milton , Virginia , as well as one of the signers of Albemarle County , Virginia 's Declaration of Independence in 1779 .
Walter Spratt ( 14 April 1889 -- 22 January 1945 ) was an English professional footballer who played as a full - back in The Football League for Manchester United and Brentford .
Ibn - e - Insha ( Punjabi , Urdu : ابن انشاء‎ ) born Sher Muhammad Khan ( Punjabi , Urdu : شیر محمد خان‎ ) on 15 June 1927 died 11 January 1978 , was a Pakistani Leftist Urdu poet , humorist , travelogue writer and columnist .
William John Wolfgram was a United States Army Lieutenant during World War II . He served in the army from 1942 until his death in combat in 1945 .
Dmitri Ivanovich Yermakov ( Russian : Дмитрий Иванович Ермаков ) ( 1846 -- November 10 , 1916 ) was a Russian photographer known for his series of the Caucasian photographs .
Gilly Coman ( 13 September 1955 -- 13 July 2010 ) was an English actress , who played Aveline in the first four series of Carla Lane 's sitcom Bread .
William the Walloon ( date of birth unknown ; d. ( probably ) 22 December 1089 ) was a Benedictine abbot .

Nicolasa Pradera ( 1870 - 1959 ) was a Spanish chef , restaurateur , and is most known for her cookbook `` La cocina de Nicolasa '' ( the Kitchen of Nicolasa ) , which is one of the staples of Basque cooking .

Bājūrī Ibrāhīm ibn - Muhammad ( 1783/1784 - 1860 ) was an Egyptian theologian and lecturer ( 19th century ) at the theologic academy of al - Azhar in Cairo .

Theodoor Wilkens or Theodorus Wilkens ( alias Goedewil ) ( 1690 , Amsterdam -- 1748 , Amsterdam ) , was an 18th - century painter and draughtsman from the Dutch Republic who specialised in landscapes .

Don Haig ( 22 July 1933 -- 2 March 2002 ) was a Canadian filmmaker , editor , and producer .
Lehmann Bernheimer ( 27 December 1841 - 29 May 1918 ) was a German antique dealer , who built the Bernheimer - Haus in Munich .
Julius Pomponius Laetus ( 1428 -- June 9 , 1498 ) , also known as Giulio Pomponio Leto , was an Italian humanist .

Hussein Kamal ( Arabic : حسين كمال‎ ) ( 17 August 1932 -- 24 March 2003 ) was an Egyptian television , film and theatre director .
John Belasyse , 1st Baron Belasyse ( or Bellasis ) PC ( 24 June 1614 -- 10 September 1689 ) was an English nobleman , soldier and Member of Parliament , notable for his role during and after the English Civil War .

Thomas Rudd ( 1583?--1656 ) was an English military engineer and mathematician .
Charlotte of Albret , suo jure Dame de Châlus , Duchess of Valentinois ( 1480 -- 11 March 1514 ) , also known as Charlotte d'Albret , was a wealthy French noblewoman of the Albret family .
Carl Gustav Alexander Brischke ( December 17 , 1814 -- 1897 ) was a German entomologist who worked on Diptera and Hymenoptera , mainly the Ichneumonidae and Braconidae .
Diana , Lady Mosley ( 17 June 1910 -- 11 August 2003 ) , born Diana Freeman - Mitford and usually known as Diana Mitford , was one of Britain 's noted Mitford sisters .
Rhoda Erdmann ( 5 December 1870 -- 23 August 1935 ) was a German cell biologist .
Sir Harry Evan Auguste Cotton CIE ( better known as H. E. A. Cotton , or Evan Cotton ) ( 24 May 1868 -- 7 March 1939 ) was a Liberal politician , barrister , administrator , journalist , historian and writer .

Beatrice Bolam , MBE ( born 1919 -- died 2 January 2013 ) was an English politician and councillor for Jarrow , South Tyneside .
Richard Newcome ( Newcombe ) ( 1701 - 1769 ) was an English bishop of Llandaff and bishop of St Asaph .
Nicolai Andresen ( 24 September 1781 -- 18 November 1861 ) was a Norwegian merchant , banker and member of Stortinget .
Thomas Longman ( 1699 -- 18 June 1755 ) was an English publisher who founded the publishing house of Longman .
Francesco Solari ( c. 1415 -- 1469 ) was an Italian sculptor , architect and engineer .
William Patton ( 23 August 1798 in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania - 9 September 1879 in New Haven , Connecticut ) , was a New York City pastor , abolitionist , and the son of patriot Robert Patton .
Tuanku Imam Bonjol ( 1772 -- 6 November 1864 ) , also known as Muhammad Syahab , Peto Syarif , and Malim Basa , was one of the most popular leaders of the Padri movement in Central Sumatra .
Robert Ker , 2nd Duke of Roxburghe ( c. 1709 -- 20 August 1755 ) was a Scottish peer .

Edward Bligh ( 19 September 1769 -- 2 November 1840 ) , styled The Honourable from birth , was an Irish politician , a noted amateur cricketer and a prominent early member of Marylebone Cricket Club .
Colonel Thomas Walter Harding ( 1843 - -1927 ) was an industrialist and civic figure in Leeds , West Yorkshire , England .
Estvan Svend Aage Wehlast ( 15 April 1916 -- 9 February 1945 ) was a member of the Danish resistance killed by Gestapo while resisting arrest .
Saneeya Hussain ( 13 August 1954 -- 20 April 2005 ) was a Pakistani journalist and environmentalist .
Eliza Jane Scovill ( December 3 , 2001 -- May 16 , 2005 ) was the daughter of AIDS denialist Christine Maggiore , an HIV - positive activist who publicly questioned the link between HIV and AIDS , and supported HIV - positive pregnant women who want to avoid taking anti - HIV medication .
Thomas Coglan Horsfall ( 1841 - 1932 ) was a noted philanthropist , town planner , writer and founder of the Manchester Art Museum in Ancoats Hall .
Octavius Winslow ( 1 August 1808 -- 5 March 1878 ) , also known as `` The Pilgrim 's Companion '' , stood out as one of the foremost evangelical preachers of the 19th Century in England and America .
