Francis Kenna ( 21 September 1865 -- 23 June 1932 ) , was an Australian poet , journalist , and Labor Member of the Legislative Assembly in Queensland .
Derek Pugh ( 8 February 1926 -- 2 May 2008 ) was a British track and field athlete who competed in sprinting events .
Orlando Nappe ( Buenos Aires , c. 1931 - -2007 ) was an Argentine footballer .
Francisco de Meneses Brito ( died 1672 ) was Royal Governor of Chile between 1664 and 1667 .
Ronald Clyne ( December 28 , 1925 -- 2006 ) was an American freelance designer and graphic artist best known for creating over 500 covers for Folkways Records during the more than three - decade lifetime of his independent company from 1948 - -1986 .
Maria Verelst ( 1680 - -1744 ) was an 18th - century English painter .
Gregory Akindynos ( Latinized as Gregorius Acindynus ) ( Greek : Γρηγόριος Ἀκίνδυνος ) ( ca . 1300 -- 1348 ) was a Byzantine Greek theologian .
Heinz Kohnen ( 5 February 1938 -- 25 July 1997 ) was a German scientist and geophysicist known for his work in polar research .
Johannes Megapolensis ( 1603 - -1670 ) was a dominie ( pastor ) of the Dutch Reformed Church in the Dutch colony of New Netherland ( present - day New York state in the United States ) , beginning in 1642 .
Maurus von Schenkl ( b. at Auerbach in Bavaria , 4 January 1749 ; d. at Amberg , 14 June 1816 ) was a German Benedictine theologian and canonist .
Sir John Davie , 2nd Baronet ( 1612 - 1678 ) of Creedy in the parish of Sandford , Devon , was Member of Parliament for Tavistock , Devon , in 1661 and was Sheriff of Devon from 1670 to 1671 .
Rear Admiral Frederick Warden CB ( 18 November 1807 -- 11 November 1869 ) was a Royal Navy officer who went on to be Commander - in - Chief , Channel Squadron .
Wonseong of Silla ( r. 785 - 798 , died 798 ) was the 38th to rule the Korean kingdom of Silla .
Khalil Tahmasebi ( died 1955 ) was a carpenter and member of the fanatical Islamic organization , Fadayan - e Islam who assassinated Iranian Prime Minister Ali Razmara on 7 March 1951 .
Ado Birk ( also known as Aadu Birk , Aado Birk or Avdei Birk ; 14 November ( O.S. 2 November ) 1883 -- 2 February 1942 ) , was an Estonian politician who was the Estonian Prime Minister for three days , from 28 July 1920 to 30 July 1920 .
Niki Marangou ( 1948 - 7 February 2013 ) was an award winning Cypriot author and artist .
Zihni Gjinali ( 5 May 1926 - 19 July 2005 ) was a famous Albanian footballer who played his professional career for Besa , Dinamo Tirana and Partizani Tirana football clubs .
Armas Leinonen ( 28 December 1900 , Oulu -- 29 May 1985 ) was a Finnish schoolteacher and politician .
Christian Magnus Falsen ( 14 September 1782 -- 13 January 1830 ) was a Norwegian constitutional father , statesman , jurist , and historian .
Thomas Christie , Jr. ( 1855 - 2 February 1934 ) was a pharmacist and federal politician in Quebec .
Gaetano Cecere , ( November 26 , 1894 -- 1985 ) American sculptor , born , educated and worked in New York City .
Nasir Subhani ( Kurdish : ناسر سوبحانی , Persian : ناصر سبحانی‎ ) ( 14 October 1951 - 17 April 1990 or 19 March 1990 ) was a Kurdish scholar from Iranian Kurdistan .
Anthony O'Grady Lefroy CMG ( 14 March 1816 -- 21 January 1897 ) , often known as O'Grady Lefroy , was an important government official in Western Australia before the advent of responsible government .
Glória de Sant'Anna ( 26 May 1925 -- 2 June 2009 ) was a Portuguese - born poet and educator who lived in Portuguese Mozambique from 1951 to 1974 .
Paul Fung ( 1897 - -1944 ) was an American cartoonist best known for the comic strip Dumb Dora .
John Laskey Woolcock ( 7 November 1861 -- 18 January 1929 ) was a barrister and Supreme Court judge in Queensland , Australia .
Børge Mogensen ( 13 April 1914 -- 5 October 1972 ) , was a Danish furniture designer .
Caroline Bauer ( 29 March 1807 -- 18 October 1877 ) was a German actress of the Biedermeier era who used the name Lina Bauer .
Pros Mund ( died 1644 ) was a Danish admiral .
Santi Buglioni , byname of Santi di Michele ( 1494 - 27 November 1576 ) was an Italian sculptor , the nephew and collaborator of Benedetto Buglioni .
Brigadier Neil Mackenzie Freeman DSO ( 21 April 1890 -- 1961 ) was a senior officer of the Australian Army .
Johann Gottlieb Graun ( 27 October 1703 -- 28 October 1771 ) was a German Baroque / Classical era composer and violinist , born in Wahrenbrück .
John Collingwood Bruce died on 5 April 1892 ; his wife Charlotte died in 1893 , and their daughter Frances died aged 18 months on 17 December 1839 , They are buried in the family grave in Jesmond Old Cemetery .
Dr. Virginia Kneeland Frantz ( 1896 - 1967 ) was a pathologist and educator credited with a series of discoveries in the study of thyroid , breast and pancreatic tumors .
Admire Rakti ( 20 February 2008 -- 4 November 2014 ) was a Japanese Thoroughbred racehorse who won the Diamond Stakes in Japan and the Caulfield Cup in Australia .
George J. Walker ( 16 January 1934 -- 11 April 2005 ) served as an officer in the U.S. Army , including a stint in 1985 as Deputy Commanding General of the United States Army Intelligence and Security Command(INSCOM ) .
Alfred Lindon ( born Abner Lindenbaum ; c. 1867 -- 1948 ) was a Polish jeweller from a poor Jewish background who became an expert on pearls .
Werner Kutzsche ( born 14 May 1911 in Niederlößnitz near Radebeul , died 1 February 2000 in Dresden ) was a German engineer , who was known for his work in the fields of radio - frequency engineering and electroacoustics .
Yang Xuangan ( 楊玄感 Yáng Xuángǎn ) ( died 613 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Sui Dynasty .
Thomas Dix Hincks ( 1767 in Dublin , Ireland -- 1857 in Belfast , Ireland ) was an Irish orientalist and naturalist .
Juan de Albi was a Spanish Carthusian of the Convent Val - Christ , near Segovia , date of birth uncertain ; died 27 December 1591 .
Yossef Harmelin ( 1922 -- December 12 , 1994 ) was an Israeli civil servant , serving as the director of the Shabak from 1964 to 1974 and again from 1986 - 1988 and as ambassador in Iran and South Africa .
Prof Haroon Khan Sherwani ( 1891 - -1980 ) was a renowned Indian historian , scholar , and author .
Ivan Jandl ( 24 January 1937 -- 21 November 1987 ) was a Czech child actor .
Amara Sinha ( or Amara Simha ) ( c. CE 375 ) was a Sanskrit grammarian and poet , of whose personal history hardly anything is known .
Archibald Wickstead ( 6 November 1884 -- 1 February 1966 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Derbyshire in 1911 and 1912 .
Charles Pearson ( 4 October 1793 -- 14 September 1862 ) was Solicitor to the City of London , a reforming campaigner , and -- briefly --
Bashir Ahmed Qureshi ( Sindhi : بشير احمد قريشي‎ ) , ( 10 August , 1959 -- 7 April 2012 ) ; was a Sindhi nationalist who served as the leader of Jeay Sindh Qaumi Mahaz ( JSQM ) , a Sindhi nationalist movement in Sindh , founded by G. M. Syed .
Clement Meadmore ( 9 February 1929 -- 19 April 2005 ) was an Australian - American sculptor known for massive outdoor steel sculptures .
Yosef Kushnir ( Hebrew : יוסף קושניר‎ , born 15 November 1900 , died 6 January 1983 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Mapam from 1960 until 1961 , and again from 1962 until 1965 .
Santaji Mhaloji Ghorpade,(1660 - 1696 ) popularly known as `` Santaji '' or `` Santaji Ghorpade '' , was one of the greatest warriors and the chief General of the Maratha Empire during Chhatrapati Rajaram 's regime .
Sol Schoenbach ( 1915 - -1999 ) was an American bassoonist and teacher .
Bevil Higgons ( 1670 - -1735 ) was an English historian and poet , He was born at Kezo .
Horst Schüler - Springorum ( 15 October 1928 - 5 September 2015 ) was a German Professor of Jurisprudence .
Wilibald Swibert Joseph Gottlieb von Besser ( 7 July 1784 -- 11 October 1842 ) was an Austrian - born botanist who worked most of his life within the territory of western Ukraine .
Vytautas Petrulis ( born February 3 , 1890 in Katelišės , near Vabalninkas ; executed in 1942 , near Uchta , RSFSR ) was a Lithuanian politician , one of the main figures in the Lithuanian Christian Democratic Party , and an accountant .
Jimmy Wheeler ( 16 September 1910 - 8 October 1973 ) was a British variety theatre comedian and pioneer of radio and television .
( Charles ) Philip Fothergill ( 23 February 1906 -- 31 January 1959 ) was an English woollen manufacturer and Liberal Party politician .
Nicholas Dias Abeysinghe Amarasekere Maha Mudaliyar , ( Sinhala : නිකලස් ඩයස් අබේසිංහ අමරසේකර ) ( 8 May 1719 - 10 May 1794 ) was a Ceylonese Dutch colonial administrator .
Muriel Denison , née Jessie Muriel Goggin ( 1886 - -1954 ) , was a Canadian writer .
Sir Patrick Hancock GCMG ( 25 June 1914 -- 1 February 1980 ) was a British diplomat who was ambassador to Israel , Norway and Italy .
Singanallur Venkataramana Iyer Sahasranamam ( b. 29 November 1913 -- 19 February 1988 ) , commonly known as S. V. Sahasranamam , was an Indian theatre and film actor and also a director , who worked mainly in Tamil cinema .
Simicoudza Simicourba ( 1858 -- 1911 ) , otherwise known as Sitarane , was a thief and murderer on the island of Réunion .
Jim Buck ( 28 November 1931 -- 4 July 2013 ) was a New York City dog walker .
Asbjørn Nesheim ( 14 December 1906 in Trondheim --19 January 1989 in Oslo ) was a Norwegian linguist and curator known for his research on the Sámi languages and cultural history , particularly for his collaboration with Konrad Nielsen on volumes four and five of Nielsen 's Lapp Dictionary .
Alonzo Potter ( 6 July 1800 -- 4 July 1865 ) was an American bishop of the Episcopal Church in the United States who served as the third Bishop of Pennsylvania .
Dirk III van Brederode ( ca . 1308 -- Haarlem , 11 November 1377 ) was lord of Brederode .
Count Wilhelm IV of Eberstein ( 3 May 1497 -- 1 July 1562 ) was a member of the Swabian noble Eberstein family .
Petar Manola ( Serbian Cyrillic : Петар Манола ) ( born 28 February 1918 -- 2004 ) was a Bosnian Serb football player .
Mahvash ( née Akram , Persian : مهوش ) , ( 1920 - 1961 ) , also known as Banu Mahvash ( English : Lady Mahvash ) , Ma'sumeh Azizi Borujerdi , and Akram Ābgūshtī , was a singer , dancer , film actress and stage performer .
Christoph Frankopan ( Croatian : Krsto Frankopan Brinjski ; 1482 - -1527 ) was a Croatian count from the noble House of Frankopan .
Eglantine Wallace , Lady Wallace ( died 1803 ) , was an English author .
Paul Lüönd ( 15 April 1950 -- 3 April 2014 ) was a Swiss musician and politician .
Thomas Fairfax , 1st Viscount Fairfax of Emley ( 1575 - 23 December 1636 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1601 and 1626 .
Emilie Frances Bauer ( pseudonym : Francisco di Nogero ; March 5 , 1865 Walla Walla , Washington -- March 9 , 1926 Manhattan , New York ) was an American music critic and pianist .
Henry East Havergal ( 1820 - -1875 ) was a priest in the Church of England and an organist .
Henry Augustus Marshall ( died 1841 ) was a British official in Ceylon .
Harry Hopkinson ( 8 June 1902 -- 4 March 1979 ) has been credited as one of the world 's greatest yodelers .
Sutton Vane ( 9 November 1888 -- 15 June 1963 ) was a British playwright best known work for Outward Bound ( 1923 ) , which was filmed twice and was still being performed eight decades after its premiere .
Vice - Admiral Cecil Vivian Usborne , CB , CMG ( 17 May 1880 -- 31 January 1951 ) was a high - ranking officer in the British Royal Navy .
Frank Seeds ( March 26 , 1896 -- October 1963 ) was a professional football player who played in the National Football League during the 1926 season with the Canton Bulldogs .
Jeff Fehring ( 21 April 1955 -- 25 July 2008 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( as the AFL was then known ) from 1977 to 1981 .
Thomas Reynell ( 13 September 1625 -- 1698 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1654 and 1689 .
Holden Furber ( 13 March 1903 -- 19 January 1993 ) was a professor of South Asia Studies at the University of Pennsylvania from 1952 till 1973 .
Sir Frederick Taylor , 1st Baronet MD FRCS ( 6 April 1847 - 2 December 1920 ) was a British physician and president of the Royal College of Physicians 1915 - 1918 .
Maximilian Gustav Alfred Cecil Michaelis ( born Cabourg , France 19 August 1913-died Aix - en - Provence 3 May 1997 ) , was an artist who also practised in glass and ceramics , and a philanthropist who encouraged crafts and design .
Iannis Xenakis ( Greek : Γιάννης ( Ιάννης ) Ξενάκης ( ˈʝanis kseˈnacis ) ; 29 May 1922 -- 4 February 2001 ) was a Greek - French composer , music theorist , and architect - engineer .
Rolf Bossi ( 10 September 1923 -- 22 December 2015 ) was a German criminal defense lawyer .
Patrick Kinane ( 3 July 1892 -- 15 July 1957 ) was an Irish Clann na Poblachta politician .
Jean I of Albret ( 1425 -- 3 January 1468 ) , 15th Lord of Albret , was a Viscount of Tartas .
Mavis Taylor ( 1915 -- 14 March 2007 ) was an Australian who was named an Australian Living Treasure for her humanitarian work for the people of East Timor in her later years .
Kurt Walter Bachstitz ( 4 October 1882 - 1949 in The Hague ) was a German - Austrian art dealer .
James Abernethy FRSE ( 12 June 1814 -- 8 March 1896 ) was a Scottish civil engineer .
Reginald Clifford Allen , 1st Baron Allen of Hurtwood ( 9 May 1889 -- 3 March 1939 ) , known as Clifford Allen , was a British politician , leading member of the Independent Labour Party ( ILP ) , and prominent pacifist .
Maurizio Arcieri ( 30 April 1942 -- 29 January 2015 ) formerly leader of The New Dada , a 1960s Italian beat music band , and a member of Krisma , was a successful singer in the 1970s .
Lajos Keresztes - Fischer ( 8 January 1884 -- 29 April 1948 ) was a Hungarian military officer , who served as Chief of the General Staff in 1938 .
Frank E. Kirby ( July 1 , 1849 -- August 25 , 1929 ) was a naval architect in the Detroit , Michigan ( USA ) area in the early 20th century .
Adrianus Johannes Ehnle ( 1819 - 1863 ) , a Dutch painter of historical and genre subjects , was born at the Hague in 1819 , and studied under C. Kruseman .
Neil Myles ( 17 June 1925 -- 1993 ) was a Scottish professional footballer .
Adolfo Costa du Rels ( or Adolfo Costa du Reís ) ( 1891 - - 26 May 1980 ) was a Bolivian writer and diplomat who became the last President of the Council of the League of Nations .
John Stewart , 1st Earl of Traquair ( died 1659 ) was a Scottish statesman , the son of John Stewart , the younger , of Traquair in Peeblesshire , of a branch , originally illegitimate , of the house of Buchan , and was created Baron Stewart of Traquair in 1628 and earl of Traquair in 1633 .
Eliyahu Eliashar ( Hebrew : אליהו אלישר‎ , 10 October 1899 - 30 October 1981 ) was an Israeli politician and writer .
Eyo Edet Okon ( 10 June 1914 - -28 , September 2010 ) fondly called Akamba Ete ( Great Papa ) is a Nigerian Christian pastor and minister .
Stefan Pogonowski ( 1895 - -1920 ) was a Polish professional soldier and military officer .
Mons Lie ( 15 February 1757 -- 2 August 1827 ) was a Norwegian police chief and writer .
Thomas Vautrollier ( died 1587 ) was a French Huguenot refugee who became a printer in England and , briefly , in Scotland .
Georg Gottlob Ungewitter ( 15 September 1820 -- 6 November 1864 ) was a German architect and master builder .
Lúcio Alberto Pinheiro dos Santos ( Braga , 19 April 1889 - Rio de Janeiro , 11 November 1950 ) was a Portuguese philosopher and teacher , noted for coining the term and writing the first theory of rhythmanalysis , focused on its physiological dimensions .
Sir Alexander Walden ( died 1401 ) , of Matching and Rickling , Essex .
Eli Marsden Wilson , A.R.E. , A.R.C.E. ( 24 June 1877 - 13 November 1965 ) was an English artist who had seventeen pictures exhibited at the Royal Academy .
Heinrich Laehr ( 10 March 1820 -- 18 August 1905 ) was a German psychiatrist born in Sagan , Silesia .
Rufus Phineas Stebbins ( 8 March 1810 in South Wilbraham , Massachusetts -- 13 August 1885 in Cambridge , Massachusetts ) was a Massachusetts and Pennsylvania clergyman .
Peter Hately Waddell ( 19 May 1817 -- 5 May 1891 ) was a Scottish cleric and prolific writer .
Francisco de Murga y Ortiz de Orué ( 1570 ? - 1636 ) was Spanish soldier and engineer who became Governor and Captain - General of Cartagena .
Wen Xingyu ( Chinese : 文兴宇 ; 1941 - -2007 ) was a popular comedian and director in mainland China .
Sima Wei ( 司馬瑋 ) ( 271 - -291 ) , courtesy name Yandu ( 彥度 ) , formally Prince Yin of Chu ( 楚隱王 ) , was an imperial prince during Jin Dynasty ( 265 - 420 ) and was the second of the eight princes commonly associated with the War of the Eight Princes .
Charles Henry Tilson Marshall ( 1841 -- 20 January 1927 ) was a British Army Officer , serving in the Punjab , India .
Pedro Álvarez Holguín ( 1490 - 1542 ) was a Spanish nobleman , military and Conquistador of Perú .
Ray F. Smith ( 1919 -- 23 August 1999 ) was an American agronomist whose research focused on biological methods of arthropod pest management .
Rev. Dr. James Kalacherry ( 20 April 1892 -- 27 October 1949 ) was an Indian educationalist and bishop of the Syro - Malabar Catholic Church , taking charge of the Diocese of Changanassery .
John Bullingham ( died 1598 ) was the Bishop of Gloucester in the Church of England from 1581 .
Jacques Vieau ( or Vieaux ) ( May 5 , 1757 -- July 1 , 1852 ) was a French - Canadian fur trader and first permanent white settler in Milwaukee , Wisconsin .
Andrea Adams ( died 7 November 1995 ) was a BBC broadcaster and journalist known for insightful programs that she wrote and produced for Radio 4 's Does He Take Sugar and Woman 's Hour .
Bartholomaeus Schwartz ( latinised to Bartholomaeus Nigrinus ) ( 1595 - -1646 ) was pastor of the St. Peter and St. Paul 's Church in Danzig ( Gdańsk ) , Royal Prussia ( now Poland ) .
Rambhatla Lakshminarayana Sastry M.A. ( b : 9 December 1908 - d : 19 November 1995 ) was an eminent Telugu and Sanskrit Pundit and Puranic commentator .
Ludovico Coccapani ( 23 June 1849 -- 14 November 1931 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic from the Archdiocese of Pisa and served as a teacher and as a member of the Secular Franciscan Order .
John T. Prout ( 1880 - -1969 ) was an American and Irish soldier .
Frank Markham Skipworth ( 1854 Castor , Lincolnshire -- 1929 London ) was an English portrait painter .
Elston Grey - Turner CBE MC TD ( 16 August 1916 - 20 January 1984 ) was a British doctor , secretary of the British Medical Association from 1976 - 79 .
Zhiyan ( 智儼 ) ( 602 - -668 ) was the second patriarch of the Chinese Buddhist Huayan school .
Robert Brandon ( died 30 May 1591 ) was an English goldsmith and jeweller to Queen Elizabeth I of England .
Manuel Izquierdo ( September 26 , 1925 -- July 17 , 2009 ) was a sculptor and woodcut artist .
Khenpo Shenga Rinpoche , also Shenpen Chökyi Nangwa ( 1871 - -1927 ) was a Tibetan scholar in the Nyingma and Sakya traditions of Tibetan Buddhism .
The two armies fought the Battle of Adramyttium on Saturday , 19 March 1205 outside the city walls , and the result was a massive defeat for Constantine Laskaris and the Greeks , with most of the army either perishing or being captured .
Mahabir Prasad Asthana ( 1903 in Lucknow , Uttar Pradesh , India -- 1976 ) was a freedom fighter and Congress Party leader .
Johannes Legrant ( fl . c. 1420 -- 1440 ) was a French or Burgundian composer of the early Renaissance .
Felice Anerio ( c. 1560 -- 26 or 27 September 1614 ) was an Italian composer of the late Renaissance and early Baroque eras , and a member of the Roman School of composers .
Basil Kennett ( 1674 - -1715 ) was a Church of England cleric who served as the first chaplain to the British Factory at Leghorn .
Richard Hartmann ( 8 November 1809 -- 16 December 1878 ) was a German engineering manufacturer .
Shyam Kumari Khan ( née Nehru , 20 October 1904 - 9 June 1980 ) was an Indian lawyer , freedom fighter , politician and social worker .
Anthony Coucheron ( also recorded as Anton Coucheron or Anthony Willemsen ; c.1650 -- 14 March 1689 ) was an engineering officer .
Jean Hepburn , Lady Darnley , Mistress of Caithness , Lady Morham ( died 1599 ) was a Scottish noblewoman and a member of the Border clan of Hepburn .
Sir David Aubrey Scott GCMG ( 3 August 1919 -- 27 December 2010 ) was a British diplomat who served as High Commissioner to New Zealand and Ambassador to South Africa .
Clara de Chatelain , née Clara Du Mazet de Pontigny ( 31 July 1807 , London -- 30 June 1876 , London ) was an English writer , composer and translator .
Sankari Prasad Basu ( 21 October 1928 -- 6 July 2014 , also credited as Sankariprasad Basu ) is an Indian scholar , writer and critic who writes mainly in the Bengali language .
Pedro Fernández Checa , usually known as Pedro Checa ( 1910 -- 6 August 1942 ) was a Spanish Communist who played a leading role in the party during the Spanish Civil War ( 1936 - -39 ) .
Thomas Hoccleve or Occleve ( c. 1368 - -1426 ) was an English poet and clerk .
Ferenc Sipos ( 13 December 1932 -- 17 March 1997 ) was a Hungarian footballer and trainer .
Guarin ( French : Guérin , Italian : Guarino , Norman : Warin ) ( died 21 January 1137 ) was the chaplain ( magister capellanus ) and chancellor of Roger II of Sicily from about 1130 to his death , during the first decade of the Norman kingdom of Sicily .
Rev. Joseph Cooke ( 1775 - -1811 ) , a Free Christian , was expelled by the Wesleyan Methodists on doctrinal grounds and became the inspiration behind the Methodist Unitarian movement formed under the leadership of another former Wesleyan Joseph Ashworth .
Meiler Bourke , 11th Mac William Iochtar and lord of Lower ( North ) Connacht , died 1520 .
Reverend David Railton MC MA , ( 13 November 1884 -- 13 June 1955 ) was a Church of England clergyman , a Military chaplain and the originator of the idea of the Grave of The Unknown Warrior .
Robert Habersham Coleman ( 1856 - -1930 ) was an iron processing and railroad industrialist and owner of extensive farmland in Pennsylvania .
Carl Ernst Naumann ( 15 August 1832 -- 15 December 1910 ) was a German organist , composer , conductor , editor , arranger and musicologist .
Peter Kastner ( 1 October 1943 -- 18 September 2008 ) was a Canadian - born actor who achieved prominence as a disaffected youth in movies of the 1960s .
Sir Mark Wood , 1st Baronet ( 16 March 1750 -- 6 February 1829 ) was an army officer and engineer .
Dangereuse de l'Isle Bouchard ( Poitevin : Dangerosa ; 1079 - 1151 ) was the daughter of Bartholomew de l'Isle Bouchard .
Peter Bisaillon ( also Bezellon or Bizaillon ) , ( baptized Pierre ) ( c. 1662 -- 18 July 1742 ) was born in France and came to New France with four of his brothers ; all of whom occupied themselves with the trade with various native tribes .
Maurice Fishberg ( 1872 - -1934 ) was a Jewish - American physical anthropologist who specialised in ethnology of the Jews .
Lizbeth Stewart ( 1948 - -2013 ) , who is also known as Lizbeth McNett Stewart , was an American ceramist who was born in Philadelphia and grew up in Southampton , Pennsylvania .
Ernst Mahler ( October 17 , 1887 -- July 30 , 1967 ) was an Austrian chemist and leader of the Kimberly - Clark Corporation in Wisconsin .
S. Omar Barker ( 1894 - -1985 ) , an oft - recited cowboy poet was born in a log cabin in New Mexico where he lived his entire life as a rancher , teacher and writer .
James Creed Meredith K.C. , LL.D. ( 28 November 1875 -- 14 August 1942 ) was an Irish nationalist of the early 20th century , who upheld Brehon Law .
George Landseer , was an English painter born 1829 and died in London 1878 ; he was the nephew of Sir Edwin Henry Landseer and his father Thomas Landseer was also an artist .
Boston King ( c. 1760 - -1802 ) was a former American slave and Black Loyalist , who gained freedom from the British and settled in Nova Scotia after the American Revolutionary War .
Robert Preston , 1st Viscount Gormanston ( 1435 - -1503 ) was an Irish peer and statesman who held the offices of Deputy to the Lord Chancellor of Ireland and Lord Deputy of Ireland .
Sir Richard Tichborne , 2nd Baronet ( 1578 -- April 1652 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1597 .
John Jeremy Lloyd , OBE ( 22 July 1930 -- 23 December 2014 ) was an English writer , screenwriter , author , poet and actor , best known as co - author and writer of several successful British sitcoms , including Are You Being Served ? and ' Allo ' Allo!.
Chaim Widawski ( c. 1906 - -June 1944 ) was a popular Zionist activist in the Łódź Ghetto during World War II . After the German takeover of Poland , the Nazis confiscated personal radios from Jews and Poles , and their possession was made punishable by death .
Otto Ender ( 24 December 1875 - 25 June 1960 ) was an Austrian political figure .
Paolo Cavara ( 4 July 1926 -- 7 August 1982 ) was an Italian screenwriter and a film director .
Dorothea Ruth Etchells ( 17 April 1931 -- 8 August 2012 ) was an English poet and college principal who spent most of her working life in the University of Durham .
John Towill Rutt ( 1760 - -1841 ) was an English political activist , social reformer and nonconformist man of letters .
Sasi Perumal ( Tamil : சசி பெருமாள் ) ( c. 1955 -- 31 July 2015 ) was a Gandhian activist and anti - liquor activist from Salem , Tamil Nadu .
Willie Toner ( 18 December 1929 -- 29 March 1999 ) was a Scottish football player and manager , who played for Celtic , Sheffield United , Kilmarnock , Hibernian and Ayr United .
Elizabeth Inglis ( 10 July 1913 -- 25 August 2007 ) was an English actress , known for her role in The Letter , opposite Bette Davis .
George Luke ( 17 December 1933 -- 24 March 2010 ) was an English footballer who played as a left - winger for Newcastle United , Hartlepools United and Darlington in the 1950s and early 1960s .
Kazbek Gekkiyev ( c.1984 -- 5 December 2012 ) was a Russian television journalist who was killed on 5 December 2012 in the North Caucasus Republic of Kabardino - Balkaria .
Thomas Haydock ( 1772 - -1859 ) , born of one of the oldest English Catholic Recusant families , was a schoolmaster and publisher .
Harry Norman Brookman ( 22 January 1884 -- 26 April 1949 ) , always referred to as Norman Brookman , was a farmer and politician in South Australia .
Thapliyal Gyaneshwar Prasad ( 19 October 1938 -- 25 November 2007 ) was an Indian first - class cricketer who played for Delhi cricket team and Southern Punjab .
Reginald Logan Rait ( January 1902 -- 1975 ) , was a British Pattenmaker and Liberal Party politician .
Roy Furr ( 1907 -- June 13 , 1975 ) was the president of the Furr 's chain of supermarkets and restaurants .
Iustinianus ( died 407 AD ) was a Roman military commander who supported the usurper Constantine III .
Carl Fredrik Wisløff ( 31 December 1908 -- 25 June 2004 ) was a Norwegian theologian and Christian preacher , who spent much of his professional career at the MF Norwegian School of Theology .
Robert Murcutt ( 1791 - -1835 ) was an English first - class cricketer associated with Cambridge Town Club who was active in the 1820s .
Raimondo Scoppa ( March 22 , 1820 -- 1890 ) was an Italian painter of both historical subjects and landscapes .
Philip H. Bruck ( January 6 , 1845 -- January 6 , 1920 ) was the 29th mayor of Columbus , Ohio and the 26th person to serve in that office .
William Bingley ( January 1774 -- 11 March 1823 ) was an English cleric , naturalist and writer .
Emma Vyssotsky ( October 23 , 1894 -- May , 1975 ) , born Emma T. R. Williams in Media , Pennsylvania was an American astronomer .
Sir William Henry Watson QC ( 1 July 1796 -- 13 March 1860 ) , was a British politician and judge .
Josephine Thrane ( née Buch ; 5 April 1820 -- 30 September 1862 ) was a Norwegian teacher and political activist .
Venerable Teresa Chikaba ( c. 1676 -- December 6 , 1748 ) was an Guinean princess declared as Venerable by the Catholic Church .
Paul Rosbaud ( 18 November 1896 - -28 January 1963 ) , was a metallurgist and scientific adviser for Springer Verlag in Germany before and during World War II . He continued in science publishing after the war with Pergamon Press in Oxford , England .
Herluf Trolle ( 14 January 1516 -- 25 June 1565 ) was a Danish naval hero , Admiral of the Fleet and co - founder of Herlufsholm
John Howson ( c. 1557 -- 6 February 1632 ) was an English academic and bishop .
Alex Konadu ( 1950 -- 18 January 2011 ) was a Ghanaian guitarist who was known for his contribution to the Highlife tradition .
Paul Raphael Montford ( 1 November 1868 -- 15 January 1938 ) was an English - born sculptor , active in Australia ; winner of the gold medal of the Royal Society of British Sculptors in 1934 .
Wilfred Harvey Schoff ( 1874 - -1932 ) was an early twentieth century American antiquarian and classical scholar .
María Santos Corrales ( November 1 , 1797 -- 1881 ) was the inspiration of Peru 's famous poet and patriot soldier , Mariano Melgar ; she is forever immortalized as `` Silvia '' in his poetry .
Richard Dunthorne ( 1711 -- 3 March 1775 ) was an English astronomer and surveyor , who worked in Cambridge as astronomical and scientific assistant to Roger Long ( master of Pembroke Hall and Lowndean Professor of Astronomy and Geometry ) , and also concurrently for many years as surveyor to the Bedford Level Corporation .
Leland Lawrence Briggs ( April 24 , 1893 -- November 12 , 1975 ) was an American accounting scholar , and Professor at the University of Vermont , known as founder of The Accountants Digest , which he edited and published until 1973 .
Simon Mathews ( died 1755 ) was a Welsh immigrant who came to Pennsylvania with his cousin Simon Butler in 1712 .
Ulysses Grant - Smith ( 1870 - -1959 ) was an American diplomat originally from Washington County , Pennsylvania .
Johan Martin Preisler ( 14 March 1715 in Nuremberg -- 17 November 1794 in Copenhagen ) was a German engraver , most notable for his work in Denmark .
Kārlis Kļava ( 9 March 1907 -- 1941 ) was a Latvian military officer and sports shooter .
Baldwin Hamey the Younger M.D. ( 1600 - -1676 ) was an English physician , now best known as a medical biographer .
Eugene C. Whitney ( 26 August 1913 -- 22 March 1998 ) was a celebrated power engineer who designed hydroelectric turbines and generators at Westinghouse Electric Company .
Wilmot Hyde Bradley , aka `` Bill '' Bradley ( 4 April 1899 in New Haven , CT -- 12 April 1979 in Bangor , ME ) was a co - founder ( 1943 ) and Chief of the Branch of Military Geology and Chief Geologist of the U.S. Geological Survey from 1944 to 1959 .
John Barkham , D.D. ( 1572?--1642 ) was an English clergyman , antiquary and historian .
Captain Sir Robert Henry Muirhead Collins KCMG , ( 1852 - -1927 ) was an English - born Royal Navy officer , Colonial ( Permanent Victorian Naval Forces ) naval officer , Colonial public servant , Australian Federationist , Australian public service department head and Australia 's official representative in London .
Wladimir Burliuk ( Ukrainian : Володимир Давидович Бурлюк ; Russian : Владимир Давидович Бурлюк ; 1886 - -1917 ) was a Ukrainian avant - garde artist ( Neo - Primitivist and Cubo - Futurist ) , book illustrator .
Henry Compton , 1st Baron Compton ( 14 July 1544 -- 10 December 1589 ) was an English peer and Member of Parliament .
Fawzi al - Ghazzi ( 1891 - -1929 ) ( Arabic : فوزي الغزي‎ ) , was a Syrian politician known for being the father of the Syrian constitution .
Ruud Knuppe ( 6 August 1938 , Amsterdam - 19 April 2002 , Jisp ) was a Dutch sprint canoer who competed in the early 1960s .
John Madew ( died 1555 ) was an English churchman and academic , Regius Professor of Divinity at Cambridge and Master of Clare Hall .
Sir Humphrey Wingfield ( died 1545 ) was an English lawyer and Speaker of the House of Commons of England between 1533 and 1536 .
Ivan Stojmenović ( 1957 -- 3 November 2014 ) was a Serbian - Canadian mathematician and computer scientist well known for his contributions to communications networks and algorithms .
Most Rev. Dr. Nicholas Donnelly ( 23 November 1837 -- 29 March 1920 ) , D.D. , MRIA , was a Roman Catholic auxiliary bishop of Dublin .
Richard de Luci ( 1089 -- 14 July 1179 ) ( also Richard de Lucy ) was first noted as High Sheriff of Essex , after which he was made Chief Justiciar of England .
Joanna Wiszniewicz ( 18 March 1947 -- 31 January 2009 ) was a Polish academic and historian .
Gustav Winkler ( 11 May 1867 in Liegnitz -- 26 April 1954 in Berlin ) was a German industrialist .
Jan Weenix or Joannis Wenix ( between 1640/1649 -- 19 September 1719 ( buried ) ) was a Dutch painter .
Wadie Haddad ( Arabic : وديع حداد‎ ; 1927 -- 28 March 1978 ) , also known as Abu Hani , was a Palestinian leader of the Popular Front for the Liberation of Palestine 's armed wing .
Helen Naha ( 1922 - -1993 ) was the matriarch in a family of well known Hopi potters .
José Álvarez de Toledo y Dubois ( 14 May 1779 , Havana - 16 April 1858 , Paris ) was a politician and leader of a military force against Spanish rule in Texas .
Jonathan Bates ( 1 November 1939 -- 31 October 2008 ) was an English sound editor .
Caesar Kleberg ( September 20 , 1873 - 1946 ) was an American conservationist , born in Cuero , Texas .
Andra Gavrilović ( Serbian : Андра Гавриловић ; Svilajnac , Principality of Serbia 11 July 1864 -- Belgrade , Kingdom of Yugoslavia 24 February 1929 ) was Serbian historian , historian of literature , writer and diplomat .
Joanne Woollard ( died 27 February 2015 ) was a British art director .
Sanya Dharmasakti ( Thai : สัญญา ธรรมศักดิ์ , rtgs : Sanya Thammasak , pronunciation : ( sǎn.jaː tʰam.má.sàk ) , 5 April 1907 -- 6 January 2002 ) was a Thai jurist , university professor and politician .
Ernst Hellmut Vits ( 19 September 1903 -- 23 January 1970 ) was a German lawyer who headed the rayon manufacturer Vereinigte Glanzstoff - Fabriken ( VGF ) from 1940 to 1969 .
Henry Grey , 4th Earl of Kent ( c. 1495 -- 24 September 1562 ) was Earl of Kent from 1524 to his death .
Thomas Vavasour ( born about 1536 - 7 ; died at Kingston upon Hull , 2 May 1585 ) was an English Roman Catholic physician , and pensioner of St John 's College , Cambridge .
George Finch , 9th Earl of Winchilsea KG PC FRS ( 4 November 1752 -- 2 August 1826 ) was an important figure in the history of cricket .
Mark Keyworth ( 19 February 1948 -- 23 November 2014 ) was an English rugby union player who played for Swansea , Aberystwyth , the North Midlands county team and the national team .
Vilho Turunen ( 16 December 1923 , Polvijärvi - 8 February 1973 ) was a Finnish agricultural worker , logger , trade union functionary and politician .
Paul Prosper Henrys ( or Paul - Prosper ) ( 13 March 1862 -- 6 November 1943 ) was a French general .
Christopher Airay ( 1601 -- 18 October 1670 ) was an English preacher and a pioneer in English logic .
Joyce La Mers ( 1920 -- October 2013 ) was an American writer of light poetry .
Stanley Royle ( 1888 - -1961 ) was a post - impressionist English landscape painter and illustrator who lived for most of his life in and around Sheffield ( England ) and Canada .
John Edward Sawyer ( 1917 -- 1995 ) was a prominent academic and philanthropic administrator .
João Soares de Sousa ( 1493 in Vila do Porto -- 2 January 1571 in Vila do Porto ) was the third Donatary - Captain of Santa Maria , succeeding his father João Soares de Albergaria , who had died on 1499 .
Svatopluk Havelka ( born 2 May 1925 -- 24 February 2009 ) was a Czech composer .
Adriana Basile ( ca . 1580 -- ca . 1640 ) was an Italian composer and singer .
I m Yunjidang ( 任允摯堂 ; 1721 - 1793 ) was a Korean scholar , writer and neo - Confucian philosopher .
Admiral Sir Erasmus Ommanney KCB , FRS , FRGS , JP ( 22 May 1814 -- 21 December 1904 ) was a Royal Navy officer and an Arctic explorer of the Victorian era .
Ruy Fernández de Fuenmayor ( 1603 - 1651 ) was a Spanish soldier who was governor of Venezuela Province between 1637 and 1644 .
John Ayliffe , LL.D. ( 1676 - -1732 ) was an English jurist , expelled from the University of Oxford in a high - profile controversy .
Fred Newton Scott ( 1860 - -1931 ) was an American writer , educator and rhetorician .
Tich Gwilym ( 10 September 1950 -- 19 June 2005 ) , born Robert Gwilliam , was a Welsh rock guitarist who was most notable for his Hendrix inspired version of the Welsh national anthem , Hen Wlad Fy Nhadau , considered one of the most famous renditions of the song .
Eugen Anton Theophil von Podbielski ( 17 October 1814 -- 31 October 1879 ) was a general in the Prussian cavalry and general inspector of the artillery .
Leveson Francis Vernon - Harcourt ( 1839 - -1907 ) was a British civil engineer , author of several treatises on river and harbour engineering .
Blanche Robinson ( Mrs. Martin Hennion Robinson , née Williams ; 18 May 1883 , near Liberty , Kansas -- 19 August 1969 , Los Angeles ) was an American composer and well - known piano accompanist .
George Ffitch ( 15 January 1929 - 5 July 2001 ) was a British newsreader , television presenter , radio personality and journalist .
Jehoiada Brewer ( 1752?--1817 ) was a Welsh dissenting minister .
Sir Gilbert Greenall , 1st Baronet DL ( 11 May 1806 -- 10 July 1894 ) , was a British businessman and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1847 and 1892 .
Nepomucena Kostecka , née Żółkowska ( 24 November 1807 -- 10 March 1847 ) was a Polish stage actress .
Juan Ángel Arias ( 1800 - -1842 ) served as the acting Supremo Director of Honduras ( 24 December 1829 -- 22 April 1830 ) .
The Right Reverend Francis Paget , DD ( 20 March 1851 -- 2 August 1911 ) was an English theologian , author and the 33rd Bishop of Oxford .
Zhang Huizan ( 1884 or 1885 - 28 January 1931 ) was a Lieutenant general in the Chinese National Revolutionary Army .
Pieter Corbeels ( Leuven , 12 March 1755 -- Tournai , 21 June 1799 ) was a Belgian book printer and resistance leader .
Peter Hansson is a co - founder and guitarist ( 1987 - -1993 ) of Swedish metal band Therion .
Immanuel Halton ( 1628 - -1699 ) was an English astronomer and mathematician , an associate of John Flamsteed .
Olivia Rossetti Agresti ( 30 September 1875 -- 6 November 1960 ) was a British activist , author , editor , and interpreter .
José Antonio de Areche Zornoza ( died 1788 ) was a Spanish visitador in Peru ( 1777 - -82 ) .
José del Carmen Quesada del Río ( 1833 - 1885 ) was a Chilean lawyer and magistrate .
Ketil Egge ( 11 March 1950 -- 26 March 1997 ) is a Norwegian actor and theatre director .

Katharina of Nassau - Beilstein ( died : 6 September 1459 ) was the daughter of Count Henry II of Nassau - Beilstein and his wife , Katharina of Randerode .
Anderson Ruffin Abbott , M.D. ( 7 April 1837 -- 29 December 1913 ) was the first Black Canadian to be a licensed physician .
Charles Townshend , 2nd Viscount Townshend Bt KG PC FRS ( /ˈtaʊnzənd/ ; 18 April 1674 -- 21 June 1738 ) was a British Whig statesman .
John Albert Broadus ( 1827 - -1895 ) was an American Baptist pastor and President of the Southern Baptist Theological Seminary .
Carl Augustus Heber ( April 15 , 1874 or 1875 --1956 ) was an American sculptor noted for his public monuments .
Charles - Théophile Gaudin ( 4 August 1822 , Petit - Château , near Lausanne -- 12 January 1866 , Lausanne ) was a Swiss paleontologist known for his research in the field of paleobotany .
Agnes Mortimer , Countess of Pembroke ( 1317 -- 25 July 1368 ) was the wife of Laurence Hastings , 1st Earl of Pembroke .
Corneliu Dragalina ( 5 February 1887 , Caransebeș -- 11 July 1949 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian General during World War II , the son of the World War I - general Ion Dragalina .

Holger Gilbert - Jespersen ( 22 September 1890 -- 30 July 1975 ) was a Danish flutist , orchestral musician and academic flute teacher .
Helen Hooker or Helen Hooker O'Malley Roelefs ( 1 January 1905 -- 2 April 1993 ) was an American sculptor and portrait painter who spent a considerable part of career in Ireland .
Lieutenant General Alexander Mackenzie Fraser ( 1758 - 13 September 1809 ) was a British General .
Giovanni Bassignani ( 1669 -- May 1717 ) was an Italian architect and engineer of the late - Baroque .
Helen Octavia Dickens ( 1909 - -2001 ) was the first African - American woman to be admitted to the American College of Surgeons .
Albert Webster Edgerly ( 1852 -- 1926 ) was a 19th- and 20th - century American social reform activist .
Hamilton Wright Mabie , A.M. , L.H.D. , LL.D. ( 1846 - -1916 ) was an American essayist , editor , critic , and lecturer .
Laurel Elizabeth Keyes ( died 1983 ) was an American author , lecturer and counselor .
John - Baptiste Nguyễn Bửu Đồng was a Vietnamese Roman Catholic priest from the city of Huế who was murdered by the Việtcộng during the 1968 Tet Offensive .
John Cook Wilson ( born Nottingham 6 June 1849 , died 11 August 1915 ) was an English philosopher .
Major General Hisham Ikhtiyar ( 1941 -- 20 July 2012 ) ( family name also transliterated as Ikhtiar , Bakhtiar , Bekhityar , Bekhtyar and other variants ) was a Syrian military official , and a national security adviser to president Bashar al - Assad .
Johannes Ludwig Janson ( 1 September 1849 -- 28 October 1914 ) was a German specialist in veterinary science .
Mary Wimbush ( 19 March 1924 -- 31 October 2005 ) was an English actress whose career spanned sixty years from the 1940s to the 2000s .
Lars Olsson Smith ( 12 October 1836 -- 9 December 1913 ) , also L.O. Smith , was a Swedish spirits manufacturer and politician .
Ella Fry ( née Robinson ) ( 1916 - -1997 ) was an artist , musician , and chairperson of the Western Australian Art Gallery , in Perth , Western Australia from 1976 to 1986 .
Humble Ward , 1st Baron Ward , of Birmingham ( c. 1614 -- 14 October 1670 ) was the son and heir of William Ward , a London goldsmith .
Marharajah Badan Singh ( Hindi : बदन सिंह ) ( Reign : 1722 - -1756 ) was the formal founder of the princely state of Bharatpur .
Bobby Buckle ( 1869 - -1959 ) was one of twelve schoolboys who founded the Hotspur Football Club in 1882 later to become Tottenham Hotspur Football Club .
James Henthorn Todd ( 23 April 1805 -- 28 June 1869 ) was a biblical scholar , educator , and Irish historian .
Michel Bakhoum ( 1913 - -1981 ; Arabic : ميشيل باخوم‎ , Mīšīl Bāḫūm ) was an Egyptian consulting civil engineer , university professor , and a researcher in concrete structures .
Francis Chambers ( 1828/1829 - 30 November 1900 ) was a British architect , active in London .
Frank Stukus died July 2001 , age 83 , pre - deceased by his first wife Anna and his son Frank Jr. , and survived by wife Audrey , daughter Maureen and grandchildren Robert and Anna .
Hugh Potter ( 1596 -- 12 February 1662 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1640 and 1662 .
Luis Ceballos y Fernández de Córdoba ( 31 July 1896 in San Lorenzo de El Escorial -- 26 September 1967 ) was a Spanish forest engineer and botanist .
Archibald Targett ( 1862 -- 1931 ) was a tinsmith and political figure in Newfoundland .

Mary Jane Seaman , married name Mrs. Chippendale ( 1837 ? , Salisbury -- 26 May 1888 , Camberwell ) was an English actress .
Rose Beaudet ( 1862 - -1947 ) was an American actress and opera singer of the late Victorian era and early 20th century who regularly appeared in musical theatre .
Phil Carreón ( aka Phillip Lozano Carreón , Jr. ; né Alonzo Carreón ; 6 May 1923 Los Angeles -- 13 October 2010 Boulder City , Nevada ) was an American big band leader based in Los Angeles who flourished from 1946 to 1952 , retiring from music in 1952 .
Sebastian Horsley ( born Marcus A. Horsley ; 8 August 1962 -- 17 June 2010 ) was a London artist .
Nelly Moore or Eleanora Moore ( 1844/45 -- 12 January 1869 ) was a British actress who died young .
Frederick Whitworth Aylmer , 6th Baron Aylmer ( 12 October 1777 -- 5 March 1858 ) was a British Royal Navy officer who fought during the French Revolutionary Wars and the Napoleonic Wars and who eventually rose to the rank of admiral .

Fráech mac Finchada or Fróech mac Findchado ( died 495 ) was a king of Leinster .
Les Charge ( 27 July 1891 -- 30 March 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
François de Bas ( 10 September 1840 -- 22 February 1931 ) was a Dutch general and military historian .
Charles Lambart , 3rd Earl of Cavan ( 7 September 1649 -- 5 December 1702 ) was an Irish peer .
Walter Rehberg ( 14 May 1900 in Geneva -- 24 October 1957 ) was a Swiss concert pianist , composer and writer on musical subjects who was particularly active from the 1920s to 1950s .
Carl Martin Bergh ( December 22 , 1849 -- June 15 , 1906 ) was a Norwegian - American immigrant who is most associated with the resettlement of fellow Scandinavian families to the area of James City County and York County surrounding the community of Norge , Virginia .
Giorgio Borg Olivier ( Maltese : Ġorġ Borg Olivier ) ( 5 July 1911 -- 29 October 1980 ) , also known as George Borg Olivier , was a Maltese statesman and leading politician .

Archduke Friedrich , Duke of Teschen ( Friedrich Maria Albrecht Wilhelm Karl ; 4 June 1856 -- 30 December 1936 ) was a member of the House of Habsburg and the Supreme Commander of the Austro - Hungarian Army during World War I.
Heinrich Meldahl ( 8 September 1776 -- 24 February 1840 ) was a Norwegian builder , architect and the owner of an iron foundry .
Thomas Brett ( 1747 , Catherington , Hampshire -- 31 December 1809 , Kingston Cross , Portsmouth , Hampshire ) was one of first - class cricket 's earliest well - known fast bowlers and a leading player for Hampshire when its team was organised by the Hambledon Club in the 1770s .
Moropant Ramchandra Paradkar ( Devanagari : मोरेश्वर रामजी पराडकर ) ( 1729 - -1794 ) , popularly known in Maharashtra as Moropant ( मोरोपंत ) or Mayur Pandit ( मयूर पंडित ) , was a Karhade Brahmin Marathi poet who was the last among those classified by Marathi literary scholars as pandit ( पंडित ) poets .
Antonio Ruiz - Pipó ( 27 April 1934 -- 24 October 1997 ) was a Spanish virtuoso pianist and composer .

Gustav Kramer ( 11 March 1910 -- 19 April 1959 ) was a German zoologist and ornithologist who specialised in allometry .
Sidney Griffith ( née Wynne ; died 1752 ) , known in her time as `` Madam '' Griffith , was an important figure in the Welsh Methodist revival of the mid-18th century .
José Veríssimo Dias de Matos ( 8 April 1857 -- 2 December 1916 ) was a writer , educator , journalist , literary critic , and founding member of the Brazilian Academy of Letters .
Otto Detlev Creutzfeldt ( 1 April 1927 -- 23 January 1992 ) was a German physiologist and neurologist .
Milorad Nedeljković ( 3 December 1883 , Knjaževac , Kingdom of Serbia - 1961 , France ) was a Serbian economist and Axis - collaborating politician .

Maol Muire Ó hÚigínn ( Anglicised : Miler O'Higgin , died circa 1590 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic clergyman .
Wickliffe Draper ( August 9 , 1891 -- 1972 ) was an American multimillionaire and philanthropist .
Emanoil Bârzotescu ( 20 October , 1888 - 3 July , 1968 ) was a Romanian Major - General during World War II . He served as General Officer Commanding 1st Division from 1940 to 1942 , and retired in 1942 .
Endymion Porter ( 1587 - -1649 ) was an English diplomat and royalist .
Carolina Uccelli ( 1810 - -1885 ) was an Italian composer known for opera .
Ethel Dench Puffer Howes ( 1872 - -1950 ) was an American psychologist and feminist organizer .
Sampson Gideon ( February 1699 in London -- 17 October 1762 ) was a Jewish - British banker in the City of London .
Sir Edward Bagnall Poulton , FRS ( 27 January 1856 -- 20 November 1943 ) was a British evolutionary biologist who was a lifelong advocate of natural selection through a period in which many scientists such as Reginald Punnett doubted its importance .
Alexander Cores ( 1901-February 5 , 1994 ) was a violinist and founder and first violin of the Dorian String Quartet .
The Reverend Dr Robert Stirling ( 25 October 1790 -- 6 June 1878 ) was a Scottish clergyman , and inventor of the Stirling engine .
Sir James Grant , 1st Baronet ( died 1695 ) was a Scottish lawyer of the seventeenth century .
Gwynfor Davies ( 12 August 1908 - 10 March 1972 ) was a Welsh cricketer .
Rudolf Ruedemann ( October 16 , 1864 - -June 18 , 1956 ) was a German American paleontologist , widely known as an expert in graptolites , enigmatic fossil animals .
Captain Charles John Philip Cave FRAS , FSA ( 1 May 1871 -- 8 December 1950 ) was a meteorologist , a church architectural historian , and a captain in the Royal Engineers .
David Broadfoot GC ( 21 July 1899 -- 31 January 1953 ) was a Scottish seaman awarded the George Cross for his role during the sinking of the MV Princess Victoria .
Gustaf Flink , born 18 January 1848 in Ås Parish , Skaraborg County , died 11 January 1931 , was a Swedish mineralogist .
Tom Dardis ( 1926 - -2001 ) was an American author and editor .
Vasile Roaită ( 1914 - -16 February 1933 ) was a Romanian railway worker for Căile Ferate Române , shot during the Griviţa Strike of 1933 and later touted as a proletarian hero under the Communist regime of Gheorghe Gheorghiu - Dej .
Alfred Cowles , Jr. ( 5 January 1865 , Chicago -- 15 January 1939 , Chicago ) He was the son of Alfred Cowles , Sr . and Sarah Hutchinson Cowles .
Tung Kuei - sen ( 1951 - 3 April 1991 ) was a member of the Taiwan - based United Bamboo Gang .
Ted Nealon ( 24 November 1929 -- 28 January 2014 ) was an Irish Fine Gael politician and journalist .
General Sir Robert Henry MacFarlane , KCB , GCH ( 1771 - -1841 ) was a British Army officer during the Napoleonic Wars .
Dentist Stanley D. Tylman ( 1893 - 1982 ) taught more than 1,000 students at the University of Illinois at Chicago College of Dentistry in his career as a Professor of Dentistry ( 1920 - 1962 ) and head of the Department of Fixed Partial Prosthodontics , and also influenced dentists internationally .
William Mackay Mackenzie ( 1871 - -1952 ) was a Scottish historian , archaeologist and writer , who was Secretary of the Royal Commission on Ancient and Historical Monuments of Scotland between 1913 and 1935 , and also an expert on folk - lore .
Kevin Whyman ( 4 October 1975 - 1 August 2015 ) was an English rower , turned air pilot , who died in an aviation accident at the 2015 CarFest .
Geertruid Adriaansdochter ( ? ? in Wormer -- 1573 in IJpesloot near Amsterdam ) , was a Dutch farmer .
Francis X. King ( 10 January 1934 -- 8 November 1994 ) was a British occult writer and editor who wrote about tarot , divination , witchcraft , magic , sex magic , tantra , and holistic medicine .
Savitri Khanolkar , born Eve Yvonne Maday de Maros , on July 20 , 1913 -- 1990 in Neuchâtel , Switzerland .
Gangadhar Nehru ( 1827 -- February 1861 ) was an Indian police officer , who served as the last kotwal of Delhi ( Chief of police ) in the court of Bahadur Shah II , before the position was abolished following the Indian Rebellion of 1857 .
Sir Edward Beauchamp , 1st Baronet ( 12 April 1849 -- 1 February 1925 ) was a British businessman and Liberal Party politician .
Godfroy Langlois ( 26 December 1866 -- 6 April 1928 ) was a politician , a journalist and a lawyer in Quebec .
John Blake ( 1890 -- 2 September 1960 ) , better known as Bandsman Jack Blake , was a British boxer who became British middleweight champion in 1916 .
Samuel Eson Johnson Ecoma ( 29 November 1930 -- 30 August 1999 ) was a Nigerian jurist and the Chief Judge of Cross River State appointed in March 1990 .
John Reynell ( 1809 - -1873 ) was a South Australian winemaker .
Friedrich William Adalbert von Bredow ( 24 May 1814 -- 3 March 1890 ) was a German cavalry officer .
Jacometto Veneziano ( active 1472 - -1497 ) , was an Italian painter .
John Hamilton , 1st Marquess of Hamilton ( c. 1535 -- 26 April 1604 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Sir Henry Bagenal PC ( c. 1556 -- 14 August 1598 ) was marshal of the army in Ireland during the reign of Queen Elizabeth I.
Sigebert III ( c. 630 - -656/660 ) was the king of Austrasia from 634 to his death ; probably on 1 February 656 , or maybe as late as 660 .
George Henry Bruce Blunt , otherwise known as Bruce Blunt ( 1 July 1899 -- 8 July 1957 ) was an English poet , journalist and wine merchant best known for his collaborations with the composer Peter Warlock .
Victor Roelens ( 21 July 1858 -- 5 August 1947 ) was a Belgian priest who became Vicar Apostolic of Upper Congo in 1895 , and remained the premier bishop in the Congo Free State , then the Belgian Congo , until he retired in 1941 .
Givi Amilakhvari ( Georgian : გივი ამილახვარი ) ( 1689 - -1754 ) was a Georgian nobleman ( tavadi ) with a prominent role in the politics of eastern Georgia in the first half of the 18th century .
Sir Frederick Dixon - Hartland , 1st Baronet ( 1 May 1832 -- 15 November 1909 ) was an antiquary , banker and a Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1881 to 1909 .
Charles Alfred Matley ( 1866 - -1947 ) was a British paleontologist and geologist in India , the British West Indies and Wales .
Herman Rudolf Günsberg ( 1827 - -1879 ) was a chemist originating in Pidkamin , near Brody who distinguished himself by his fostering of the economic development of Galicia .
Victor Bruns ( Russian : Виктор Брунс ; 15 August 1904 -- 6 December 1996 ) was a German composer and bassoonist .
Heneage Finch , 6th Earl of Aylesford DL ( 24 December 1824 -- 10 January 1871 ) , styled Lord Guernsey until 1859 , was a British peer and politician .
John Pennington , 1st Baron Muncaster ( c. 1740 -- 8 October 1813 ) , known as John Pennington until 1783 , was a British peer and Tory politician .
Sir Anthony Kingston ( ca . 1508 -- 14 April 1556 ) was an English royal official , holder of various positions under several Tudor monarchs .
Wang Ya ( Chinese : 王涯 ; died December 17 , 835 ) , courtesy name Guangjin ( 廣津 ) , formally Duke of Dai ( 代公 ) , was an official of the Chinese Tang dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Xianzong and Emperor Xianzong 's grandson Emperor Wenzong .
Hugh Smyth , OBE ( 1941 -- 12 May 2014 ) was a Northern Irish politician who was leader of the Progressive Unionist Party .
His Majesty Ambrose Ezeolisa Allagoa ( 1914 - 2003 ) was King of Nembe Kingdom from 1980 until his death .
Denis Flannery ( 2 April 1928 -- 12 February 2012 ) was an Australian rugby league footballer of the 1940s and 50s .

Laurent - Benoît Dewez ( 14 April 1731 -- 1 November 1812 ) was a Belgian architect of Walloon origin .
General Sir Robert John Hussey Vivian GCB ( 1802 - -1887 ) was a British officer in the Madras infantry from the Vivian family .
Giuseppe Vari ( 9 March 1924 -- 1 October 1993 ) was an Italian film director , editor and screenwriter .
Erling Falk ( 12 August 1887 -- 31 July 1940 ) was a Norwegian politician , ideologist and writer .
Herbert Edward Andrewes ( 1863 , Reading - 1950 , Highgate ) was an English entomologist who specialised in beetles of the order Coleoptera .
The Rt Revd Hollingworth Tully Kingdon DD ( known as Tully ) was an Anglican bishop , the second Bishop of Fredericton until his death on 13 October 1907 .
Manol Lazarov Sofiyanets ( Bulgarian:Манол Лазаров Софиянец ) born 1826 and died 1881 , was a Bulgarian educationalist , poet and writer based in Sofia .
M. C. Joshi ( 1928 - -1983 ) from Belgaum , India was a nuclear physicist and the founder and head of the university department of physics , University of Mumbai .
Maria of Bosnia ( German : Maria von Bosnien ; Bosnian : Марија , Marija ; d. 27 April 1403 ) was a member of the House of Kotromanić who married into the House of Helfenstein .
Louise Adeline Weitzel ( December 2 , 1862 -- May 6 , 1934 ) was an American writer of German descent .
Abraham Wood ( 1610 - -1682 ) , sometimes referred to as `` General '' or `` Colonel '' Wood , was an English fur trader ( specifically the beaver and deerskin trades ) and explorer of 17th century colonial Virginia .
Ernest Gagnon ( 7 November 1834 -- 15 September 1915 ) was a Canadian folklorist , composer , and organist .
Sir Norton Knatchbull , 1st Baronet ( 26 December 1602 -- 3 February 1685 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1640 and 1679 .
Elijah Johnson ( c.1789(A ) -- April 3 , 1849 ) was an African American who was one of the first colonial agents of the American Colonization Society in what later became Liberia .
Sir John Maxwell Bemrose ( 1 July 1904 -- 13 July 1986 ) , known as Sir Max Bemrose , was an English industrialist , politician , and county officer for Derbyshire .
Ali ibn Yusuf ( Arabic : علي بن يوسف‎ ) ( born 1084 died 26 January 1143 ) was the 5th Almoravid king he reigned 1106 - -1143 .
Otto Sander ( 30 June 1941 -- 12 September 2013 ) was a German film , theater , and voice actor .
Robert MacCarty , Viscount Muskerry ( 1698 -- 19 September 1769 ) was an Irish officer of the Royal Navy , and a colonial administrator .
Gideon Lincecum ( 22 April 1793 -- 28 November 1874 ) was an American pioneer , historian , physician , philosopher , and naturalist .
Rosita Beatrice Missick - Butterfield , MBE ( 14 November 1936 -- 10 January 2015 ) was a Turks and Caicos Islander who served as the first woman Member of Parliament and Speaker of the House of Assembly of the Turks and Caicos Islands .
Julius Ernst Rautenstein ( ca . 1590 - 95 ; after 6 March 1654 ) was a German composer .

Betty Duvall ( 1845 - -1891 ) was a Confederate spy during the American Civil War .
Ne Win ( Burmese : နေဝင်း IPA : ( ne wɪɴ ) ; 14 May 1910 -- 5 December 2002 ) was a Burmese politician and military commander .
Otto Wood ( 1894 -- Dec. 31 , 1930 ) was a Depression - era desperado , born in Wilkes County , N.C. in 1894 .
David G. Goodman ( 12 February 1946 -- 25 July 2011 ) was an American academic , author , editor and Japanologist .
Helene Anna Held ( 19 March 1872 -- 12 August 1918 ) , known professionally as Anna Held , was a Polish - born French stage performer and singer , most often associated with impresario Florenz Ziegfeld , her common - law husband .
Charles Bocquet ( 13 December 1918 -- 19 June 1977 ) was a French biologist , Professor of the Université de Paris and an expert on crustaceans .
Father Sergei Spytetsky ( Polish : Sergiusz Spytecki ) ( 12 July 1877- 28 August 1963 ) was an Orthodox ( and later Greek - Catholic ) priest .
Louisa Jo Killen ( né Louis Killen ; 10 January 1934 -- 9 August 2013 ) was an English folk singer from Gateshead , Tyneside .
Harold Trowbridge Pulsifer ( born November 18 , 1886 Manchester , Connecticut - 1948 Sarasota , Florida ) was an American poet and magazine editor .
Revaz Gabashvili ( Georgian : რევაზ გაბაშვილი ) ( November 6 , 1882 -- 1969 ) was a Georgian politician and writer involved in the independence movement and revolutionary journalism in the early 20th century .
Freddie Tavares ( 1913 - -1990 ) was an American musician and inventor .
Axel Erik Heinrichs ( 21 July 1890 -- 16 November 1965 ) was a Finnish military general .
Joseph Quinn ( c. 1861-July 5 , 1887 ) was a New York clerk , amateur wrestler and murder victim of Danny Lyons , a co - leader of the Whyos street gang .
Johann Lukas Legrand ( or Jean - Luc Le Grand ; 30 May 1755 -- 4 October 1836 ) was a Swiss silk ribbon manufacturer and politician at the time of the Helvetic Republic .
