John Drummond , 2nd Earl of Perth ( 1588 -- 11 June 1662 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Rombout Verhulst ( 15 January 1624 -- buried 27 November 1698 ) was a Flemish sculptor and draughtsman who spent most of his career in the Dutch Republic .
Dudley Mecum ( 1896 - -1978 ) was an American pianist , vocalist and songwriter .
István Szelmár , also known in Slovene as Števan Selmar ( 23 October 1820 -- 15 February 1877 ) was a Slovene Roman Catholic priest and writer in the Kingdom of Hungary .
Daniel Gralath ( 30 May 1708 -- 23 July 1767 ) was a physicist and a mayor of Danzig .
Stephen Decatur Hatch ( b. 1839 - d. 1894 ) was a prominent late-19th century architect who was responsible for a number of historically or architecturally significant buildings in Manhattan , New York City and elsewhere .
Alfred Hoppe ( 6 June 1830 -- 15 April 1919 ) was an English cricketer active in the 1850s .
Anastasios Metaxas ( Greek : Αναστάσιος Μεταξάς , 27 February 1862 -- 28 January 1937 ) was a Greek architect and shooter .
Oliver Perry - Smith ( October 11 , 1884 in Philadelphia -- 13 May 1969 ) was an American rock climber , mountaineer and skier who moved to Dresden in 1902 to attend a technical university .
Charles Upham Shepard ( born in Little Compton , Rhode Island , 29 June 1804 ; died in Charleston , South Carolina , 1 May 1886 ) was an American mineralogist .
Henry Olaf Hoff ( 14 July 1912 -- 25 June 2011 ) was a Norwegian welder , trade unionist and politician for the Communist and Labour parties .
Mountague Bernard ( January 28 , 1820 -- 1882 ) was an English international lawyer .
Martin Schaffner ( 1478 - -1548 ) was a German painter and medallist .
Sergio Peresson ( 1913 - -1991 ) was an Italian - born violin maker .
Arthur Greiner ( 1884 Chicago , Illinois -- 15 Dec 1916 Chicago , Illinois ) was an American racecar driver , and historically the first to finish last in the Indianapolis 500 .
Shakir Hassan Al Said ( Arabic : شاكر حسن ال سعيد‎ ) ( 1925 - -2004 ) , an Iraqi painter , sculptor and writer , is considered one of Iraq 's most innovative and influential artists .
Sir Isaac Wolfson , 1st Baronet FRS ( 17 September 1897 -- 20 June 1991 ) was a Scottish businessman and philanthropist .
Merga Bien ( late 1560s -- 1603 ) was a German woman convicted of witchcraft and perhaps the most famous of the victims in the Fulda witch trials in 1603 - -1605 .
Peregrine Hoby ( 1 September 1602 -- 6 May 1679 ) , was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1640 and 1679 .
Russell Bulgin ( 1958 - -2002 ) was an automotive journalist .
Raymond Yellow Thunder ( January 1 , 1921 -- February 13 , 1972 ) was an Oglala Lakota , born in Kyle , South Dakota , on the Pine Ridge Indian Reservation .
Tofail Ahmed ( 1920 at Baralia village , Lakshmipur District in Bangladesh -- 2002 in Dhaka , Bangladesh ) was a well - known Bangladeshi researcher of Folk Art . He was also a collector of Folk artifacts and has authored several books on Bangladeshi Folk arts and Crafts .
Daniel Rudge ( 1840 -- June 26 , 1880 ) was a British engineer who built high - end bicycles and velocipedes .
Margaret Sanborn ( 1915 - -2005 ) was an American writer and biographer of Robert E. Lee and Mark Twain ( aka Samuel Clemens ) .
Richard Henry Coleman ( 3 April 1888 -- 17 February 1965 ) was a cathedral organist , who served at Peterborough Cathedral .
Chris Canavan ( 1928/1929 -- 1 March 2013 ) was a British television and stage actor .
Mohammad Nabi Mohammadi died in Pakistani hospital on 21 April 2002 .
Alexander Rudolf Hohlfeld ( born December 29 , 1865 in Dresden , Saxony ( Germany ) , died 1956 in Wisconsin ) was a professor of German at the University of Wisconsin from 1901 until 1936 .
Sir John de Grey ( died 1266 ) was an English soldier and High Sheriff .
William Henry Leatham ( 6 July 1815 - 14 November 1889 ) was a British banker , poet and Liberal politician .
James Sheridan Muspratt ( 8 March 1821 -- 3 February 1871 ) was a research chemist and teacher .
Edmee Sophie Gail née Garre ( b. 28 August 1775 , d. 24 July 1819 ) was a French singer and composer .
Wayne England ( died 9 February 2016 ) was an English artist whose work regularly appeared in role - playing games , wargaming rulebooks and magazines and was used on cards for collectible card games such as Magic :
Leslie Armour ( 9 March 1931 -- 1 November 2014 ) was a Canadian - born philosopher and writer on social economics .
Spencer Rodney , 5th Baron Rodney ( 30 April 1785 -- 15 May 1846 ) was an English peer and clergyman , styled The Honourable Spencer Rodney from 1802 until 1843 .
Walter Gorn ( 24 September 1898 -- 10 July 1968 ) was a German general , serving during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves and Swords ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub und Schwertern ) .
Anastasius ( Greek : Ἀρτέμιος Ἀναστάσιος Β΄ ) , known in English as Anastasios II or Anastasius II ( died 719 ) , was the Byzantine Emperor from 713 to 715 .
Sir William Robertson Nicoll CH ( 10 October 1851 -- 4 May 1923 ) was a Scottish Free Church minister , journalist , editor , and man of letters .
Sir Thomas Manly Deane ( 1851 -- 1933 ) was an Irish architect , the son of Sir Thomas Newenham Deane and grandson of Sir Thomas Deane , who were also architects .
Jakob Wimpfeling ( 25 July 1450 -- 17 November 1528 ) was a Renaissance humanist and theologian .
Musa McKim Guston , née McKim ( August 23 , 1908 -- March 30 , 1992 ) , was a painter and poet .
Erol Güney ( born Mikhael Rottenberg ; 29 August 1914 -- 12 October 2009 ) was a Turkish - Israeli journalist , translator and author .
Pierre Alphonse de Tonty , or Alphonse de Tonty , Baron de Paludy ( ca . 1659 -- 10 November 1727 ) was an officer who served under the French explorer Cadillac and helped establish the first European settlement at Detroit , Michigan , Fort Pontchartrain du Detroit on the Detroit River in 1701 .
Sir Alfred Henry Thesiger ( 15 July 1838 -- 20 October 1880 ) , styled The Hon . Alfred Thesiger from 1858 to 1877 and The Rt Hon . Lord Justice Thesiger from 1877 , was a British lawyer and judge .
Mary Frith ( c. 1584 -- 26 July 1659 ) , alias Moll ( or Mal ) Cutpurse , was a notorious pickpocket and fence of the London underworld .
Captain Levett Landon Boscawen Ibbetson ( 1799 -- 8 September 1869 ) was an English 19th century geologist , inventor , organiser and soldier .
Cyril Morley Shelford ( 1921 -- 2001 ) was a rancher , author and political figure in British Columbia .
Ahmed Mohamed Mahmoud ( ca . 1974 -- 4 February 2011 ) was an Egyptian print reporter for the newspaper Al Tawuun , which is distributed by state - run Al - Ahram .
George S. Phalen ( 2 December 1911 , Peoria , Illinois -- 14 April 1998 , Dallas ) was an American hand surgeon remembered for his work on carpal tunnel syndrome including his description of Phalen 's maneuver .
Shneur Zalman Fradkin of Lublin ( 1830 - -1902 ) , also known as the Toras Chessed ( after his main work ) or The Liader ( after his place of birth ) , was a famous Chabad posek and gaon .
Max Finkelstein ( died 1940 ) was a captain in the New York City Police Department .
Jacopo de ' Barbari , sometimes known or referred to as de'Barbari , de Barberi , de Barbari , Barbaro , Barberino , Barbarigo or Barberigo ( c. 1460/70 -- before 1516 ) , was an Italian painter and printmaker with a highly individual style .
Franz Behr ( 22 July 1837 -- 15 February 1898 ) was a prolific , but minor , and now almost forgotten , German composer of songs and salon pieces for piano .
Fu Dingyi ( Chinese : 符定一 ; pinyin : Fú Dìngyī ; 12 December 1877 -- 3 May 1958 ) was a Chinese educator and scholar .
Atle Jebsen ( 10 November 1935 -- 13 October 2009 ) was a Norwegian businessperson and ship - owner .
Jakob Zeugheer ( known also as J. Z. Herrmann ) , ( born Zürich 20 July 1803 ; died Liverpool 15 June 1865 ) was a Swiss violinist , conductor and composer .
Yamuna Karjee ( 1898 - 1953 ) was an Indian independence activist .
Jules Jacot - Guillarmod ( 24 December 1868 -- 5 June 1925 ) was a Swiss doctor , mountaineer and photographer .
Virginia Livingston ( 1906 - -1990 ) was an American physician and cancer researcher who advocated the unsupported theory that a specific species of bacteria she named Progenitor cryptocides was the primary cause of cancer in humans .
Radomir Pavitchevitch ( died 24 July 2005 ) was a French legionnaire , veteran of World War II . He enlisted for five years on 9 December 1931 , and was assigned to the 2nd Foreign Legion Regiment at Oujda , Algeria .
`` Shorty '' George Snowden ( July 4 , 1904 -- May 1982 ) was an American dancer in Harlem during the 1920s and 1930s .
James Chester Manifold ( 10 February 1867 -- 30 October 1918 ) was an Australian politician and philanthropist .
Ralph Cornall ( 17 March 1894 -- 19 October 1984 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Richard Bellings ( 1613 - -1677 ) was a lawyer and political figure in 17th century Ireland and in the Wars of the Three Kingdoms .
Mufti Mahmood Hasan Gangohi ( 1907 - -1996 ) was an Indian Mufti and Islamic scholar .
Barry Coward ( 22 February 1941 - 17 March 2011 ) was professor of history at Birkbeck College , University of London , and an expert on the Stuart age .
Luigi Carpaneda ( 28 November 1925 -- 14 December 2011 ) was an Italian fencer and sailor .
Major - General James Robert Brunker ( 22 December 1806 -- 24 March 1869 ) was Commander of British Troops in China and Hong Kong .
Kalevi Hämäläinen ( 13 December 1932 -- 10 January 2005 ) was a Finnish cross - country skier who competed in the late 1950s and early 1960s .
Björn J : son Lindh ( born Björn Lindh ; 25 October 1944 -- 21 December 2013 ) was a Swedish flautist , pianist , music arranger , composer and artist .
Richard Davis Anderson , Sr . ( 17 February 1922 -- 4 March 2008 ) was an American mathematician known internationally for his work in infinite - dimensional topology .
Humphrey Lestocq ( 23 January 1919 -- 29 January 1984 ) was a British actor , best known for his roles in Angels One Five ( 1952 ) and The Long Shadow ( 1961 ) , and guest appearances in the television series , The Avengers .
Stelios Perpiniadis ( Greek : Στέλιος Περπινιάδης , 1899 -- 4 September 1977 ) , better known as Stellakis ( Greek : Στελλάκης ) , was a Greek folk musician who wrote , sang , and played guitar in the rebetiko style .
Antonio Draghi ( ca . 1634 -- 16 January 1700 ) was a Baroque composer .
Lockie Wood ( 4 November 1904 -- 3 March 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Arthur South ( 29 October 1914 -- 28 January 2003 ) was a prominent Norfolk politician and administrator in the 1970s .
Silvestro Durante ( died 1672 ) was an Italian church musician and composer .
Ambrose Harris ( 29 October 1902 -- 1952 ) was an English professional footballer who played in a number of positions , mainly as a half - back .
Basil Lam ( 1914 - 4 March 1984 ) was an English early music scholar and harpsichordist .
Barbara of Brandenburg ( 30 May 1464 -- 4 September 1515 ) , a member of the German House of Hohenzollern , was by birth Margravine of Brandenburg and by her two marriages Duchess of Głogów from 1472 to 1476 and Queen of Bohemia from 1476 to 1490/1500 .
Josep Maria Puig Doria ( died 2006 ) was a Spanish jeweller .
Thomas O'Hagan , 1st Baron O'Hagan KP , PC , QC ( 29 May 1812 -- 1 February 1885 ) , was an Irish lawyer and judge .
Wong Ah Kiu ( 1918 -- 19 January 2006 ) , legally known as Nyonya binti Tahir , was a Malaysian woman born to a Muslim family but raised Buddhist .
Maio of Bari ( Italian : Maione da Bari ) ( died 10 November 1160 ) was the third of the great admirals of Sicily and the most important man in the Norman kingdom of Sicily during the reign of William I ( 1154 - -66 ) .
Henry Perigal , Jr. FRAS MRI ( 1 April 1801 -- 6 June 1898 ) was a British stockbroker and amateur mathematician , known for his dissection - based proof of the Pythagorean theorem and for his unorthodox belief that the moon does not rotate .
Roy John Britten ( 1 October 1919 -- 21 January 2012 ) was an American molecular biologist known for his discovery of repeated DNA sequences in the genomes of eukaryotic organisms , and later on the evolution of the genome .
Antonello da Messina , properly Antonello di Giovanni di Antonio , but also called Antonello degli Antoni ( c. 1430 -- February 1479 ) , was an Italian painter from Messina , Sicily , active during the Italian Renaissance .
Giovanni Pietro de Pomis ( ca.1565 or 1569/70 -- 6 March 1633 ) was an Italian painter , medailleur , architect and fortress master builder .
Thomas Friedrich Zobel von Giebelstadt und Darstadt ( 1799 - 12 July 1869 ) was an Austrian lieutenant feldmarshal .
Heywood Hardy ( 1842 - 1933 ) was an English painter , especially known for his hunting motifs .
William McGibbon ( April 1690 , in Glasgow , Scotland -- 3 October 1756 ) was a Scottish composer and violinist .
K. S. Narayanaswamy , ( born Koduvayur Sivarama Narayanaswamy , Tamil : கொடுவயூர் சிவராம நாராயணஸ்வாமி ; 27 September 1914 -- 1999 ) was a Carnatic veena exponent of the Thanjavur style , in which nuances and subtleties are given more importance over rhythm based acrobatics .
Yahya El Mashad ( Arabic : يحيى المشد‎ ; u1932 -- 14 June 1980 ) was an Egyptian nuclear scientist who headed the Iraqi nuclear program .
James Mann , 5th Earl Cornwallis ( 20 September 1778 -- 21 May 1852 ) , known as James Cornwallis until 1814 and as James Mann between 1814 and 1823 and styled Viscount Brome between 1823 and 1824 , was a British peer and Tory politician .
Spencer Smith - White ( 14 April 1909 -- 26 March 1998 ) was an Australian botanist , winner of the Clarke Medal in 1967 .
Harry C. Solomon ( 1889 - -1982 ) , an American neurologist , psychiatrist , researcher , administrator , and clinician , was among the first to advocate for major changes in public psychiatry .
Oktay Sinanoğlu ( 25 February 1935 - 19 April 2015 ) was an internationally renowned Turkish scientist of physical chemistry , molecular biophysics and biochemistry .
Rudolf Kaiser ( 10 September 1922 -- 11 September 1991 ) was a designer of gliders who worked for Alexander Schleicher GmbH & Co. The designs of Rudolf Kaiser have proven themselves for over 50 years all over the world .
Anton Christoforidis ( Greek : Αντώνης Χριστοφορίδης ) ( 26 May 1917 -- 31 October 1985 ) was a Greek professional light heavyweight boxer .
Paul Abraham ( Hungarian : Ábrahám Pál ; 2 November 1892 -- 6 May 1960 ) was a composer of operettas .
Henry William Pickersgill RA ( 3 December 1782 -- 21 April 1875 ) was an English painter specialising in portraits .
Inta Ezergailis ( 11 September 1932 in Riga , Latvia -- 1 January 2005 , in Ithaca , New York ) , was a Latvian American professor emerita of German literature at Cornell University from 1969 to 1999 , specializing in Thomas Mann and contemporary women writers .
Arthur Tracy ( 25 June 1899 -- 5 October 1997 ) was an American vocalist , billed as The Street Singer .
Percy Abercrombie ( 1 January 1884 -- 22 May 1964 ) was an Australian rules footballer of the 1900s who played with Essendon and South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Roy McGregor ( 8 July 1894 -- 1 June 1977 ) was a New Zealand zoologist and conservationist who was successful in halting forestry in the Waipoua forest and establishing the forest as a protected sanctuary .
Henry Holland , 3rd Duke of Exeter ( 27 June 1430 -- September 1475 ) was a Lancastrian leader during the English Wars of the Roses .
Josephine Bell , pseudonym of Doris Bell Collier , ( 8 December 1897 - -24 April 1987 ) , was an English physician and writer .
Helen Bright Clark ( 1840 - -1927 ) was a British women 's rights activist and suffragist .
John Norman Heathcote ( 21 June 1863 -- 16 July 1946 ) was a British author , watercolourist and photographer , best remembered for his book St Kilda , published in 1900 , about the Scottish Hebridean archipelago of St Kilda .
Julio Irigoyen ( born 1 July 1894 - 29 August 1967 Buenos Aires ) was an Argentine film director .
Robert Orlando Morgan ( 1865 -- 16 May 1956 ) was an English music teacher , composer and musicologist .
Eliyahu Hacarmeli ( Hebrew : אליהו הכרמלי‎ , born Eliyahu Lulu ; 1 August 1891 -- 21 December 1952 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset from 1949 until 1952 .
Karl Heinrich Ulrichs ( 28 August 1825 -- 14 July 1895 ) was a German writer who is seen today as the pioneer of the modern gay rights movement .
Johann Gottfried Koehler ( 15 December 1745 -- 19 September 1801 ) was a German astronomer who discovered a number of nebulae , star clusters , and galaxies .
Euan Dickson DSC and bar , DFC ( 31 March 1892 -- 10 March 1980 ) was a British born New Zealander bomber pilot in the First World War .
Lawrence Anthony ( 17 September 1950 -- 2 March 2012 ) was an international conservationist , environmentalist , explorer and bestselling author .
Annibale Brugnoli ( 22 February 1843 -- 11 December 1915 ) was an Italian painter , mainly of genre and historical pieces , in oil and fresco .
The Rev. Edward Marsden ( 1869 - 1932 ) was a Canadian - American missionary and member of the Tsimshian nation who became the first Alaska Native to be ordained in the ministry .
Patrocinio Gamboa ( 30 April 1865 -- 24 November 1953 ) was a Filipino revolutionary notable for her participation in the Philippine Revolution .
Sabata Jonguhlanga Dalindyebo ( 1928 - -1986 ) was the ruler of the Thembu people of South Africa .
Ramachandra Mohapatra ( 1 January 1905 -- 5 May 1975 ) was born on 1 January 1905 in a village called Sailo Jharapada , 35 kilometres from Cuttack , Odisha and was a freedom fighter .
Larbi Benbarek or Larbi Ben Mbarek ( Arabic : لعربي بن مبارك‎ -- also known as the Black Pearl ; born 16 June 1914 -- died 16 September 1992 ) was a Moroccan football player recognized as the first successful African player in Europe .
Emelia Christine Schaub ( 1891 - 1995 ) was a lawyer who was Michigan 's first elected woman prosecutor , the first woman in the United States to successfully defend a murder trial .
Carlo Campanini ( 5 October 1906 -- 20 November 1984 ) , was an Italian actor , singer and comedian .
Lyle Shelton ( 1934 - -2010 ) was an American aviator who set the world 's absolute propeller - driven 3-kilometer speed record of 528.329 mph .
Anthoni van Noordt ( ca . 1619 -- 23 March 1675 ) was a Dutch composer and organist .
Jack Finck ( 21 January 1930 -- 31 October 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the early 1950s .
Jan Pouwer ( 21 September 1924 , Dordrecht -- 21 April 2010 , Zwolle ) was a Dutch anthropologist with a thorough grounding in his profession in terms of fieldwork and theory .
Pery Ribeiro ( 27 October 1937 -- 24 February 2012 ) was a Brazilian singer of bossa nova , MPB and jazz , active as a singer from 1959 until shortly before his death .
Mary Knowles ( 1733 - -1807 ) , née Morris , was an English Quaker poet and abolitionist .
Richard Stock ( 1569 -- 1626 ) was an English clergyman and one of the Puritan founders of the Feoffees for Impropriations .
Clemens August of Bavaria ( German : Clemens August von Bayern ) ( 17 August 1700 -- 6 February 1761 ) was a member of the Wittelsbach dynasty of Bavaria and Archbishop - Elector of Cologne .
Mephan Ferguson ( 25 July 1843 -- 2 November 1919 ) was an Australian manufacturer , particularly of water supply pipes , notably for the pipleline to the Western Australian goldfields .
Giovanni Angelo Montorsoli ( 1507 -- 31 August 1563 ) , also known as Giovanni Agnolo Montorsoli , was a Florentine sculptor and Servite friar .
Emanuel Litvinoff ( 5 May 1915 -- 24 September 2011 ) was a British writer and well - known figure in Anglo - Jewish literature , known for novels , short stories , poetry , plays and human rights campaigning .
Kosmas Balanos ( Greek : Κοσμάς Μπαλάνος ) ( 1731 - -1808 ) was a Greek mathematician , author and school director .
Menelaus of Alexandria ( /ˌmɛnɪˈleɪəs/ ; Greek : Μενέλαος , Menelaos ; c. 70 -- 140 CE ) was a Greek mathematician and astronomer , the first to recognize geodesics on a curved surface as natural analogs of straight lines .
Ann Quin ( born 17 March 1936 in Brighton , Sussex -- ? August 1973 ) was a British writer noted for her experimental style .
Richard Óge Martyn ( c. 1602 -- 1648 ) was a Galway lawyer and member of the Catholic Confederates of Ireland .
Ferdinando Baldi ( 19 May 1927 -- 12 November 2007 ) was an Italian film director , film producer and screenwriter .
Robert Crichton , 6th Lord Crichton of Sanquhar , ( died 1561 ) was the son of William Crichton , 5th Lord Crichton of Sanquhar and Elizabeth Fleming , daughter of Malcolm Fleming , 3rd Lord Fleming .
Abdülaziz of the Ottoman Empire or Abdülaziz I ( Ottoman Turkish : عبد العزيز / ` Abdü’l-`Azīz , Turkish : I. Abdülaziz ; 9 February 1830 -- 4 June 1876 ) was the 32nd Sultan of the Ottoman Empire and reigned between 25 June 1861 and 30 May 1876 .
Alberto Giacometti ( Italian pronunciation : ( alˈbɛrto dʒakoˈmetti ) ; 10 October 1901 -- 11 January 1966 ) was a Swiss sculptor , painter , draughtsman and printmaker .
Sophie of Saxe - Lauenburg ( born : before 1444 ; died : 9 September 1473 ) was a Duchess of Saxe - Lauenburg by birth and by marriage Duchess of Jülich - Berg .
Ahmet Haşim ( also written as Ahmed Hâşim ; احمد هاشم ; 1884 ? -- 4 June 1933 ) was an influential Turkish poet of the early 20th century .
Euphrosina Heldina von Dieffenau , or Heldin ( died 1636 ) , was a Swedish courtier .
Kyaw Zaw ( Burmese : ‌ကျော်ဇော , ( tɕɔ̀ zɔ́ ) ; 3 December 1919 -- 10 October 2012 ) was one of the founders of the Tatmadaw ( the modern Burmese Army ) and a member of the legendary `` Thirty Comrades '' who trained in Japan in the struggle for independence from Britain .
Bernard Charles Cotton ( 1905 -- 3 May 1966 ) was an Australian malacologist and museum curator of British origin .
Bernard Bennett ( 31 August 1931 -- 12 January 2002 ) was an English professional player of snooker and English billiards , whose career spanned twenty - six years between 1969 and 1995 .
Gottfried Lengnich ( Polish : Gotfryd Lengnich ) ( 4 December 1689 -- 28 April 1774 ) was an 18th - century historian , lawyer and politician .
Mark Schwed ( 1956 -- 31 January 2008 ) was an American television critic and journalist .
Leslie Rubinstein ( Pueblo , CO , June 21 , 1939 -- Glenview , IL , September 22 , 2007 ) was an American music critic and journalist .
Jeremiah Langhorne ( died 1742 ) was a prominent landowner and jurist in colonial Pennsylvania .
Ernst Lerch ( 19 November 1914 -- 1997 ) was one of the most important men of Operation Reinhard ( German : Aktion Reinhard ) , responsible for `` Jewish affairs '' and the mass murder of the Jews in the General Government ( Generalgouvernement ) .
Yves Nicolazic ( 1591 - -1645 ) was the Breton peasant who said he saw Saint Anne , the mother of the Virgin Mary , having unearthed a previously forgotten statue of Saint Anne in his field .
Sir Samuel Eyre ( 1633 -- 12 September 1698 ) , was an English judge .
Rev. Albert Edward Smith ( October 20 , 1871 - -1947 ) was a Canadian religious leader and politician .
Charles Aimé Halpin was the archbishop of the Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Regina , Saskatchewan , Canada from 12 December 1973 until his death 16 April 1994 .
Walter Edward Kittel , often known as Walter Edwards , ( 1880 - -1922 ) was an early pioneer in American aviation in the Pacific Northwest .
John L. LeFlore ( 1903 - -1976 ) was a civil rights leader and politician in Mobile , Alabama .
Jan I of Opole ( Polish : Jan I Opolski ) ( 1410/1413 -- 5 September 1439 ) was a Duke of Opole since 1437 ( with his brother as co - ruler ) .
William Willsher ( 12 October 1814 ( baptised ) -- 30 November 1861 ) was an English cricketer who played for Kent .
Juris Podnieks drowned on 23 June 1992 while scuba - diving in a lake in Courland .
Roger Leyburn ( died 1508 ) was an English churchman and academic , Master of Pembroke Hall , Cambridge , archdeacon of Durham and bishop of Carlisle .
Peter Mundy ( fl . 1600 -- 1667 ) was a seventeenth - century British merchant trader , traveller and writer .
Edward William Terrick Hamilton ( 26 November 1809 -- 28 September 1898 ) was a British businessman and politician who spent fifteen years as a pastoralist in New South Wales .
René Mugica ( 8 August 1909 -- 3 May 1998 ) was an Argentine actor , film director and screenwriter .
Galindo Mellado Cruz ( 18 April 1973 -- 9 May 2014 ) , commonly referred to by his alias El Mellado and/or Z-9 , was a Mexican drug lord and one of the founders of Los Zetas , a criminal organization originally formed by ex - commandos from the Mexican Armed Forces .
Major - General Sir William Bellairs KCMG CB , ( 28 August 1823 -- 24 July 1913 ) was a British army officer .
George Langton Hodgkinson ( Kentish Town , 13 February 1837 -- 16 February 1915 , Wotton - under - Edge , Gloucestershire ) was an Anglican clergyman .
Longchen Rabjampa , Drimé Özer ( Wylie : klong chen rab ' byams pa dri med ' od zer ) , commonly abbreviated to Longchenpa ( 1308 - -1364 ) , was a major teacher in the Nyingma school of Tibetan Buddhism .
Dubh Essa Níc Eidhin , Queen of Moylurg , died 1187 .
Mohan Dharia ( 14 February 1925 - 14 October 2013 ) was a former Union minister , a lawyer and social worker .
Father Morton A. Hill , S.J. ( 1917 - 1985 ) was a leader of the campaign against pornography in the 1960s , 1970s and 1980s .
Nicholas Orontony ( c. 1695 - -1750 ) was an 18th - century Wyandot leader who , in the years before the French and Indian War , tried to escape the domination of New France over Native people in the Detroit region by resettling in the Ohio country and forming an anti - French tribal coalition .
Jean - Gilles Delcour ( 1632 - -1695 ) , is a walloon painter of religious subjects , was born at Hamoir , near Liège .
Kara Mahmud Pasha ( Turkish : Kara Mahmud Paşa , fl . 1749 - -22 September 1796 ) was a hereditary Ottoman governor ( mutasarrıf ) of the Sanjak of Scutari ( known in historiography as Pashalik of Scutari ) , belonging to the Ottoman Albanian Bushati family ( Buşatlı ) .
Martin Rasmussen Hjelmen ( 24 January 1904 -- 30 May 1944 ) was a Norwegian sailor and communist activist .
Stevan Dohanos ( May 18 , 1907 , Lorain , Ohio -- 1994 ) was an artist and illustrator of the social realism school , best known for his Saturday Evening Post covers , and responsible for several of the Do n't Talk set of World War II propaganda posters .
Paul René Gauguin ( 27 February 1911 -- 14 February 1976 ) was a Norwegian painter , graphical artist , sculptor , book illustrator and scenographer .
Dan Jacobo Beninson ( 1931 - -2003 ) was an Argentine radiation expert who worked for the Argentine Atomic Energy Commission ( CNEA ) since 1955 holding different posts .
John Caius MD ( born John Kays ) ( /ˈkiːz/ ; 6 October 1510 -- 29 July 1573 ) , also known as Johannes Caius and Ioannes Caius , was an English physician , and second founder of the present Gonville and Caius College , Cambridge .
Sir Wylie McKissock , OBE ( 27 October 1906 -- 3 May 1994 ) was a British neurosurgeon .
Jagdish Swaminathan commonly known as J. Swaminathan ( June 21 , 1928 -- 1994 ) was a leading Indian artist , painter , poet and writer .
George Robert Johnston ( 1954 -- 2004 ) , better known as the Ballarat Bandit or as John Doe # 39 - 04 , was a Canadian - born burglar who gained nationwide attention as he spent the last several years of his life hiding from police in Death Valley National Park .
Flavius Julius Crispus ( died 326 ) , also known as Flavius Claudius Crispus and Flavius Valerius Crispus , was a Caesar of the Roman Empire .
August Christian Baumann ( 25 May 1770 -- 3 November 1831 ) was a Norwegian mine superintendent and politician .
Konstantinos Damianos ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Δαμιανός , 1853 - -1915 ) was a senior Greek Army officer who fought in the Balkan Wars of 1912 - -1913 .
Viliame ( William ) Vuetasau ( c.1820 - 1857 ) was the son of Roko Malani , the seventh Roko Sau of Lau and second Tui Nayau and Ciri of Taqalevu .
Harold Pender ( 1879 - -1959 ) was an American academic , author , and inventor .
Simon Luttichuys ( 1610 - -1661 ) was a Dutch Golden Age still life painter .
Francis Ludlow Holt ( 1780 -- 29 September 1844 ) was a legal and dramatic author .
Leopold Anton Kirchner ( ? - 29 December 1879 Kaplice , Bohemia ) , sometimes Kirschnerm , was an Austrian physician and entomologist .
Rogelio Sinán ( born on Taboga Island in 1902 ; died in 1994 ) was the pseudonym of Panamanian writer Bernardo Domínguez Alba .
Gilbert LaBine , OC ( 10 February 1890 -- 8 June 1977 ) was a Canadian prospector who , in 1930 , discovered radium and uranium deposits at Port Radium , Northwest Territories .
Richard Gurney ( 1790 - -1843 ) was vice - warden of the stannaries of Devon .
Augustus Bernard Tancred ( 20 August 1865 -- 23 November 1911 ) was a leading 19th century South African Test cricketer .
Haji Mohamed Sanusi Mahmood ( 8 October 1909 -- 8 October 1995 ) was the first Mufti of Singapore .
Ragnar Hasselgren ( June 3 , 1904 - September 28 , 1982 ) was a Swedish - born singer and recording artist , who was active on the American West Coast during the 1940s and 1950s .
W. D. Cocker ( 1882 , Rutherglen -- 1970 ) was a Scottish poet who wrote in both Scots and English .
Christopher Grene ( 1629 - -1697 ) , was a Jesuit priest .
Jacques Dumas ( 7 November 1908 -- 21 July 1994 ) , better known as Marijac , was a French comics writer , artist and editor .
Sun Wanrong ( 孫萬榮 ) ( died 697 ) was a khan of the Khitan people who , along with his brother - in - law Li Jinzhong , rose against Chinese hegemony in 696 , with Li Jinzhong as khan , and they further invaded Chinese territory then under the rule of Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty .
William Hoogland ( ca.1794 - 1832 ) was an engraver in Boston , Massachusetts , and New York in the early 19th - century .
Graham Whettam ( 7 September 1927 -- 17 August 2007 ) was an English post - romantic composer .
Dorothy Napangardi ( born early 1950s -- 1 June 2013 ) was a Warlpiri speaking contemporary Indigenous Australian artist born in the Tanami Desert and who worked in Alice Springs .
Colin Tapley ( 7 May 1907 -- 1 December 1995 ) was an actor in both American and British films .
Jacobus Boonen ( 11 October 1573 -- 30 June 1655 ) was the sixth Bishop of Ghent ( 1617 - -1620 ) and the fourth Archbishop of Mechelen ( 1621 - -1655 ) .
Surendranath Dasgupta ( Bengali : সুরেন্দ্রনাথ দাশগুপ্ত ) ( October 1887 -- 18 December 1952 ) was a scholar of Sanskrit and philosophy .
William Henry Stanley Monck ( April 21 , 1839 - -June 24 , 1915 ) was an Irish astronomer and philosopher .
Peter Ewart ( 14 May 1767 -- 15 September 1842 ) was a British engineer who was influential in developing the technologies of turbines and theories of thermodynamics .
Dr. Horse was the stage name of Al Pittman ( 17 September 1917 -- 28 April 2004 ) , an American rhythm and blues vocalist and entertainer who performed between the 1930s and 1960s .
Anthony Hyman ( 1946 - -1999 ) was a noted British academic , writer and Islamicist .
Ann J. Lane ( 1931 - -2013 ) was an American educator , historian , and author that was considered to be a pioneer in the fields of women 's history and women 's studies .
Patrick Hume , 1st Earl of Marchmont ( 13 January 1641 -- 2 August 1724 ) , known as Sir Patrick Hume , 1st Baronet from 1648 to 1690 and as Lord Polwarth from 1690 to 1697 , was a Scottish statesman .
Dennis List ( 1946 - 9 November 2007 ) was a New Zealand poet , editor and novelist .
Willem Jacobsz Delff ( c. October 1580 -- 14 April 1638 ) was a Dutch Golden Age engraver and painter .
Wang Yuankui ( 王元逵 ) ( 812 - -854 ) , formally Duke Zhong of Taiyuan ( 太原忠公 ) , was a general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty .
Iosif Trifa ( 3 March 1888 - 12 February 1938 ) was a Romanian Orthodox priest and evangelist .
Albert Fearnley ( 10 March 1924 -- 4 May 1999 ) was an English rugby league footballer and coach who played as a second - row .
Peter Westerstrøm ( 1779 - -1809 ) was a Swedish mass murderer who gained notoriety for the Saksebøl Slaughter in Moss , Norway during the Napoleonic wars .
Josip Marohnić ( November 12 , 1866 - -January 23 , 1921 ) remains up to this day the most influential Croatian emigrant in the Americas .
Al al - Din ( Chinese : 阿老瓦丁 ; pinyin : Ālăowădīng ; Wade -- Giles : A - lao - wa - ting , the name presumably representing Ala - ud - din , d. 1312 ) was a Muslim Persian mangonel expert who served in Kublai Khan 's army in the conquest of the Southern Song Dynasty .
Samuel Angus ( 27 August 1881 -- 17 November 1943 ) was professor of New Testament and Church History at St Andrew 's College in the University of Sydney from 1915 to 1943 .
Alfonso López Trujillo ( 8 November 1935 -- 19 April 2008 ) was a Colombian Cardinal Bishop of the Roman Catholic Church and president of the Pontifical Council for the Family .
Duncan McFarlan ( died 7 September 1816 ) was a United States Democratic - Republican U.S. Congressman from North Carolina between 1805 and 1807 .
Étienne Provost ( 1785 -- 3 July 1850 ) was a French Canadian fur trader whose trapping and trading activities in the American southwest preceded Mexican independence .
Stanisław Paklepka , Latin Paclesius ( d. Lublin 1565 ) was one of the first generation of Polish Calvinists , then later an Arian .
Andrew Findlater ( 1810 - 1 January 1885 ) was a Scottish editor notable for his work on Chambers 's Encyclopaedia .
Yehoshua Zettler ( July 15 , 1917 -- May 20 , 2009 ; last name also spelled as Zeitler ) was an Israeli who served as the Jerusalem commander of Jewish paramilitary group Lehi , often also called as the Stern gang .
Nguyễn Thị Bích(阮氏碧 ) , also known as Nguyễn Nhược Thị Bích ( 阮若氏碧 , An Phuớc District , Ninh Thuận , 1830 - -1909 ) was a Vietnamese poet .
Yadollah Sahabi ( 25 February 1905 -- 12 April 2002 ) was a prominent Iranian scholar , writer , reformist and politician .
Wu Kung - tsao or Wu Gongzao ( 1902 - -1983 ) was a famous Chinese teacher of t'ai chi ch'uan .
Leo Dobrigh ( 6 December 1898 -- 17 April 1973 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and Richmond in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Carl - Erik Quensel ( 1907 - -1977 ) was a Swedish statistician and demographer , specializing in population statistics , statistical distribution theory and biostatistics .
Bekir Sıtkı Bircan ( 1886 -- 26 June 1967 ) was a Turkish footballer , a high school teacher and 5th of the founder of Galatasaray SK .
Admiral Sir Henry Ruthven Moore GCB , CVO , DSO ( 29 August 1886 -- 12 March 1978 ) was the last British admiral to command Home Fleet during World War II . He served in that post from 1944 to 1945 .
Bob Kelsey ( 27 September 1925 -- 19 April 1990 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Beach Lawrence ( 23 October 1800 -- 26 March 1881 ) was an American politician and jurist who served as lieutenant governor of Rhode Island from 1851 to 1852 under Governor Philip Allen .
Leopold Z. Goldstein ( 1899 - 1963 ) , an American physician and endocrinologist , was born in Camden , New Jersey , graduated from Camden High School and the University of Pennsylvania Medical School in 1922 .
Nicholas Kratzer ( 1487 ? -- 1550 ) was a German mathematician , astronomer , and horologist .
Count Bertalan Széchényi de Sárvár - Felsővidék ( 24 October 1866 -- 3 June 1943 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Speaker of the House of Magnates from 1 May 1935 until his death .
Augustus Voelcker F.R.S. ( 24 September 1822 -- 5 December 1884 ) , full name John Christopher Augustus Voelcker , was a Royal Agricultural Society of England chemist .
Louis Harold Gray ( 10 November 1905 -- 9 July 1965 ) was an English physicist who worked mainly on the effects of radiation on biological systems , inventing the field of radiobiology as he went .
William Bedloe ( 20 April 1650 -- 20 August 1680 ) was an English fraudster and Popish Plot informer .
Following Todar Mal 's death on 8 November 1589 in Lahore , his body was cremated according to the Hindu traditions .
Raffaello de Banfield ( 2 June 1922 -- 7 January 2008 ) , correctly Raphael Douglas , Baron von Banfield Tripcovich , was a British - born composer .
John Maurice Shaftesley OBE ( 1901 - -1981 ) was an English journalist and writer , and editor of the Jewish Chronicle from 1946 to 1958 .
William Powditch ( 8 February 1795 -- 22 August 1872 ) was a very early settler in New Zealand 's Bay of Islands and a politician in Auckland .
Hendrick Christiaensen ( died 1616 ) was a Dutch explorer who was involved in the earlier exploration of what became the colony of New Netherland .
Bermudo Pérez de Traba ( died 1168 ) , the eldest son of Count Pedro Fróilaz de Traba and his first wife Urraca Fróilaz , was a member of the most important medieval lineage in Galicia .
Edwin Ruud ( 9 June 1854 -- 9 December 1932 ) was a Norwegian mechanical engineer and inventor who immigrated to the United States where he designed , sold , and popularized the tankless - water heater .
Fred Herd ( 26 November 1873 -- 14 March 1954 ) was a Scottish professional golfer from St Andrews .
Arthur Hill Hassall ( 13 December 1817 , Teddington -- 9 April 1894 , San Remo ) was a British physician , chemist and microscopist who is primarily known for his work in public health and food safety .
Isaac H. Brown ( 1812 - 1880 ) was the sexton at Grace Episcopal Church in Greenwich Village , and arbiter of style in Manhattan where he planned weddings , arranged soirées and funerals for the wealthy of New York City .
Edwin E. Kintner ( 1920 - -2010 ) was an American nuclear pioneer and engineer and a U.S. Navy captain who was in charge of de - contamination of the Three Mile Island accident .
George Synnot ( 1819 - 1871 ) was one of Victoria 's pioneer settlers arriving in the Port Phillip District about 1837 and rising to become a prominent land owner and Geelong businessman .
Angus Holden , 1st Baron Holden ( 16 March 1833 -- 25 March 1912 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician who was active in local government and sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1885 and 1900 .
Laura Mancini ( 6 May 1636 -- 8 February 1657 ) was a niece of Cardinal Mazarin .
Arnold of Altena , count of Altena , count of Isenberg and Hövel , Vogt of Werden ( 1166 - -1209 ) was son of Eberhard IV of Berg .
Reuben Farley ( 17 January 1826 in West Bromwich -- 1899 ) , was the eighth of ten children of the mining engineer Thomas Farley ( 1781 - -1830 ) .
Tom Palumbo ( 1921 -- 2008 ) was an American photographer and theatre director .
Jonathan Nash Hearder ( 24 December 1809 -- 16 July 1876 ) was a British electrical engineer , inventor , and educator .
Benjamin Mildmay , 1st Earl FitzWalter PC ( 27 December 1672 -- 29 February 1756 ) , styled The Honourable Benjamin Mildmay until 1728 and known as The Lord FitzWalter between 1728 and 1730 , was a British politician .
Aleks Buda ( 1910 - -1993 ) was an Albanian historian of Jewish origin .
Samuel Jones - Loyd , 1st Baron Overstone ( 25 September 1796 -- 17 November 1883 ) was a British banker and politician .
William Ott died on 4 January 1951 , aged 78 years .
Kim Malthe - Bruun ( 8 July 1923 -- 6 April 1945 ) was a Canadian - born seaman and a member of the Danish resistance executed by the German occupying power .
Jan Svatopluk Presl ( 4 September 1791 -- 6 April 1849 ) was a Bohemian natural scientist .
Sir Dinshaw Maneckji Petit , 1st Baronet ( 30 June 1823 -- 5 May 1901 ) , Parsi entrepreneur and founder of the first textile mills in India .
William Cibotti was a member of Philadelphia City Council representing the 2nd District from 1968 to 1975 .
Emil Fey ( 23 March 1886 -- 16 March 1938 ) was an officer in the Austro - Hungarian Army , leader of the right - wing paramilitary Heimwehr forces and politician of the First Austrian Republic .
Arsenije IV Jovanović Šakabenta ( Serbian Cyrillic : Арсеније IV Јовановић Шакабента , Serbian pronunciation : ( ǎrseːnije t͡ʃětʋr̩ːtiː ) ; 1698 -- 18 January 1748 ) was the Patriarch of Serbs from 1725 to 1737 and Metropolitan of Karlovci from 1737 to his death in 1748 .
Gadhra Mór mac Dundach ( died 1027 ) was King of Síol Anmchadha and Uí Maine .
Ignazio Cirri or Giacomo Matteo Ignazio Cirri ( 20 September 1711 -- 13 July 1787 ) was an Italian organist and composer in the 18th century .
Al - Mundhir III ibn al - Nu'man ( Arabic : المنذر بن النعمان‎ ) , also known as Al - Mundhir ibn Imri ' al - Qays ( المنذر بن إمرئ القيس ) ( died 554 ) was the king of the Lakhmids in 503/505 - -554 .
George T. Pierce ( ca . 1823 Pawling , Dutchess County , New York -- 1874 ) was an American lawyer and politician from New York .
Nathalan ( or Nachlan ) , ( died 678 ) is a saint in the Roman Catholic Church , who was active in the district now known as Aberdeenshire , Scotland .
Robert Devereux , 16th Viscount Hereford ( 3 January 1843 -- 27 March 1930 ) was an English Peer .
Victor McMahon ( 1903 -- 9 March 1992 ) was an Australian flute teacher and flautist .
Aert Mijtens ( c.1541 - -1602 ) was a Flemish Renaissance painter .
`` Gunner '' Laurence Joseph Browne or alternatively `` Lawrence Joseph Brown '' ( 3 October 1896 -- 31 May 1916 ) was an Irish gunner for the British Navy between 1914 and 1916 .
Birgitte Gøye ( 1511 - 26 July 1574 ) was a Danish county administrator , lady in waiting , landholder and noble , co - founder and principal of Herlufsholm School .
Ardashir I or Ardeshir I ( Middle Persian : , New Persian : اردشیر ) , also known as Ardashir the Unifier ( 180 - -242 AD ) , was the founder of the Sasanian Empire .
Nadine Blacklock ( 1953 - -1998 ) was a nature photographer best known for her detailed nature photography of the Lake Superior area .
Hendrick Munniks , Munnicks , or Munnekus ( c1600 -- 1664 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Robert C. Barnfield ( 1856 - -1893 ) was an English painter who was born in Gloucester .
Hari Om Sharan ( 26 September 1932 -- 17 December 2007 ) was a Hindu devotional singer and lyricist .
Broder Lysholm Krohg ( 19 August 1777 -- 16 October 1861 ) was a Norwegian military officer and civil servant .
Frances Ulric Cole ( 9 September 1905 -- 21 May 1992 ) was an American pianist , editor , music educator and composer .
John Hughes Morris ( 1870 - -1953 ) was born in Penrhosllugwy , Anglesey but moved to Liverpool as a young lad .
Taufiq Wahby ( 1891 - 1984 ) was a prominent Kurdish writer , linguist and politician .
Jan Kašpar ( 20 May 1883 -- 2 March 1927 ) was a Czech aviator , aircraft constructor , designer and engineer .
Sir Henry Coward ( 26 November 1849 -- 10 June 1944 ) was a British conductor .
Sir William Job Collins KCVO ( 9 May 1859 -- 11 December 1946 ) was a surgeon and later a Liberal politician and legislator .
Arathoon Stephen ( 1861 -- 14 May 1927 ) was an Indian hotelier and real estate developer of Armenian descent .
Leopold Teller ( April 3 , 1844 , Budapest - 1908 ) was a Hungarian actor .
Gin Chow ( 1857 - June 1933 ) was a Chinese immigrant who gained fame in California as a prophet and fortune teller able to predict the weather and other natural events .
John Pierre Burr ( abt 1792 -- 4 April 1864 ) was an American abolitionist and community leader in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania , active in education and civil rights for African Americans .
Isaac Duncan MacDougall ( 10 July 1897 -- 4 April 1969 ) was a National Government , Conservative and Progressive party member of the Canadian House of Commons .
Princess Konstancja Lubomirska ( ca . 1618 - -1646 ) was a Polish noble lady .
Late Pt . Vinayakbuva Utturkar ( 1914 - 1989 ) was a Hindustani Classical Music Vocal performer .
John Fitzmaurice ( 18 November 1947 in Copenhagen - August 2003 in Brussels ) , was an administrator , academic and writer .
Alan Neville Gent ( 11 November 1927 -- 20 September 2012 ) was an English scientist who contributed to understanding adhesion physics , and fracture of rubbery , crystalline and glassy polymers .
Emery Hawkins ( April 30 , 1912 -- June 1989 ) was an American animator who worked at various studios such as Disney , Screen Gems , Walter Lantz , Warner Bros. , and UPA during the golden age of animation .
Jetsun Dechen Wangmo ( died 2011 ) was a Tibetan Buddhist .
Sir Charles Theodore Hagberg Wright , LL.D. ( 17 November 1862 , Middleton Tyas , Yorkshire -- 7 March 1940 in London ) was the Secretary and Librarian of the London Library from 1893 until his death .
Sir Brian Corby ( 10 May 1929 - 23 April 2014 ) was a British businessman who held a variety of positions on the boards of important industrial , artistic and education organisations .
Freddie Anderson ( 11 September 1922 -- 10 December 2001 ) was an Irish writer , playwright , author , poet and socialist , born in Ballybay , County Monaghan , Ireland , who became an influential figure in left wing culture and folk music scene in Glasgow from the 1950s until his death in 2001 .
Sir ( Herbert ) Hamilton Harty ( 4 December 1879 -- 19 February 1941 ) was an Irish composer , conductor , pianist and organist .
Pierre Willems ( born Maastricht , 6 January 1840 ; died Leuven , 23 February 1898 ) was a Dutch philologist and historian of Ancient Rome .
Frei Manuel Correia ( or Correa ) ( ca . 1600 -- 1653 ) was a Portuguese Baroque composer .
James Butler , 9th Earl of Ormond and 2nd Earl of Ossory ( 1496 -- 28 October 1546 ) , known as The Lame , was the son of Piers Butler , 8th Earl of Ormond and Margaret Fitzgerald , Countess of Ormond .
Alf Hearnden ( 19 January 1874 -- 23 October 1951 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rao Surtan Singh ( राओ सुरतन सिंह ) was the 12th Rao of Bundi ( बूंदी ) , ruling from 1531 to 1544 .
Pierrequin de Thérache also Pierre or Petrus de Therache ( c.1470 - 1528 ) was a French renaissance composer from Nancy .
Marie Hamsun ( born Marie Andersen ) ( 19 November 1881 - 4 August 1969 ) was a Norwegian actress and writer .
Percy Bolt ( 1885 - -1953 ) was an Australian pioneer rugby league player from the 1910s .
Felicity Lane - Fox , Baroness Lane - Fox , OBE ( 22 June 1918 -- 17 April 1988 ) was a Conservative member of the House of Lords and champion of disability issues .
Hugo Schmeisser ( 24 September 1884 -- 12 September 1953 ) was a German developer of infantry weapons in the 20th century .
Lady Isabella de Beauchamp , Lady Kidwelly , Baroness Despenser ( born c. 1263 - died before 30 May 1306 ) , was an English noblewoman and wealthy heiress .
Charles Lee Smith ( 1887 -- 1964 in San Diego , California ) was an atheist , a free - thought activist , a white supremacist and anti - Semite in the United States .
Louis Bignon ( 26 June 1816 -- 18 May 1906 ) was a famous French chef whose Café Riche became the most fashionable in Paris .
Ferdinand Jung ( 24 January 1905 -- 2 December 1973 ) was a German Communist activist who resisted the Nazi government in the 1930s and spent a good deal of time in prisons and concentration camps .
Leicester Gataker ( 1874 - 1942 ) was an English professional water diviner , or water finder .
Gerald Westbury ( 29 July 1927 -- 12 June 2014 ) , OBE , usually known as Charley Westbury , was an English surgeon who pioneered treatments for cancer , particularly sarcoma , developing techniques for preserving muscle function after surgery .
Collins Chabane ( 15 April 1960 -- 15 March 2015 ) was a South African Minister of Public Service and Administration .
Pundit Sahadeo Tiwari died on 14 April 1972 .
Dipa Ma ( March 25 , 1911 - September 1989 ) was a Bangladeshi meditation teacher of Theravada Buddhism , a student of Anagarika Munindra .
Dora Söderberg ( 10 November 1899 -- 9 November 1990 ) was a Swedish stage actress .
Peter Sørensen Vig ( 7 November 1854 -- 21 March 1929 ) , commonly known as P. S. Vig , was a Danish American pastor , educator , and historian in the Lutheran church .
Clive Uptton ( 12 March 1911 -- 11 February 2006 ) was a widely regarded British illustrator and painter of landscapes and portraits .
Flora Bramley ( 1909 -- 23 June 1993 ) was an English actress and comedian .
George Auldjo Jamieson FRSE ( 1 May 1828 - 18 July 1900 ) was a Scottish businessman , chartered accountant and local councillor .
François Baillairgé ( 21 January 1759 -- 15 September 1830 ) was an architect who also pursued painting and wood sculpture .
Tammy Hynes ( 11 August 1897 -- 9 September 1969 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
William Sullivan Barnes , ( 16 June 1841 -- 2 April 1912 ) , was born in Boston and became a Unitarian minister .
Maj - Gen . Ladislaus Herbert Richard Pope - Hennessy ( 1875 - 1 March 1942 ) , was a British Liberal Party politician and soldier of Irish Catholic descent .
Edward Timothy Hooley ( 1842 -- 3 August 1903 ) , usually known as E. T. Hooley or Tim Hooley , was an explorer in Western Australia , who in 1866 pioneered an overland stock route from Geraldton to the Ashburton River .
Isabella Bendidio ( Marchesa Bentivoglio ) ( 13 September 1546 -- after 1610 ) was a Ferrarese noblewoman who , along with her sister Lucrezia Bendidio , sang in the first incarnation of the concerto delle donne as part of the court 's musica secreta .
Yan Xishan ( or Yen Hsi - shan , IPA : ( i̯ɛ́n ɕíʂɛ̄n ) ; 8 October 1883 -- 22 July 1960 ) was a Chinese warlord who served in the government of the Republic of China .
Patriarch Athanasius II Dabbas ( died 1619 ) , sometime known also as Athanasius III , was Melkite Greek Patriarch of Antioch from 1611 to 1619 .
William Pitt Cobbett ( 26 July 1853 in Adelaide , South Australia -- 17 October 1919 in Hobart , Tasmania ) was an Australian academic , jurist , and editor .
Alejandro Kuropatwa ( 1956 - -2003 ) was a famous Argentine photographer .
Raphael Kirchner ( 1876 - 2 August 1917 ) was an Austrian artist , principally a portrait painter and illustrator best known for Art Nouveau and early pin - up work , especially in picture postcard format .
Jens Edvard Kraft ( 22 December 1784 -- 21 July 1853 ) was a Norwegian civil servant , bibliographer , and a writer on topographical - statistical topics .
Colin Milne ( c.1743 - -1815 ) was a Scottish priest of the Church of England and botanist .
Major - General George Douglas , 1st Earl of Dumbarton KT ( 1635 -- 20 March 1692 ) was a Scottish nobleman , and soldier .
Thomas Paty ( c.1713 -- 4 May 1789 ) was a British surveyor , architect and mason working mainly in Bristol .
Friedrich Kipp ( 1814 -- 21 January 1869 ) was a German physician and entomologist .
Adolph Giesl - Gieslingen ( 7 September 1903 - 11 February 1992 ) was an Austrian locomotive designer and engineer .
John Meredith Bass ( 1804 - -1878 ) was an American banker , planter and Whig politician .
Erich Topp ( 2 July 1914 -- 26 December 2005 ) was the third most successful of German U - Boot Experten commanders of World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves and Swords ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit Eichenlaub und Schwertern ) .
Clayton Rawson ( 1906 - -1971 ) was an American mystery writer , editor , and amateur magician .
Hugh Montgomerie , 7th Earl of Eglinton ( 1613 - -1669 ) , was the son of Alexander Montgomerie , 6th Earl of Eglinton .
Sir William Blizard FRS FRSE PRCS FSA ( 1 March 1743 -- 27 August 1835 ) was an English surgeon .
Gasparo Alberti ( also : Gaspar de Albertis ; Gaspare Albertus ; Gaspar bergomensis ; Gaspar de padua ; c. 1485 -- c. 1560 ) was an Italian composer .
Ilo Mitkë Qafëzezi ( 1889 - -1964 ) was a prolific Albanian writer of historical and religious subjects .
Dyer Pearl ( 1857 - September 1930 ) was a prominent Wall Street businessman and a member of the New York Stock Exchange for twenty - six years .
Gene Klavan ( May 4 , 1924 -- April 8 , 2004 ) was an American disc - jockey ( DJ ) , columnist and author .
Sydney Mary Thompson ( also known as Madame Christen ) ( 1847 -- 16 July 1923 ) was an Irish geologist , botanist and artist .
Charles Frodsham ( 15 April 1810 London --1871 London ) was a renowned English watch and clockmaker .
Lê Chân Tông ( chữ Hán : 黎真宗 , 1630 - -1649 ) birth name Lê Duy Hựu ( 黎維祐 , 黎維禔 ) , was the seventh king of Vietnamese Lê Dynasty .
Jonathan Fiifii'i ( 1921 - October 1989 ) was a Kwaio at Ane'emae near Oloburi , Malaita , Solomon Islands .
John Komnenos Doukas ( Greek : Ιωάννης Κομνηνός Δούκας , Iōannēs Komnēnos Doukas ) , Latinized as Comnenus Ducas , was ruler of Thessalonica from 1237 until his death in 1244 .
Muhammad Habibur Rahman ( Bengali : মুহাম্মদ হাবিবুর রহমান‎ ; 3 December 1928 -- 11 January 2014 ) was a former chief justice of Bangladesh Supreme Court in 1995 .
Alexander Stanhope ( 1638 -- 20 September 1707 ) was an English envoy in Madrid between 1690 and 1699 .
Henry Flood ( 1732 -- 2 December 1791 ) , Irish statesman , son of Warden Flood , Lord Chief Justice of the King 's Bench for Ireland , was educated at Trinity College , Dublin , and afterwards at Christ Church , Oxford , where he became proficient in the classics .

Harry Liddell ( 1866 - -1931 ) was a British politician .
Sir Rhys Hopkin Morris ( 5 September 1888 -- 22 November 1956 ) was a Welsh Liberal politician who was a Member of Parliament from 1923 - -1932 and from 1945 - -1956 .
Michaela Denis ( 28 August 1914 - 4 May 2003 ) was a British - born wildlife documentary film - maker and presenter , working with her husband , Armand Denis .
Jacques Delécluse ( 15 September 1933 -- 29 October 2015 ) was a French percussionist and composer born in Béthune .
Lilla Brignone ( 23 August 1913 -- 24 March 1984 ) was an Italian film and theater actress .
Wabbicommicot ( died 1768 ) was a Mississauga chief instrumental in maintaining friendly relations between his Mississauga tribe and the British .
Richard Dadd ( 1 August 1817 -- 7 January 1886 ) was an English painter of the Victorian era , noted for his depictions of fairies and other supernatural subjects , Orientalist scenes , and enigmatic genre scenes , rendered with obsessively minuscule detail .
Major General Sir John Campbell , 2nd Baronet , of New Brunswick , Canada , ( 14 April 1807 -- 18 June 1855 ) , was a British army officer and the son of General Sir Archibald Campbell , 1st Baronet of New Brunswick , Canada .
Abraham Mignon or Minjon ( 21 June 1640 - 27 March 1679 ) , was a Dutch golden age painter , specialized in flower bouquets .
Ivan Ribar ( Croatian pronunciation : ( ǐvan rîbaːr ) ; 21 January 1881 - 2 February 1968 ) was a Yugoslav politician and soldier of Croatian descent .

Robert of Durazzo ( 1326 -- 19 September 1356 , Poitiers ) was the third son of John , Duke of Durazzo and Agnes de Périgord .
Louay Kayali ( Arabic : لؤي كيالي‎ ) , ( 1934 - -1978 ) was a Syrian modern artist .
Sir John Juyn SL ( died 24 March 1440 ) was a British judge .
Welcome Duru ( 1933 - -2009 ) was a South African actor , boxing promoter , composer , musician , politician and a socialite , also known as Bra Wel .
Mary Hayden Pike ( née Green ) ( 30 November 1824 -- 15 January 1908 ) American author born in Eastport , Maine to Elijah Dix Green and Hannah Caflin Hayden .
Hendrick Snyers ( born 1611 , Antwerp -- died 1644 , Antwerp ) , was a Flemish Baroque engraver .
Pavlo Teteria ( Ukrainian : Павло́ Тете́ря ; Russian : Па́вел Ива́нович Тете́ря , Polish : Paweł Morzkowski herbu Ślepowron ) ( 1620s--1670 ) was Hetman of Right - bank Ukraine ( 1663 - -1665 ) .
Moyses Chahon ( 1918 - -1981 ) was a Brazilian Army general and a distinguished veteran of World War II . He was born in Rio de Janeiro .
Arthur Hobhouse , 1st Baron Hobhouse KCSI , PC , QC ( 10 November 1819 -- 6 December 1904 ) , was an English lawyer and judge .
Edward Southwell , Jr. of King 's Weston , Gloucestershire ( 1/16 June 1705 -- 16 March 1755 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician .
Otto VI , Count of Tecklenburg ( died 1388 ) was the only son of Count Nicholas I and his wife , Helena of Oldenburg - Wildeshausen - Alt - Bruchhausen .
Oveco Núñez ( died 951 ) was the Bishop of León from 927 until his death .
Dick Tyldesley ( Richard Knowles Tyldesley born 11 March 1897 , Westhoughton , Lancashire , died 17 September 1943 , Bolton , Lancashire ) was a Lancashire cricketer who was one of the most important figures in Lancashire breaking Yorkshire 's stronghold on the County Championship between 1926 and 1930 .
Gilbert Dyer ( 1743 - -1820 ) was an English bookseller , known also as an antiquarian writer .
Nicolas Desportes ( 1718 - -1787 ) was a French painter , specialising in representations of animals and hunting scenes .
Antoine de Longueval ( fl . 1498 - -1525 ) was a French singer and composer of the Renaissance .
Edward Edmondson , Jr. ( 1830 - -1883 ) was an American artist , active for most of his career in Dayton , Ohio .
Gabriele Zerbi ( 1445 - -1505 ) was a Veronese professor at the Universities of Bologna and Padua .
Walford Bodie , whose real name was Samuel Murphy Bodie ( 1869 - -1939 ) , was a Scottish showman , hypnotist , ventriloquist and stage magician , famous for his ' mock ' electrocutions involving a replica of ' The Electric Chair ' .
Arthur Corbin Gould ( 1850 - -1903 ) was an avid shooter and member of the Massachusetts Rifle Association .
Philip Hershkovitz ( 12 October 1909 -- 15 February 1997 ) was an American mammalogist .
Air Marshal Boediardjo ( 16 November 1921 -- 15 March 1997 ) was Indonesian Minister of Information ( 1968 - 1973 ) for Indonesian First Development Cabinet ( Indonesian : Kabinet Pembangunan I ) .
Agnes Reston ( nee Harkness , 1771 -- 24 December 1856 ) was a Scottish wartime nurse during the Peninsular War .
D. P. Shettian ( 29 June 1932 -- 2 September 2006 ) was the second Bishop - in - Karnataka Southern Diocese of Church of South India headquartered in Mangalore where the Bishop 's Cathedra is placed at the CSI - Shanthi Cathedral , Balmatta , Mangalore .
Allen Boretz ( 1900 - -1985 ) , was an American songwriter , playwright and screenwriter .
Charles Eugene Lancelot Brown ( 17 June 1863 -- 2 May 1924 ) founded BBC Brown Boveri ( later ASEA Brown Boveri ) with Walter Boveri .
Medford Bryan Evans ( August 21 , 1907 -- February 4 , 1989 ) was a college professor , author , editor , and critic of liberalism in American politics , education , and society .
Dr. Abdul Jabbar Junejo ( 26 November 1935 -- 12 July 2011 ) was a prolific Sindhi writer , poet , novelist , story - writer , critic , linguist , historian and musicologist , born on 26 November 1935 at Pir Fateh Shah Village , District Badin , Sindh , Pakistan .
Elías Regules ( 1861 - -1929 ) was a Uruguayan physician , teacher , writer and politician .
Narayan Dutt Shrimali ( Paramhansa Nikhileshwaranand ascetically ) ( 21 April 1933 -- 3 July 1998 , Jodhpur ) was an academic and astrologer .
Anne Louise Gregory Ritter ( 1868 - 1929 ) was an American artist and art teacher .
Paul Zeeuwts ( b. Anderlecht 9 May 1948 , d. Brussels 17 March 2009 ) was President of the Flemish IWT from 1991 until his death in 2009 .
Peter Slaghuis ( 21 August 1961 -- 5 September 1991 ) was a Dutch DJ , producer and remixer , whose work was mostly released under the name Hithouse ( a literal translation of his last name -- slag , a hit , a beat ; and huis , house ) .
Jesse LaFollette ( 1781 NJ-1843 Ind ) is featured in one of the limestone panels at the Lincoln Boyhood National Memorial in Lincoln City , Indiana .
Fausto Cleva ( 17 May 1902 -- 6 August 1971 ) was an Italian - born American operatic conductor .
Humphrey of Montfort ( died 12 February 1284 ) was a nobleman of the Kingdom of Jerusalem .
Frank Bellamy ( 21 May 1917 -- 5 July 1976 ) was a British comics artist , best known for his work on the Eagle comic , for which he illustrated Heros the Spartan and Fraser of Africa .
John de Troye ( died 1371 ) was a Welsh - born Crown official and judge in fourteenth century Ireland , who held the offices of Chancellor of the Exchequer of Ireland and Lord Treasurer of Ireland .
Aurelio Bacciarini ( 8 November 1873 -- 27 June 1935 ) was a Swiss Roman Catholic who served as the interim administrator of the Diocese of Lugano .
John Colin McCormack ( 2 December 1941 -- 19 June 2004 ) was a Welsh actor who enjoyed success in classical stage performances and television shows including BBC TV 's Dixon of Dock Green , a show he returned to twenty years later when he played a police constable .
Ian Wooldridge , OBE ( 14 January 1932 -- 4 March 2007 ) was a British sports journalist .
Mike Marqusee ( pronounced mar - kuh - see ; 27 January 1953 -- 13 January 2015 ) was an American writer , journalist and political activist in London .
Billy Bowlegs III , Billy Fewell , aka Cofehapkee ( 1862 - -1965 ) , was a Seminole elder , also of African - American descent .
Dezső Dersfi or Dezső , son of Ders ( died 1075 ) was a Hungarian prelate and politician , who served as Archbishop of Esztergom from 1067 to 1075 .
Brian Dorman ( 2 July 1937 -- 27 July 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Bernt Theodor Anker ( 7 March 1867 -- 21 August 1943 ) was a Norwegian linguist , priest and author .
Jean - Pierre Hautier ( 18 October 1955 -- 12 October 2012 ) was a Belgian television presenter and broadcaster for RTBF .
Petrus Filipsson ( Latin : Petrus Philippi ) , also known as Peder Filipsson Röde , was Archbishop of Uppsala , Sweden , from 1332 to 1341 .
Aleksander Józef Lisowski HNG ( c. 1580 -- October 11 , 1616 ) was a Polish--
Alexander Boyd , 3rd Lord Boyd ( died after 1508 ) Scottish noble .
António Manoel de Vilhena ( 28 May 1663 -- 10 December 1736 ) was a Portuguese nobleman who was the 66th Prince and Grand Master of the Order of St. John of Jerusalem from 19 June 1722 to his death in 1736 .
Ronald Sims ( 1926 - -2007 ) was a distinguished ecclesiastical architect who redesigned many English church interiors .
George Ambrum ( 1943 - 1986 ) was an Australian rugby league player from the 1960s and 1970s .
Robert Cock ( 25 May 1801 -- 23 March 1871 ) was one of the first European explorers of the Adelaide region of South Australia following the establishment of the new colony in December 1836 .
Edward Findley ( 8 September 1864 -- 26 October 1947 ) was an Australian politician and publisher .
Stanley Portal Hyatt ( 2 January 1877 -- 30 June 1914 ) was an English explorer , hunter , and writer .
Ahmed bey Pepinov Omar oglu ( Azerbaijani : Əhməd bəy Ömər oğlu Pepinov ; 1893 - -1938 ) , also known as Ahmet bey Pepinov , was an Azerbaijani statesman of Meskhetian Turkish origin who served as Minister of Agriculture in the fifth cabinet of Azerbaijan Democratic Republic , and was member of Parliament of Azerbaijan .
Karl Hubbuch ( 21 November 1891 -- 26 December 1979 ) was a German painter , printmaker , and draftsman associated with the New Objectivity .
Marcel Kerff ( Maartensvoeren , 2 June 1866 - Moelingen , 7 August 1914 ) was a Belgian cyclist who participated in the 1903 Tour de France , where he finished sixth .
Erna Viitol ( born on 10 May 1920 -- 11 November 2001 ) was an Estonian sculptor .
Fahredin Nuri ( 24 November 1914 -- 16 November 1984 ) was a notable Albanian hydraulic engineer .
Ragenar ( Latin Ragenarius , French Ragenaire or Réginaire ) was the bishop of Amiens from 830 to 833 and again from 834 until his death in 849 .
Carlos Coimbra ( 1925 -- 14 February 2007 ) was a Brazilian film editor , director and screenwriter .
Thomas William Hodgson Crosland ( July 21 , 1865 or 1868 - -1924 ) , was a British author , poet , journalist and friend of royalty .
James Latimer Allen ( 1907 - 1977 ) was a photographer and portraitist known for his images of the Harlem Renaissance of the 1920s and ' 30s .
Sir Nicholas Pelham ( 1650 ? -- 8 November 1739 ) was a British politician .
Torii Kiyomoto ( Japanese : 鳥居 清元 ; 1645 - -1702 ) was a kabuki actor from Osaka and painter of billboards and other kabuki advertisements ; the founder of the Torii school of artists , he painted in an early form of what came to be known as the ukiyo - e style .
Xiong Yong ( Chinese : 熊勇 , died 838 BC ) was from 847 to 838 BC the 10th viscount of the state of Chu during the Western Zhou Dynasty of ancient China .
Lippo II Alidosi ( also called Litto , died 1350 ) was a ruler of Imola , a member of the Alidosi family .
Boris Berlin ( 27 May 1907 -- 24 March 2001 ) was a Canadian pianist , music educator , arranger , and composer of Russian birth .
Khanai Qobadi ( ca.1700 - -1759 ) was an 18th - century Kurdish Jaff poet , and one of the main Gurani poets .
George McLeod Winsor ( 1856 , Gateshead - 27 July 1939 , Isleworth , Middlesex ) was a British writer .
Johan Wilfred John `` Mick '' Mibus , known as Wilfred Mibus or Mick Mibus ( 14 September 1900 -- 18 April 1964 ) was an Australian politician .
Fung King Hey ( Simplified Chinese : 冯景禧 ; Traditional Chinese : 馮景禧 ) ( 1922 - -1985 ) , was a Chinese - born Canadian businessman .
William Joseph Bryan , Jr. ( 1926 - -1977 ) was an American physician and a pioneering hypnotist .
Rudolph Cartier ( born Rudolph Kacser , renamed himself in Germany to Rudolph Katscher ; 17 April 1904 -- 7 June 1994 ) was an Austrian television director , filmmaker , screenwriter and producer who worked predominantly in British television , exclusively for the BBC .
Charles Wycliffe Goodwin ( 1817 - -1878 ) was a British Egyptologist , bible scholar , lawyer and judge .
Dionigi Galletto ( 26 January 1932 -- 25 September 2011 ) was an Italian mathematician and academician .
Joseph Bourret ( 10 June 1802 -- 5 March 1859 ) was a 19th - century Canadian lawyer , banker and politician .
Charles - Fernand de Condamy ( 1855 - 1913 ) was a French animal painter .
Cecil Harmsworth King ( 20 February 1901 -- 17 April 1987 ) was chairman of Daily Mirror Newspapers , Sunday Pictorial Newspapers and the International Publishing Corporation ( 1963 - -68 ) , and a director at the Bank of England ( 1965 - -68 ) .
Henri Chopin ( 18 June 1922 -- 3 January 2008 ) was an avant - garde poet and musician .
Major - General Sir Ivor Philipps KCB , DSO ( 9 September 1861 -- 15 August 1940 ) was a British officer in the British Indian Army and a Liberal Party politician .
Henry Rowland - Brown ( 1865 , Woodridings , Pinner -- 1921 , Harrow Weald , London ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera By profession Rowland - Brown was a journalist and author .
José Alves de Cerqueira César ( May 23 , 1835 -- July 26 , 1911 ) was a Brazilian politician , governor of the State of São Paulo from December 1891 to August 1892 .
Sir Thomas Carus SL ( c.1515 - -5 July 1571 ) was an English barrister and judge who served as a Justice of the Queen 's Bench .
Louis - Paul M'Fédé ( 26 February 1961 -- 10 June 2013 ) was a Cameroonian soccer player who played midfield .
Charles Ingram , 9th Viscount of Irvine ( 19 March 1727 -- 27 June 1778 ) , known as Charles Ingram until 1763 , was a British landowner , politician and courtier .
Francis Ayscough ( 1701 - -1763 ) was a tutor to George III and Clerk of the Closet to his father Frederick , Prince of Wales and later Dean of Bristol Cathedral .
Rosina Megan Boyd ( 29 January 1915 -- 15 November 2001 ) was a British fly tyer most noted for her Atlantic salmon flies .
Thomas de Beauchamp , 12th Earl of Warwick , KG ( 16 March 1338 -- 8 April 1401 ) was an English medieval nobleman , and one of the primary opponents of Richard II .
Shafi Inamdar ( Marathi : शफी इनामदार ; 23 October 1945 -- 13 March 1996 ) was an Indian actor .
Paul Hankar ( 11 December 1859 -- 17 January 1901 ) was a Belgian architect and furniture designer , and an innovator in the Art Nouveau style .
Thomas Fairfax , 5th Lord Fairfax of Cameron ( 16 April 1657 -- 6 January 1710 N.S. ) was an English politician .
Elsie Wilkins Sexton ( née Wing , 27 April 1868 -- 18 February 1959 ) was an English zoologist and biological illustrator .
Carl McCunn ( 1946 -- December 18 , 1981 ) was an American wildlife photographer who became stranded in the Alaskan wilderness and eventually committed suicide when he ran out of supplies .
Andrew MacLeish ( 26 June 1838 -- 14 January 1928 ) was a Scottish and American businessman .
Archibald Kennedy , 2nd Marquess of Ailsa , KT ( 25 August 1816 -- 20 March 1870 ) was a Scottish peer .
Morten Leuch ( 15 April 1732 -- 24 January 1768 ) was a Norwegian timber trader and landowner .
Martha Cheavens ( 1899 - -1975 ) was an American novelist , short - story writer and poet , several of whose works were adapted for the screen .
Carl August von Steinheil ( 12 October 1801 -- 14 September 1870 ) was a German physicist , inventor , engineer and astronomer .
Ursula Meyer ( 1915 - -2003 ) was a German - born American artist and a professor of sculpture .
Johann Vesque von Püttlingen ( pseudonym Johann Hoven ) ( 23 July 1803 -- 29 October 1883 ) , born J. Vesque de Puttelange , was an Austrian lawyer , diplomat , author , composer and singer .
Frederick James Sargood ( 1805 -- 15 January 1873 ) was a merchant and politician in colonial Victoria , a member of the Victorian Legislative Council and Victorian Legislative Assembly .
Johann Christian Thomae ( 5 April 1668 , Heldburg , Duchy of Saxe - Gotha - Altenburg -- 19 March 1724 , Neustadt bei Coburg , Duchy of Saxe - Coburg ) was a German historian and biographer and a Lutheran rector of Neustadt bei Coburg .
Fritz Sarasin , full name Karl Friedrich Sarasin ( 3 December 1859 -- 23 March 1942 ) was a Swiss naturalist .
Sir Edmund Fowell , 1st Baronet ( 1593 -- October 1674 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1640 to 1648 and in 1656 .
Harry Powlett , 4th Duke of Bolton PC ( 24 July 1691 -- 9 October 1759 ) , known until 1754 as Lord Harry Powlett , was a British nobleman and Whig politician , the second son of Charles Paulet , 2nd Duke of Bolton and Frances Ramsden .
Cui Lin ( died 244 ) , courtesy name Deru , was a high government official of the state of Cao Wei in the Three Kingdoms period .
Leo II of Galicia , also known as Lev Yurevich ( unknown -- 1323 ) was Prince of Lutsk and Galicia , one of the last two Rurikid kings of Galicia - Volhynia ( r. 1308 - -1323 ; according to some sources , 1315 - -23 ) .
Kerttu Nuorteva ( 10 November 1912 , Astoria , Oregon , United States - 29 August 29 1963 , Karaganda , Kazakh Soviet Socialist Republic , Soviet Union ) was a Soviet intelligence agent .
Clarence Hutchenrider ( 13 June 1908 - 18 August 1991 ) was an American jazz clarinetist born in Waco , Texas .
K. C. Hsiao ( Chinese : 蕭公權 ; pinyin : Xiāo Gōngquán ; 29 December 1897 -- 4 November 1981 ) was a Chinese scholar and educator , best known for his contributions to Chinese political science and history .
Philip Long ( died 1832 ) was an American colonist who remained loyal to the British government during the American War of Independence .
David Ayton , Sr . ( 25 May 1857 -- 30 January 1931 ) was a Scottish professional golfer who played in the late 19th century .
Edmund Aikin ( 2 October 1780 -- 11 March 1820 ) was an English architect and writer on architecture .
Arthur Christiansen ( 27 July 1904 -- 27 September 1963 ) was a journalist , and editor of Lord Beaverbrook 's newspaper the Daily Express from 1933 to 1957 .
Paul Tossanus ( Toussain ) ( 1572 - -1634 ) was a Huguenot minister , who spent most of his life in Germany .
Francis Brokesby or Brookesbuy ( 1637 - -1714 ) , was a nonjuror .
Minor Cooper Keith ( 19 January 1848 -- 14 June 1929 ) was an American businessman whose railroad , commercial agriculture , and shipping enterprises much influenced the national economies of the Central American countries , and that of Colombia .
Arthur Tiley ( 17 January 1910 -- 5 June 1994 ) was a British Conservative and National Liberal politician .
Harris Leuke Ratwatte ( known as Harris Leuke Ratwatte Dissawa ) ( 1900 - 1964 ) was a Ceylonese legislator .
Barton Booth ( 1681 -- 10 May 1733 ) was one of the most famous dramatic actors of the first part of the 18th century .
Georg Ludwig Engelhard Krebs ( 19 July 1792 - 11 May 1844 ) was a German apothecary and natural history collector who spent his entire career in South Africa .
La Voisin was convicted of witchcraft and was burned in public on the Place de Grève in Paris the 22 February 1680 .
Sant Garib Das ( 1717 - -1778 ) was a Yogi and called Acharaya ( one who is teacher to saints ) , spiritual reformer and founder of the Garibdasi panth ( a section who follow his preachings ) .
Eric Haraldsson ( Old Norse : Eiríkr Haraldsson , Norwegian : Eirik Haraldsson ; c. 885 -- 954 ) , nicknamed Eric Bloodaxe ( Old Norse : Eiríkr blóðøx , Norwegian : Eirik Blodøks ) , was a 10th - century Norwegian ruler .

Hans Hilfiker ( 15 September 1901 -- 2 March 1993 ) was a Swiss engineer and designer .
Sir Hugh Low , GCMG ( 10 May 1824 -- 18 April 1905 ) was a British colonial administrator and naturalist .
Robert William Keate ( 16 June 1814 -- 17 March 1873 ) was a career British colonial governor , serving as Commissioner of the Seychelles from 1850 to 1852 , Governor of Trinidad from 1857 to 1864 , of Natal from 1867 to 1872 , and of Gold Coast from 7 March 1873 to 17 March 1873 .
Ultrix ( officially all - caps ULTRIX ) is the brand name of Digital Equipment Corporation 's ( DEC ) discontinued native Unix operating systems .

The Hohenzollern Locomotive Works ( Aktiengesellschaft für Lokomotivbau Hohenzollern ) was a German locomotive - building company which operated from 1872 to 1929 .
Eastern Air Lines was a major American airline from 1926 to 1991 .
The Reconstruction Finance Corporation ( RFC ) was a government corporation in the United States that operated between 1932 and 1957 which provided financial support to state and local governments and made loans to banks , railroads , mortgage associations and other businesses .
The Prussian Landkreis Regenwalde in Pomerania was a rural district that existed between 1818 and 1945 .
Sieradz Voivodeship ( Polish : województwo sieradzkie ) was a unit of administrative division and local government in Poland in the years 1975 - -1998 , superseded by Łódź Voivodeship .

Uppland County , or Upplands län , was a county of the Swedish Empire from 1634 to 1641 , and from 1654 to 1714 .
The Kingdom of Kaffa ( c. 1390 - -1897 ) was an early modern state located in what is now Ethiopia , with its first capital at Bonga .

WVEP is a Public Radio formatted broadcast radio station licensed to Martinsburg , West Virginia , serving the Eastern Panhandle and the Potomac Highlands in West Virginia and the Northern Shenandoah Valley in Virginia .
Licensed to Lakeland , Florida , USA , the station is currently owned by WWAB Radio , Inc.

CFOS is an AM radio station broadcasting from downtown Owen Sound , Ontario , Canada .
KXNO is a sports radio station based in Des Moines , Iowa .

WFAN - FM ( 101.9 FM ) , also known as Sports Radio 66 and 101.9 FM or The Fan , is a sports radio station located in New York City .

KQUS - FM ( 97.5 FM ) , known as `` US97 '' , is a country music formatted radio station located in Hot Springs , Arkansas .

George Downie ( 19 January 1778 -- 11 September 1814 ) was a Scottish officer of the British Royal Navy who , during the War of 1812 , commanded a British squadron which fought an American squadron on Lake Champlain in the Battle of Plattsburgh , during which he was killed .
The Irish Guards ( IG ) , part of the Guards Division , is one of the Foot Guards regiments of the British Army and , together with the Royal Irish Regiment , it is one of the two Irish infantry regiments still remaining in the British Army .
The 1st Assault Brigade Royal Engineers was a specialisied armoured formation of the British Army active in World War II . It was formed in mid-1943 and its structure was three Assault Regiments of the Royal Engineers .

Colonel Katherine Amelia Towle ( April 30 , 1898 - March 1 , 1986 ) was the second Director of the United States Marine Corps Women 's Reserve ( USMCWR ) and the first Director of Women Marines .
James Alms ( 15 July 1728 -- 8 June 1791 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy who saw service during the War of the Austrian Succession , the Carnatic and Seven Years ' War and the American War of Independence , rising to the rank of post - captain .
Admiral John Surman Carden ( 15 August 1771 -- 22 April 1858 ) was an officer of the British Royal Navy in the early nineteenth century .

The Corps of Royal Engineers , usually just called the Royal Engineers ( RE ) , and commonly known as the Sappers , is one of the corps of the British Army .
Harry Hammond Hess ( May 24 , 1906 -- August 25 , 1969 ) was a geologist and United States Navy officer in World War II . Considered one of the `` founding fathers '' of the unifying theory of plate tectonics , Rear Admiral Harry Hammond Hess was born on May 24 , 1906 in New York City .
Sir Francis Geary , 1st Baronet ( 1709 -- 7 February 1796 ) was an officer of the Royal Navy .

Vice - Admiral Sir Edward Michael Conolly Abel Smith GCVO CB JP ( 3 December 1899 -- 3 December 1985 ) was a Vice - Admiral in the British Royal Navy who served during the First and Second World Wars .
Klaus Uebe ( 1 May 1900 -- 3 February 1968 ) was a German Luftwaffe Generalmajor and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) during World War II . The Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership .
General Henry Edward Fox ( 4 March 1755 -- 18 July 1811 ) was a British Army general .

Robert J. Kelly ( born March 4 , 1938 ) is a retired United States Navy four star admiral who served as Commander in Chief , United States Pacific Fleet ( CINCPACFLT ) from 1991 to 1994 .
The 30th Armoured Brigade ( created on 27 December 1940 ) was a World War II British Army unit that served in the campaign in Western Europe as part of the 79th Armoured Division .
Milan Ćopić ( 4 December 1897 -- 1941 ) was a Croatian communist who was in the International Brigades prison at Camp Lucász during the Spanish Civil War .

The Household Cavalry ( HCav ) is made up of the two most senior regiments of the British Army , the Life Guards and the Blues and Royals ( Royal Horse Guards and 1st Dragoons ) .
Rear Admiral Robert O. Wray , Jr. , United States Navy , is a businessman , author and retired two - star admiral who recently served as the President of INSURV , the Navy 's Board of Inspection and Survey .
