Stanisław Grodzicki ( 1912 in Ostrołęka -- 1946 near Orpington ) was a Polish fighter pilot and a Major of the Polish Air Force during World War II . He fought during The Blitz in 1941 as a night fighter pilot with No . 307 Polish Fighter Squadron , flying the Boulton Paul Defiant .
Rudolf Anderson , Jr. ( September 15 , 1927 -- October 27 , 1962 ) , was a pilot and commissioned officer in the United States Air Force and the first recipient of the Air Force Cross , the U.S. Air Force 's second - highest award for heroism .

The Queen 's Own Dorset Yeomanry was a yeomanry regiment of the British Army founded in 1794 as the Dorsetshire Regiment of Volunteer Yeomanry Cavalry in response to the growing threat of invasion during the Napoleonic wars .
Major General Clifford Coffin VC , CB , DSO & Bar ( 10 February 1870 -- 4 February 1959 ) was an officer in the British Army and was a recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .

Mann & Machine is an American science fiction / police drama series that aired for nine episodes on NBC from April 5 , 1992 to July 14 , 1992 .

Amazing Eats is an American food reality television series that premiered on January 11 , 2012 on the Travel Channel .
Keeping Up with the Kardashians ( abbreviated KUWTK ) is an American reality television series that airs on the E ! cable network and focuses on the personal and professional lives of the Kardashian--
The PBA on BBC was a presentation of Philippine Basketball Association games on Banahaw Broadcasting Corporation .
Aquele Beijo ( English : That Kiss ) is a Brazilian telenovela produced by Rede Globo and exhibited in the schedule of 19 hours .
International Playhouse is the name of an American television series that was broadcast on the now - defunct DuMont Television Network during 1951 .
Trippin is a Malaysian infotainment programme produced by 8TV , which sees local celebrities or ( beginning season two ) ordinary citizens being taken to various tourist attractions in the country , and involved in recreational activities , ranging from appreciation of arts and culture to extreme sports .
Catwalk Dogs is a British television film written by Simon Nye and produced by Shed Productions for ITV .
The Burn with Jeff Ross is a comedy panel show hosted by comedian Jeff Ross that aired on Comedy Central .
19 Kids and Counting ( formerly 17 Kids and Counting and 18 Kids and Counting ) , rendered graphically as 19 kids & Counting in its onscreen logo , is an American reality television show that aired on the cable channel TLC for seven years , until its cancellation in 2015 .
16 Wishes is a 2010 Canadian - American television film starring Debby Ryan and Jean - Luc Bilodeau , which premiered on June 25 , 2010 on Disney Channel and July 16 , 2010 on the Family Channel .
You Wrote It , You Watch It is an MTV sketch comedy series starring members of The State comedy troupe before they were given their own show by the network .
Wild Brazil is a British nature documentary series , first broadcast on BBC Two and BBC Two HD in January 2014 .
Hanggang Kailan ( English : Circle of Hearts ) is a Filipino drama series produced by GMA Network .
Zach Stone Is Gon na Be Famous is an American television comedy series created by comedian Bo Burnham and Dan Lagana that aired on MTV from May 2 to June 29 , 2013 .
Fat Guy Stuck in Internet is an American live - action science fiction comedy television series on Cartoon Network 's late night programming block , Adult Swim .
Five Years in the Life is a Canadian reality television series which aired on CBC Television from 1968 to 1972 .
The Wild Thornberrys is an American animated television series that aired on Nickelodeon .
Kourtney and Kim Take New York is an American reality television series that premiered January 23 , 2011 , on E ! and ran for two seasons .
Hello , Larry is an American sitcom that aired on NBC from January 26 , 1979 , to April 30 , 1980 .
Familie is produced by Studio - A and runs on vtm .
Unchained Reaction is a science and engineering reality game show that airs on the Discovery Channel .
Winners & Losers is an Australian television drama series first broadcast on the Seven Network on 22 March 2011 .
You Have Been Watching is a British comedy panel game presented by Charlie Brooker , produced by Zeppotron for Channel 4 and filmed at BBC Television Centre ( pilot and series 2 ) and Riverside Studios ( series 1 ) in London .
Skithouse ( styled skitHOUSE ) was an Australian sketch comedy television series that ran on Network Ten from 9 February 2003 to 28 July 2004 .
Lulu 's Islands ( French : Les Mistigris , originally Lulu la Peste ) is an animated series for children that premiered on 5 October 2009 , on the TFOU block of France 's TF1 network .
Dark of Night is an American dramatic anthology series that aired on the now - defunct DuMont Television Network which aired Fridays at 8:30pm EST from October 3 , 1952 to May 1 , 1953 .
Girls Behaving Badly is an American reality comedy television show on the Oxygen cable channel , and is also syndicated to television stations across the United States and Canada by Sony Pictures Television .
Monday Mornings is an American medical drama television series that ran on TNT from February 4 to April 8 , 2013 and aired Mondays after Dallas .
The Planners is a British television documentary series broadcast on BBC Two .
Chelmsford 123 is a British television situation comedy produced for Channel 4 by Hat Trick Productions .
Special Ops Mission is an American reality television series that premiered on August 13 , 2009 on the Military Channel ( now American Heroes Channel ) .
Rude Tube is a British television programme broadcast on Channel 4 and its sister channel E4 .
Football This Week was a TV sports program broadcast on the DuMont Television Network .
Stachys is in the subfamily Lamioideae .
Oncocnemidinae is a subfamily of moths which belong to the large moth family ( Noctuidae ) .
Lepidochrysops is a genus of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family .
Hyalimax is a genus of small , air - breathing , land slugs , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Succineidae , the amber snails .
Haplorhini ( the haplorhines or the `` dry - nosed '' primates , the Greek name means `` simple - nosed '' ) is a clade containing the tarsiers and the simians ( or anthropoids ) .
Acaenitinae is a subfamily of the parasitic wasp family Ichneumonidae .
Gundolficeras is member of the Tornoceratidae , ( goniatitid ammonites ) , from the Late Devonian named by Becker , 1995 and assigned to the Falcitornoceratinae .
The Kretschmarr Cave mold beetle ( Texamaurops reddelli ) is a small mold beetle that is in the kingdom Animalia , the phylum Arthropoda , the class Insecta , the order Coleopetera ( beetles ) , the suborder Polyphaga , the family Pselaphide ( mold beetle ) .
Spathanthus is a group of plants in the family Rapateaceae described as a genus in 1828 .
Bison occidentalis is an extinct species of bison that lived in North America from about 11,000 to 5,000 years ago , spanning the end of the Pleistocene to the mid - Holocene .
The Bengal danio or Sind danio ( Devario devario ) is a subtropical fish belonging to the minnow family ( Cyprinidae ) .
Eucestoda is the larger of the two subclasses of flatworms in the class Cestoda ( the other subclass is Cestodaria ) .
Pycina is a genus of butterflies in the Nymphalidae family found from Mexico to South America .
The Yungas tree frog , Hypsiboas balzani , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Bolivia and Peru .
Pristiglomidae is a family of small saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the order Nuculoida .
Hershkovitz 's titi ( Callicebus dubius ) is a species of titi , a type of New World monkey , from South America .
Hoplocampa is a genus of Hymenopteran sawfly in the Tenthredinidae family .
The Seoul frog or Seoul pond frog ( Pelophylax chosenicus ) is a species of true frog found on the southern and western Korean Peninsula , and possibly across the border to China in Liaoning .
Anthostema is a flowering plant genus in the Family Euphorbiaceae ( Spurge family ) first described as a genus in 1824 .
Asthenoceras belongs to the Hildoceratidae ( subfamily Grammoceratinae ) and may be a subgenus of the Lower Jurassic ( Upper Toarcian ) Grammoceras .
Marantochloa is a genus of plant in family Marantaceae described as a genus in 1860 .
The Parras pupfish ( Cyprinodon latifasciatus ) was a species of pupfish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
Creighton 's slender opossum ( Marmosops creightoni ) , also known commonly as Voss ' slender opossum is a species of South American opossum of the family Didelphidae .
Turkeypox virus is a virus of the family Poxviridae and the genus Avipoxvirus that causes turkeypox .
Anniealexandria is the only known member of the family Bipedidae in the fossil record , which otherwise only includes the extant genus Bipes from Mexico .
Claviella besucheti is a species of beetle in the family Dermestidae , the only species in the genus Claviella .
The Chironomoidea are a superfamily within the order Diptera , suborder Nematocera , infraorder Culicomorpha .
Storey 's African mole - rat ( Tachyoryctes storeyi ) is a species of rodents in the family Spalacidae endemic to Kenya .
The Holosporaceae are a family of bacteria , formerly included in the order Rickettsiales , but now raised to their own order , the Holosporales .
The Odontotremataceae are a family of saprobic fungi in the order Ostropales .
Shizocera is a genus of sawfly in the family Argidae .
The Choco broad - nosed bat ( Platyrrhinus chocoensis ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae .
Galeus is a genus of catshark , belonging to the family Scyliorhinidae , commonly known as sawtail catsharks in reference to a distinctive saw - toothed crest of enlarged dermal denticles , found along the upper edges of their caudal fins .
Chaetosaurus emeishanicola is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Chaetosaurus .
Gervais ' beaked whale ( Mesoplodon europaeus ) , sometimes known as the Antillian beaked whale , Gulf Stream beaked whale , or European beaked whale ( from which its scientific name is derived ) is the most frequently stranding type of mesoplodont whale off the coast of North America .
Skottsbergia is a monotypic genus of moss in the family Ditrichaceae containing the single species Skottsbergia paradoxa .
The Udine shrew ( Sorex arunchi ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Chaetodiadema is a genus of sea urchins of the Family Diadematidae .
Acutimitoceras is a genus belonging to the Acutimitoceratinae subfamily of the Prionoceratidae family , a member of the Goniatitida order .
Thabanchuia is an extinct genus of dvinosaurian temnospondyl within the family Tupilakosauridae .
Kaiser 's spotted newt ( Neurergus kaiseri ) , also known as the Luristan newt or emperor spotted Newt ( not to be confused with Tylototriton shanjing ) , is a species of very colourful salamander in the Salamandridae family .
The Pacific black duck ( Anas superciliosa ) is a dabbling duck found in much of Indonesia , New Guinea , Australia , New Zealand , and many islands in the southwestern Pacific , reaching to the Caroline Islands in the north and French Polynesia in the east .
Günther 's black snake , Bothrolycus ater , is a species of poorly known colubrid snake endemic to central Africa .
Cereatta is a harvestman genus in the family Assamiidae .
Gugheorites is a genus of beetle in the family Carabidae .
Paratessaropa brachyptera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Paratessaropa .
The Namaqua dove ( Oena capensis ) is a small pigeon .
Largen 's clawed frog or the Sidamo clawed frog ( Xenopus largeni ) is a species of frog in the Pipidae family .
Pomacanthus rhomboides ( Old woman angelfish ) is a large angelfish growing up to 45 cm , found in the western Indian Ocean .
Isopogon is a genus of 35 species of mainly low - growing and prostrate perennial shrubs in the family Proteaceae endemic to Australia .
Aiolopus is a genus of grasshopper belonging to the family Acrididae , subfamily Oedipodinae .
The Siberian flying squirrel ( Pteromys volans ) is an Old World flying squirrel with a range from the Baltic Sea in the west to the Pacific coast in the east .
The Waitaha penguin ( Megadyptes waitaha ) is an extinct species of New Zealand penguin discovered in November 2008 .
Unenlagiinae is a subfamily of Dromaeosauridae .
Conoclypus - from the Greek words Konos (= cone ) + clypus (= disc ) - is a genus of sea urchins belonging to the family Conoclypeidae .
The Jeju salamander , also spelled Cheju salamander , Hynobius quelpaertensis , is a species of salamander found on various islands and peninsulas off the southwestern coast of the Korean Peninsula , including Jindo , Geojedo , Jejudo , and Namhae .
Westralunio is a genus of freshwater mussels in the family Hyriidae .
Gekkoninae is a diverse subfamily of the family Gekkonidae , geckos .
Closterium is a genus of unicellular charophyte green algae in the family Closteriaceae .
Albatrellus is a genus of 19 species of mushroom - producing fungi in the family Albatrellaceae .
Gyldenstolpe 's worm skink ( Isopachys gyldenstolpei ) is a species of skink in the family Scincidae .
Althenia is a genus of aquatic plants of the family Potamogetonaceae .
Neanaperiallus is an extinct monotypic genus of parasitic wasp in the Eupelmidae subfamily Neanastatinae containing only a single species , Neanaperiallus masneri .
The Brazilian tinamou ( Crypturellus strigulosus ) is a type of tinamou found in lowland moist forest in subtropical and tropical regions of Amazonian South America .
The Malayan shrew ( Crocidura malayana ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Caspian goby ( Neogobius caspius ) is a species of fish endemic to the Caspian Sea where it is only found in brackish waters .
Thomas 's rock rat ( Aethomys thomasi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae found only in Angola .
Iberoporus cermenius is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Iberoporus .
Nemopoda is a genus of flies belonging to the family Sepsidae .
Flabellipecten is a genus of large scallops or saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Miodytiscus hirtipes is a species of beetle in the family Dytiscidae , the only species in the genus Miodytiscus .
Picrodendron is a genus of plant belonging to the family Picrodendraceae described as a genus in 1859 .
Tetroncium is a genus of plants in the Juncaginaceae described as a genus in 1808 .
The Tent - web spiders ( genus Cyrtophora ) , although technically orb - web spiders ( family Araneidae ) , do not build orb webs .
Anguispira is a genus of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Discidae , the disk snails .
Bolle 's pigeon ( Columba bollii ) is a species of the genus Columba of family Columbidae , doves and pigeons , endemic to the Canary Islands , Spain .
Parambassis is a genus of freshwater fish in the Asiatic glassfish family Ambassidae of order Perciformes .
Trochotoma is a genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pleurotomariidae , the slit snails .
Periophthalmus novemradiatus , Pearse 's mudskipper , is a species of mudskippers native to marine and brackish waters along the coasts of India .
Zemacies is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Borsoniidae
The European rabbit or common rabbit ( Oryctolagus cuniculus ) is a species of rabbit native to southwestern Europe ( Spain and Portugal ) and northwest Africa ( Morocco and Algeria ) .
Wahoo ( Acanthocybium solandri ) is a scombrid fish found worldwide in tropical and subtropical seas .
Laguncularia is a genus of plants in the family Combretaceae , with 10 species :
Truncocolumella is a genus of fungi in the family Suillaceae , of the order Boletales .
Blancocamelus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America during the Pliocene through Pleistocene 4.9 mya--300,000 years ago , existing for approximately 4.6 million years .
The Appalachian azure ( Celastrina neglectamajor ) is a butterfly in the gossamer wings family Lycaenidae .
Loxosporopsis is a genus of lichenized fungi in the Pertusariaceae family .
Octosquid is the name given to what appears to be a new species of the genus Mastigoteuthis which was discovered at a depth of 3,000 feet ( 910 m ) off the Hawaiian Islands in the summer of 2007 .
Anacardium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Anacardiaceae , native to tropical regions of the Americas .
Meller 's mongoose ( Rhynchogale melleri ) is a species of mongoose .
The Mauritius night heron ( Nycticorax mauritianus ) is an extinct night heron species from Mauritius .
Uncites is an extinct genus of Brachiopods in the family Uncitidae .
The Nicaraguan slider ( Trachemys emolli ) is a species of turtle found in Nicaragua and Costa Rica .
Myoida is an order of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the subclass Heterodonta .
Bletia is a genus of about 30 species of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) , almost all of which are terrestrial ; some are occasionally lithophytic or epiphytic .
The Russian bitterling ( Acheilognathus asmussii ) , or spiny bitterling , is a temperate freshwater fish belonging to the Acheilognathinae sub - family of the Cyprinidae family .
Bedriaga 's fringe - fingered lizard ( Acanthodactylus bedriagai ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
The Rodrigues solitaire ( Pezophaps solitaria ) is an extinct , flightless bird that was endemic to the island of Rodrigues , east of Madagascar in the Indian Ocean .
Karin Hills frog ( Brachytarsophrys ) is a genus of the Megophryidae family in the order Anura , and are found in southern China , Myanmar , northern Thailand and northern Vietnam .
Melanolestes is a Nearctic and Neotropical genus of assassin bugs ( Reduviidae ) .
Capnophyllum africanum is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , the only member of the genus Capnophyllum .
Watson 's climbing rat ( Tylomys watsoni ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Japanese giant salamander ( Andrias japonicus ) is endemic to Japan , where it is known as Ōsanshōuo ( オオサンショウウオ/大山椒魚 ) , literally meaning `` giant pepper fish '' .
Przewalski 's gerbil , Brachiones przewalskii , is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Euglossa is a genus of orchid bees ( Euglossini ) .
Diastylis is a genus of crustaceans which belong to the family Diastylidae .
Lianema tenuicornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Lianema .
Rilaena is a genus of the harvestman family Phalangiidae .
Lactifluus volemus , formerly known as Lactarius volemus , is a species of fungus in the family Russulaceae .
The Karpathos frog ( Pelophylax cerigensis ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
The Natranaerobiales are an order of bacteria placed within the class Clostridia .
The Zimmer 's tapaculo ( Scytalopus zimmeri ) is a species of passerine bird in the Rhinocryptidae family .
The Jamaican becard ( Pachyramphus niger ) is a species of bird in the family Tityridae .
Cryptobias coccineus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Cryptobias .
Thaumeledone is a genus of octopuses in the family Octopodidae found in deep waters in the Southern Hemisphere .
The Tasmanian masked owl ( Tyto novaehollandiae castanops ) is a bird in the barn owl family Tytonidae that is endemic to the island state of Tasmania , Australia .
Anteon is the largest genus in the subfamily Anteoninae of the family Dryinidae .
The Santa Marta woodstar ( Chaetocercus astreans ) is a species of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
The Pacific gull ( Larus pacificus ) is a very large gull , native to the coasts of Australia .
The Olaʻa banana hedyleptan moth ( Omiodes euryprora ) is a species of moth in the Crambidae family .
The Palau ground dove ( Gallicolumba canifrons ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Cytora is a genus of very small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Pupinidae .
Plagiaulacidae is a family of fossil mammals within the order Multituberculata .
The Réunion pink pigeon ( Nesoenas duboisi , but see below ) is an extinct species of pigeon that formerly lived on the Mascarene island of Réunion .
Rickett 's big - footed bat ( Myotis pilosus ) is a species of vesper bat .
The Ceylon tree nymph or Ceylon tree - nymph ( Idea iasonia ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Orobus is an old genus of Fabaceae family , which is now divided in the following genera :
Hemipsocidae is a family of Psocoptera belonging to the infraorder Psocetae .
Goethea is a genus of plants of the family Malvaceae , commonly placed instead in the genus Pavonia .
Sarcaulus is a genus of plants in family Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1882 .
The Tasmanian codling , Eeyorius hutchinsi , is a species of morid cod only known from the waters around Tasmania and the Australian states of Western Australia and Victoria .
Gunning 's golden mole ( Neamblysomus gunningi ) is a small mammal endemic to South Africa .
Betula fruticosa ( Chinese : 柴桦 ; pinyin : chai hua ) is a species of dwarf birch that grows in central and eastern Europe ( except for Finland where it grows rare ) and Siberia and Mongolia on elevation of 600 - -1,100 metres ( 2,000 - -3,600 ft ) in forests , streambanks , and swamps .
Miller 's snail , scientific name Cochliopina milleri , is a species of very small freshwater snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae , the mud snails .
Horaga is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae which Eliot , 1973 , places in the tribe Horagini of the Sub - Family Theclinae .
Brontolaemus is a genus of beetles in the family Laemophloeidae that is found only in the Hawaiian Islands .
D'Anchieta 's fruit bat ( Plerotes anchietae ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Tubuliporina is a bryozoan suborder in the order Cyclostomatida .
Spondylidini is a tribe of beetles in the family Spondylidinae , containing the following genera and species :
In taxonomy , Pseudocodium is a genus of green algae , of the family Pseudocodiaceae .
The Moroccan worm lizard ( Blanus mettetali ) is a species of reptile in the Blanidae family .
Montcellia is an extinct genus of nectridean lepospondyl within the family Urocordylidae that lived in the late Carboniferous period in the modern France .
Mikhail A. Fedonkin places Ovatoscutum in the extinct bilaterian phylum Proarticulata .
Cannomois is a group of plants in the Restionaceae described as a genus in 1828 .
Ctenobrycon is a genus of fish of the family Characidae found in tropical South America , with five currently recognized species in this genus .
Goodmania is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae containing the single species Goodmania luteola .
Monotherium is an extinct genus of phocid belonging to the subfamily Monachinae .
The Indian eyed turtle ( Morenia petersi ) is a species of turtle found in northeastern India ( as far west as Bihar ) and Bangladesh .
Daphniidae is a family of water fleas in the sub - order Anomopoda .
The Smooth alligatorfish ( Anoplagonus inermis , also known as the Smooth poacher or the Smooth sea - poacher ) is a fish in the family Agonidae ( poachers ) .
Scaloposauria and Silpholestidae are no longer regarded as valid groups , and Ictidodraco is now classified as a basal member of the clade Baurioidea .
Austrotrochaclis is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Ataphridae , the false top snails .
Dombeyoideae are a subfamily of the Malvaceae in the wide circumscription , as proposed by the APG .
Ziegler 's water rat ( Hydromys ziegleri ) discovered in the mid-2000s by science , is a species of rodent native to the mountains Papua New Guinea of which little is known .
The Mediterranean sand smelt , Atherina hepsetus , is a species of fish in the Atherinidae family .
The Java loach ( Pangio oblonga ) is a species of tropical freshwater fish , an unbanded kuhli loach , native to the sandy streams of Southeast Asia .
Tongeia is a Palearctic genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae found in temperate East Asia genus . Most species are endemic to China and many taxa ( species ) are recently described from China . The best known species is the more widely distributed Tongeia fischeri ( Eversmann , 1843 ) .
The Andaman crake ( Rallina canningi ) is a bird species in the family Rallidae .
Protomallocera hilairei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Protomallocera .
The Sulawesi cuckoo ( Cuculus crassirostris ) is a species of cuckoo in the Cuculidae family .
Philornis is a genus of around 50 species of fly ( Diptera , Muscidae ) from Central and South America .
The Aphrodite fritillary ( Speyeria aphrodite ) is a fritillary butterfly , from North America .
Pythonichthys is a genus of eels of the family Heterenchelyidae that occur in tropical waters of the eastern Pacific Ocean off of Panama and in the Atlantic Ocean near the Caribbean Sea and the west coast of Africa .
The Sierra Madre sparrow ( Xenospiza baileyi ) , also known as Bailey 's sparrow , is an endangered , range - restricted , enigmatic American sparrow .
Philippen 's striped turtle , `` Ocadia '' philippeni , has recently shown to be an intergeneric hybrid ( Stuart & Parham , 2006 ) between a male Mauremys sinensis and a female Cuora trifasciata .
The Panamanian night monkey or Chocoan night monkey ( Aotus zonalis ) is a species of night monkey formerly considered a subspecies of the gray - bellied night monkey of the family Aotidae .
The Nile monitor ( Varanus niloticus ) is a large member of the monitor lizard family ( Varanidae ) found throughout much of Africa but absent from the west where it is replaced by Varanus stellatus .
Rhopalostyla virgata is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Rhopalostyla .
Otoceratina is an extinct suborder of cephalopods belonging to the Ammonite subclass in the order Ceratitida .
Semotilus is the genus of creek chubs , ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Windowpane flounder ( Scophthalmus aquosus ) is a fish species in the family Scophthalmidae .
Winkelmann 's mouse ( Peromyscus winkelmanni ) is a species of rodents in the family Cricetidae found only in Mexico , and is named for John R. Winkelmann , who collected the first specimens .
Aeolodermus emarginatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Aeolodermus .
The Ryukyu kingfisher ( Todiramphus miyakoensis ) is an enigmatic taxon of tree kingfisher .
Atelecyclidae is a family of crabs belonging to the Cancroidea superfamily , and currently contains eight genera of which two are extinct .
Triuridales was an order of flower plants that was used in the well - known Cronquist system , in the subclass Alismatidae , with this circumscription : order Triuridales family Petrosaviaceae family Triuridaceae The APG II system leaves the first of these two families unassigned in the clade monocots while the second is moved to order Pandanales .
Micropolycesta sirgueyi is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Micropolycesta .
Diastylidae is one of the eight most commonly recognised families of crustaceans of the order Cumacea .
The bellowfishes or bellowsfishes are fishes in the genus Notopogon in the family Centriscidae .
Geocrinia is a genus of frogs in the family Myobatrachidae .
However , Spathicephalus shares several anatomical features with a family of stem tetrapods called Baphetidae , leading most paleontologists who have studied the genus to place it within a larger group called Baphetoidea , often as part of its own monotypic family Spathicephalidae .
The Bougainville monarch ( Monarcha erythrostictus ) is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Bolam 's mouse ( Pseudomys bolami ) is a species of nocturnal , burrowing rodent in the family Muridae that inhabits the semi arid and southern arid regions of Australia .
The Indian flying frog , Pterorana khare , is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Lilioceris is a genus of beetles in the leaf beetle family , Chrysomelidae .
Libytheana is a genus of nymphalid butterflies in the snout butterfly subfamily Libytheinae .
Necydalopsis trizonatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Necydalopsis .
The Mentawai long - tailed giant rat ( Leopoldamys siporanus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Hammatoceras is included in the subfamily Hammatoceratinae , which in the outdated 1957 Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology was part of the Hammatoceratidae , but of the Phymatoceratidae in D.T. Donovan et al .
Hubbard 's sportive lemur ( Lepilemur hubbardorum ) , or the Zombitse sportive lemur , is a sportive lemur endemic to Madagascar .
The Eurasian collared dove ( Streptopelia decaocto ) , most often simply called the collared dove , also sometimes hyphenated as Eurasian collared - dove , is a species of dove native to warm temperate and subtropical Asia , and introduced in North America in 1980s .
Elkhorn coral ( Acropora palmata ) is considered to be one of the most important reef - building corals in the Caribbean .
Alphaproteobacteria is a class of bacteria in the phylum Proteobacteria ( See also bacterial taxonomy ) .
The Simoceratinae is a subfamily in the Aspidoceratidae , a family of ammonites in the Perisphinctaceae , that lived during most of the Late Jurassic , especially in the Pacific and Tethyan realms .
The Larut Hills rice frog ( Microhyla annectens ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
The Brazilian red and white tarantula ( Nhandu chromatus ) is a tarantula species that is native to Brazil .
Diretmoides pauciradiatus ( Woods , 1973 ) ( Longwing spinyfin ) Diretmoides veriginae Kotlyar , 1987
Eubacterium could be either a Gram - positive or Gram - negative bacteria genus in the family Eubacteriaceae .
The Neretvan nase or Dalmatian nase ( Chondrostoma knerii ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Dendrophryniscus is a genus of true toads in the family Bufonidae endemic to the atlantic forests of Brazil , Amazonian Colombia , Ecuador , Peru , and the Guianas .
Rothschild 's woolly rat ( Mallomys rothschildi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .

The Coastal Range newt ( Taricha torosa torosa ) is a subspecies of the California newt ( Taricha torosa ) .
Retusa is a genus of very small head - shield sea snails or barrel - bubble snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Retusidae .
Scolodontidae is a taxonomic family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonategastropod mollusks in the superfamily Rhytidoidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The European turtle dove ( Streptopelia turtur ) is a member of the bird family Columbidae , the doves and pigeons .
The Somali bee - eater ( Merops revoilii ) is a species of bird in the Meropidae family .
Thomas 's sac - winged bat ( Balantiopteryx io ) is a species of sac - winged bat in the family Emballonuridae .
Xenophrys is a genus of amphibians in the Megophryidae family .
Mysidopsis is a genus of mysid shrimps in the family Mysidae .
The Sumatran rhinoceros , also known as hairy rhinoceros or Asian two - horned rhinoceros ( Dicerorhinus sumatrensis ) , is a rare member of the family Rhinocerotidae and one of five extant rhinoceroses .
Sclater 's lark ( Spizocorys sclateri ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Listonella is a genus of Gram - negative marine bacteria in the family Vibrionaceae named after the American microbiologist J. Liston .
The Cimicomorpha comprise an infraorder of the Heteroptera .
The Abd al - Kuri sparrow ( Passer hemileucus ) is a passerine bird endemic to the small island of Abd al Kuri ( also spelled several other ways ) in the Socotra archiplago of the Indian Ocean , off the Horn of Africa .
The MacArthur 's shrew ( Crocidura macarthuri ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Plains leopard frog ( Rana blairi ) It is sometimes referred to as Blair 's leopard frog , named after the noted zoologist and University of Texas professor , Dr. W. Frank Blair .
Metaxanthops acutus is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Metaxanthops .
Phasca is a genus of tephritid or fruit flies in the family J.R. Tephritidae .
The Carpenter 's flasher wrasse , Paracheilinus carpenteri , is a species of wrasse native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Demansia is a genus of snake of the family Elapidae ; members of the genus are commonly known as whip snakes .
Epinotia is a very large genus of tortrix moths ( family Tortricidae ) .
The Alligatorfish ( Aspidophoroides monopterygius , also known commonly as the Aleutian alligatorfish and the Atlantic alligatorfish ) is a fish in the family Agonidae ( poachers ) .
Palaeoechinastacus is the earliest body fossil from the family Parastacidae , and the earliest crayfish from Gondwana .
Heterophyllaea is a genus of three species of shrubs in the family Rubiaceae , native to Bolivia and Argentina .
Haplothismia is a genus of myco - heterotrophic plants in family Burmanniaceae , first described as a genus in 1952 .
Family Ceratopsidae Subfamily Chasmosaurinae Agujaceratops - ( Texas , USA ) Anchiceratops - ( Alberta , Canada ) Arrhinoceratops - ( Alberta , Canada ) Bravoceratops - ( Texas , USA ) Chasmosaurus - ( Alberta , Canada ) Coahuilaceratops - ( Coahuila , Mexico ) ?
Torovirinae is one of two subfamilies of enveloped , positive - stranded RNA viruses in the family Coronaviridae in the order Nidovirales .
Puperita is a genus of snails , gastropod mollusks in the family Neritidae .
Tristram 's bunting ( Emberiza tristrami ) is a species of bird in the Emberizidae family .
Callianassa is a genus of mud shrimps , in the family Callianassidae .
Oryza is situated in tribe Oryzeae , which is characterized morphologically by its single - flowered spikelets whose glumes are almost completely suppressed .
Actinoptilum is a genus of sea pens in the family Echinoptilidae , containing the single species :
Protoscalidion rugia is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Protoscalidion .
Clinothelphusa kakoota is a species of crab in the family Parathelphusidae , which is endemic to Sri Lanka .
Aspatharia is a genus of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Iridinidae .
The Kinabalu giant earthworm , Pheretima darnleiensis , is a grey - blue coloured peregrine annelid native to Mount Kinabalu , Borneo and surrounding islands as well as New Guinea .
Ileostylus is a genus of mistletoes in the family Loranthaceae .
Calodactylodes is a genus of lizards in the family Gekkonidae ( geckos ) distributed in peninsular India and Sri Lanka .
The African terrestrial barbets are the bird genus Trachyphonus in the African barbet family ( Lybiidae ) , which was formerly included in the Capitonidae and sometimes in the Ramphastidae .
The Chinese penduline tit ( Remiz consobrinus ) is a species of bird in the Remizidae family .
Negaprion is a genus of requiem sharks in the family Carcharhinidae , containing the two extant species of lemon sharks : the lemon shark ( N. brevirostris ) of the Americas , and the sicklefin lemon shark ( N. acutidens ) of the Indo - Pacific .
The Lyophyllaceae is a family of fungi in the order Agaricales .
Gibberula is a genus of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Cystiscidae , previously placed in the family Marginellidae , the margin shells or marginellids .
Hormisa was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Macrochilo
Alcorn 's pocket gopher ( Pappogeomys alcorni ) is a species of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
The Rocky Mountain capshell ( Acroloxus coloradensis ) is a species of freshwater snail in the family Acroloxidae , the river limpets .
Gigantostrea is an extinct genus of marine bivalve mollusks belonging to the family Gryphaeidae .
The Papuan hawk - owl ( Uroglaux dimorpha ) is a medium - sized , sleek owl with a proportionately small head , long tail , and short , rounded wings .
The Bornean stubtail ( Urosphena whiteheadi ) is a species of bird in the Cettiidae family .
Eridanosaurus is an extinct genus originally described as a crocodilian , but later shown to be a rhinoceros ( specifically , based on a rhinoceros vertebra ) .
Enneapterygius ornatus , known commonly as the Henderson triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
The Orbiliaceae are a family of saprobic sac fungi in the order Orbiliales .
The Chinese crocodile lizard ( Shinisaurus crocodilurus ) is a semiaquatic lizard found only in cool forests in the Hunan , Guangxi and Guizhou Provinces of China , and the Quảng Ninh Province in Vietnam .
Tepidimonas is a genus of Gram - negative , strictly aerobic , oxidase- and catalase - positive , rod - shaped , slightly thermophilic bacteria from the family Comamonadaceae .
The Weber 's dwarf squirrel ( Prosciurillus weberi ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Fayella is an extinct genus of dissorophoidean temnospondyl amphibian within the family Dissorophidae .
Globigerinana are free living pelagic foraminiferan , included in the class Rotaliata that range from the Jurassic to recent .
Philomycus is a genus of air - breathing land slugs in the family Philomycidae , the mantleslugs .
The subfamily Fulgorariinae contains sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Volutidae .

Michael F. Kresky , Jr. ( May 23 , 1904 -- August 22 , 1978 ) was a member of the Wisconsin State Senate from 1937 to 1939 .
Pietro Parolin ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈpjetro paroˈliŋ ) ; born 17 January 1955 ) is an Italian cardinal of the Catholic Church .

The Texaco Cup was an association football competition involving clubs from England , Northern Ireland , the Republic of Ireland and Scotland that had not qualified for European competitions .
